    class KibanaReporting:
    """|  This class contains methods to perform various operations related to
    elastic search data insertions and reporting."""

    def __init__(self):
        self.cafe_logger = LoggerClass().logger
        self.hookspec = HookspecMarker("pytest")
        self.config_utils = ConfigUtils()
        self.str_project_path = self.config_utils.get_project_path()
        self.is_report = False
        self.python_client_reporting_utils = None
        self.python_client_reporting_config = None
        if "auto_dashboard_report" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
            self.is_report = self.config_utils.base_config.get("auto_dashboard_report")
        else:
            self.cafe_logger.warning(
                "Warning! To push data to reporting server. Add 'auto_dashboard_report' key and its value in config.yml file"
            )
        self.automation_log_path = (
            self.str_project_path + os.sep + "features" + os.sep + pstr_temp_folder_name
        )
        self.take_screenshot_tags = ["ui_web", "ui_thick_client", "mobile_web", "mobile_app"]
        self.str_virtual_directory_path = ""
        self.str_s3_screenshot_path = ""
        self.str_bucket_directory = ""
        self.obj_error_category = ErrorCategory()
        self.aws_session = None
        self.s3_client = None

    def scenario_fail_step_def_error(self):
        try:
            if self.is_report:
                globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_failed"] = "Yes"

        except Exception as e:
            self.logger.error("Error in scenario_fail_step_def_error-->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in scenario_fail_step_def_error-->" + str(e))

    def set_scenario_feature_details(self, feature, scenario):
        """
        Description:
            |  This method is used to set the scenario and feature details

        :return: None
        """
        pytest.globalDict["scenario_name"] = scenario.name
        pytest.globalDict["scenario_tags"] = scenario.tags
        pytest.globalDict["feature_name"] = feature.name
        pytest.globalDict["feature_tags"] = feature.tags
        pytest.globalDict["feature_description"] = feature.description

    def fetch_execution_Id_details(self):
        """
        Description:
            |  This method is used to set the execution Id in os environment variable

        :return: string
        """
        try:
            if "execution_id" in os.environ:
                return os.environ["execution_id"]
        except Exception as e:
            self.logger.error("Error occured in fetch_execution_Id_details->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error occured in fetch_execution_Id_details->" + str(e))

    def create_exception_log_file_s3(self, pstr_execution_id):
        """
        Description:
                |  This method creates a an empty file on ftp and returns complete path of the created file

        :param pstr_execution_id: This parameter takes execution id
        :type pstr_execution_id: String
        :param pbyte_buffer: This content of FTP file
        :type pbyte_buffer: Byte

        :return: String
        """
        try:
            str_exception_value = (
                self.set_endtime()
                .replace("-", "")
                .replace(" ", "")
                .replace("+", "")
                .replace(":", "")
                .replace(".", "")
            )
            dict1 = self.python_client_reporting_utils.read_content_from_s3_for_execution_Id(
                pstr_execution_id
            )
            str_exception_log_file_name = str_exception_value + ".json"
            if str_exception_log_file_name in dict1:
                self.cafe_logger.info(
                    f"The file {str_exception_log_file_name} already exists in S3"
                )
                str_exception_value = (
                    self.set_endtime()
                    .replace("-", "")
                    .replace(" ", "")
                    .replace("+", "")
                    .replace(":", "")
                    .replace(".", "")
                )
                str_exception_log_file_name = str_exception_value + ".json"

            str_final_path = (
                self.str_virtual_directory_path
                + self.str_bucket_directory
                + pstr_execution_id
                + "%2F"
                + str_exception_log_file_name
            )
            self.cafe_logger.info(f"Created exception log file {str_final_path} on S3")
            return str_final_path
        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error(f"Error while creating exception log file on Kibana-->{str(e)}")
            self.cafe_logger.exception(
                f"Error while creating exception log file on Kibana-->{str(e)}"
            )

    def export_exception_log_file_s3(self, pstr_ftp_filepath, pstr_local_filepath_to_export):
        try:

            self.python_client_reporting_utils.upload_file_based_on_path(
                pstr_local_filepath_to_export, pstr_ftp_filepath
            )

        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error(
                f"Error while uploading exception log file {pstr_local_filepath_to_export} on Kibana-->{str(e)}"
            )
            self.cafe_logger.exception(
                f"Error while uploading exception log file {pstr_local_filepath_to_export} on Kibana-->{str(e)}"
            )

    def pytest_session_start_auto_dash_configuration(self, session):
        """
        Description:
            |  this method is to session_start_auto_dash_configuration

        """
        try:
            env_config_util = ConfigUtils(os.getcwd())
            if self.is_report:
                if not os.path.exists(self.automation_log_path):
                    os.mkdir(self.automation_log_path)
                self.logger = self.get_logger_for_this_file()
                if os.environ.get("PYTEST_XDIST_WORKER", "master") == "master":

                    if os.path.isfile(
                        self.automation_log_path + os.sep + "Scenario_report_Execution.json"
                    ):
                        os.remove(
                            self.automation_log_path + os.sep + "Scenario_report_Execution.json"
                        )
                    if os.path.isfile(
                        self.automation_log_path + os.sep + "Scenario_report_Execution.json.lock"
                    ):
                        os.remove(
                            self.automation_log_path
                            + os.sep
                            + "Scenario_report_Execution.json.lock"
                        )
                    if os.path.isfile(
                        self.automation_log_path + os.sep + "Scenario_report_Fail.json"
                    ):
                        os.remove(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + "Scenario_report_Fail.json")
                    if os.path.isfile(
                        self.automation_log_path + os.sep + "Scenario_report_Fail.json.lock"
                    ):
                        os.remove(
                            self.automation_log_path + os.sep + "Scenario_report_Fail.json.lock"
                        )

                    if not "--lf" in sys.argv:
                        self.abort_last_terminated_execution()
                        self.delete_file_lock_files()
                        self.delete_execution_files()
                        self.create_empty_json(
                            self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_temp_execution_filename
                        )
                        self.create_empty_json(
                            self.automation_log_path
                            + os.sep
                            + pstr_temp_feature_details_pass_fail_count_filename
                        )
                        self.create_empty_json(
                            self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_temp_feature_ids_filename
                        )
                        self.create_empty_json(
                            self.automation_log_path
                            + os.sep
                            + pstr_temp_feature_data_to_push_filename
                        )
                        self.create_empty_json(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_temp_misc)
                        self.create_empty_json(
                            self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_temp_release_tag_file
                        )
                        self.create_empty_json(
                            self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_team_release_tag_names_file
                        )
                        self.create_empty_json(
                            self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_temp_functional_tag_file
                        )
                        self.create_empty_json(
                            self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_temp_team_tag_file
                        )
                        self.create_empty_json(
                            self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_temp_platform_tag_file
                        )
                        self.create_empty_json(
                            self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_temp_products
                        )
                        self.create_empty_json(
                            self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_temp_failed_scenario_ids
                        )
                        self.create_empty_json(
                            self.automation_log_path
                            + os.sep
                            + pstr_temp_skip_feature_names_with_reason
                        )
                        self.add_key_value_in_json(
                            "ExecutionComplete", False, pstr_temp_execution_filename
                        )
                        self.logger.info("Collecting the look up info")
                        self.collect_lookup_info()
                        self.logger.info("Collected lookup info")
                        execution_details = {
                            "executionStatus": "L",
                            "executionStartTime": None,
                            "executionDuration": 0,
                            "runCommand": None,
                            "executionTags": None,
                            "isBdd": 1,
                            "frameworkId": None,
                            "browser": self.config_utils.fetch_current_browser(),
                            "isCTBuild": 1,
                            "isReRun": 0,
                            "isPerformanceExecution": 0,
                        }
                        ctDetails = {}
                        exec_start_time = self.get_current_date_time()
                        if "rerun_failures" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
                            is_rerun = self.config_utils.base_config["rerun_failures"]
                            if is_rerun:
                                execution_details["isReRun"] = 1
                        os.environ["isCTBuild"] = "0"
                        if session.config.option.jenkins_build:
                            os.environ["isCTBuild"] = "1"
                            execution_details["isCTBuild"] = 2
                            ctDetails["triggeredBy"] = session.config.option.triggeredby
                            ctDetails["jenkinsSlaveName"] = session.config.option.jenkinsslavename
                            ctDetails["repoName"] = session.config.option.reponame
                            ctDetails["branchName"] = session.config.option.branchname
                            if (
                                session.config.option.devbuildnumber == "null"
                                or session.config.option.devbuildnumber == ""
                            ):
                                ctDetails["devBuildNumber"] = None
                            else:
                                ctDetails["devBuildNumber"] = session.config.option.devbuildnumber
                            ctDetails["jobBuildId"] = session.config.option.jenkins_build
                            ctDetails["executionStartTime"] = exec_start_time
                        cafe_version = importlib.metadata.version("cafe")
                        try:
                            python_client_version = importlib.metadata.version("python_client")
                        except Exception as e:
                            raise Exception(
                                "Python Client is not installed in the system. Please install the correct python client version. The error that occured while fetching python client version is "
                                + str(e)
                            )
                        execution_details["frameworkId"] = "4.0.0"
                        execution_details["clientVersion"] = python_client_version
                        execution_details["ctDetails"] = ctDetails
                        execution_details["isDebugExecution"] = self.get_execution_mode()
                        execution_details["executionStartTime"] = exec_start_time
                        self.add_key_value_in_json(
                            "executionStartTime", exec_start_time, pstr_temp_execution_filename
                        )
                        str_exec_env = (
                            str(env_config_util.base_config["execution_environment"])
                            .strip()
                            .lower()
                        )
                        os.environ["execution_environment"] = str_exec_env
                        execution_details["executionEnvironment"] = (
                            self.python_client_reporting_utils.get_execution_environment_code(
                                str_exec_env
                            )
                        )
                        if not execution_details["executionEnvironment"]:
                            pytest.globalDict["acceptable_environment_lookup"] = (
                                self.get_value_from_json(
                                    "acceptable_environment_lookup", pstr_temp_misc
                                )
                            )
                            pytest.globalDict["acceptable_environment_values"] = pytest.globalDict[
                                "acceptable_environment_lookup"
                            ].keys()

                            self.cafe_logger.info(
                                "\n"
                                + "Your Execution Environment: ' "
                                + str_exec_env
                                + "' is not in list of acceptable environment. List of acceptable environments are "
                                + str(pytest.globalDict["acceptable_environment_values"])
                                + "\n"
                                + "Report will be generated but execution wont be considered for metrics charts in Executive Analsis Tab of QA Automation Dashboard"
                                + "\n"
                            )

                        if "use_grid" in env_config_util.base_config.keys():
                            execution_details["isGrid"] = int(
                                env_config_util.base_config["use_grid"]
                            )
                        else:
                            execution_details["isGrid"] = 0

                        execution_details["environment"] = (
                            env_config_util.base_config["environment"]
                            if "environment" in env_config_util.base_config.keys()
                            else None
                        )
                        execution_details["machineName"] = platform.uname()[1]
                        try:
                            if "userdomain" in os.environ:
                                str_username = os.environ["userdomain"] + os.sep + os.getlogin()
                            else:
                                str_username = os.getlogin()
                        except:
                            str_username = "NA"
                        execution_details["user"] = str_username
                        str_environment_type = env_config_util.base_config["environment_type"]
                        os.environ["environment_type"] = str_environment_type
                        lst_arguments = sys.argv
                        bool_parallel = self.get_int_value(
                            self.is_parallel_execution(lst_arguments)
                        )
                        execution_details["isParallel"] = bool_parallel
                        run_commands = lst_arguments
                        str_set_args = set(lst_arguments)
                        for str_argument in str_set_args:
                            str_argument = str(str_argument)
                            if "pytest" in str_argument or "py.test" in str_argument:
                                run_commands.remove(str_argument)
                            elif "features" in str_argument and "tests" in str_argument:
                                last_forward_slash = str(str_argument).rfind("/")
                                last_backward_slash = str(str_argument).rfind("\\")
                                str_arg = str(str_argument)[
                                    max(last_forward_slash, last_backward_slash) + 1 :
                                ]
                                run_commands.remove(str_argument)
                                run_commands.append(str_arg)
                            elif "python" in str_argument:
                                run_commands.remove(str_argument)
                        execution_details["runCommand"] = run_commands
                        try:
                            for a in lst_arguments:
                                if "-m=" in a:
                                    execution_details["executionTags"] = a.replace("-m=", "")
                                if "-m" == a:
                                    int_index = lst_arguments.index(a)
                                    execution_details["executionTags"] = lst_arguments[
                                        int_index + 1
                                    ]
                                if "-k=" in a:
                                    execution_details["executionTags"] = a.replace("-k=", "")
                                if "-k" == a:
                                    int_index = lst_arguments.index(a)
                                    execution_details["executionTags"] = lst_arguments[
                                        int_index + 1
                                    ]
                        except Exception as ex:
                            self.logger.error("Error setting the execution tag " + str(ex))
                            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error setting the execution tag " + str(ex))

                        dashboard_ui_url = (
                            "https://dashboards-mi-qa.midevcld.spglobal.com/automation/execution/"
                        )
                        if (
                            "dashboard_ui_url" in env_config_util.base_config.keys()
                            and env_config_util.base_config["dashboard_ui_url"] is not None
                        ):
                            dashboard_ui_url = env_config_util.base_config["dashboard_ui_url"]

                        self.logger.info("Going to push Execution Data " + str(execution_details))
                        self.push_execution_data(execution_details, dashboard_ui_url)
                        self.logger.info("Pushed Execution Data Complete " + str(execution_details))
                        self.save_execution_details(execution_details)
                    else:
                        self.logger.info("--------------------Rerun Logs--------------------")

        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error(
                "Error occured in pytest_session_start_auto_dash_configuration --> " + str(e)
            )
            self.cafe_logger.exception(
                "Error occured in pytest_session_start_auto_dash_configuration --> " + str(e)
            )
            pytest.exit(
                "Execution ID could not be generated. Either your python client version is not in line with cafe version or VPN is not connected or Reporting Services are down. \n Try one more time. If issue persists. Try executing with reporting flag to false. \n Error -> "
                + str(e)
            )

    def get_frameworkId(self, pstr_version):
        try:
            pytest.globalDict["framework_lookup"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                "framework_lookup", pstr_temp_misc
            )
            for eachdict in pytest.globalDict["framework_lookup"]:
                if (
                    eachdict["frameworkName"] == "CAFE"
                    and eachdict["frameworkLanguage"] == "Python"
                    and str(eachdict["frameworkVersion"]).lower() == str(pstr_version).lower()
                ):
                    return int(eachdict["frameworkId"])
        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error in get_frameworkId-->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in get_frameworkId-->" + str(e))

    def before_scenario_auto_dash_configuration(
        self, request, pobj_feature, pobj_scenario, pobj_globaldict
    ):
        try:
            globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "scenario_data_modify"] = {}
            globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "scenario_failure_reason"] = ""

            if "api" in pobj_scenario.tags:
                globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "bool_api_scenarios"] = "True"

            if self.is_report:
                globals()[
                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_start_time"
                ] = self.get_current_date_time()
                globals()[
                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_feature_name"
                ] = pobj_feature.name
                globals()[
                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_name"
                ] = pobj_scenario.name

                globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "Fail_Scenario_at_the_end"] = "No"
                globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "performance_test"] = "No"
                globals()[
                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "pstr_expectedvalue"
                ] = "One of the insert step has failed"
                globals()[
                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "pstr_actualvalue"
                ] = "Check Dashboard Report for more details"
                globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_failed"] = "No"
                globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_ic"] = "No"
                globals()[
                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "performance_stats_filename"
                ] = "not available"
                self.logger.info(
                    "Inside Before Scenario Auto Dash - Scenario Name-> " + pobj_scenario.name
                )
                lst_scenario_tags = pobj_scenario.tags
                globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "scenario_tags"] = str(
                    lst_scenario_tags
                )
                feature_file, feature_file_plus_feature_name = self.get_feature_file_and_its_name(
                    pobj_feature
                )
                self.collect_feature_details(
                    pobj_feature, feature_file, feature_file_plus_feature_name
                )
                if not globals().get(
                    "featureId_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name, None
                ) and not globals().get("skip_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name, None):
                    str_skip_reason = self.get_value_from_json(
                        "skip_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name,
                        pstr_temp_skip_feature_names_with_reason,
                    )
                    globals()["skip_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name] = str_skip_reason
                    if str_skip_reason:
                        self.skip_test_bcz_feature_invalid(feature_file, str_skip_reason)
                elif globals().get("skip_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name, None):
                    self.skip_test_bcz_feature_invalid(
                        feature_file, globals().get("skip_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name, None)
                    )

                if "--lf" in sys.argv or os.environ["execution_id"]:
                    if self.check_key_exists_in_json(
                        "skip_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name,
                        pstr_temp_skip_feature_names_with_reason,
                    ):
                        str_skipped_reason = self.get_value_from_json(
                            "skip_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name,
                            pstr_temp_skip_feature_names_with_reason,
                        )
                        globals()["skip_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name] = str_skipped_reason
                        self.skip_test_bcz_feature_invalid(feature_file, str_skipped_reason)
                    elif self.check_key_exists_in_json(
                        "featureId_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name,
                        pstr_temp_feature_ids_filename,
                    ):
                        globals()["featureId_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name] = (
                            self.get_value_from_json(
                                "featureId_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name,
                                pstr_temp_feature_ids_filename,
                            )
                        )
                    else:
                        self.logger.info("Feature Id does not exist going to generate feature id")
                        self.collect_feature_details(
                            pobj_feature, feature_file, feature_file_plus_feature_name
                        )

                    int_iteration = 1
                    while not globals().get(
                        "featureId_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name, None
                    ) and not globals().get("skip_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name, None):
                        if int_iteration < 100:
                            int_iteration = int_iteration + 1
                            asyncio.run(self.wait_async(5))
                            if self.check_key_exists_in_json(
                                "skip_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name,
                                pstr_temp_skip_feature_names_with_reason,
                            ):
                                str_skipped_reason = self.get_value_from_json(
                                    "skip_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name,
                                    pstr_temp_skip_feature_names_with_reason,
                                )
                                globals()[
                                    "skip_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name
                                ] = str_skipped_reason
                                self.skip_test_bcz_feature_invalid(feature_file, str_skipped_reason)
                            elif self.check_key_exists_in_json(
                                "featureId_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name,
                                pstr_temp_feature_ids_filename,
                            ):
                                globals()["featureId_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name] = (
                                    self.get_value_from_json(
                                        "featureId_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name,
                                        pstr_temp_feature_ids_filename,
                                    )
                                )

                            self.logger.warning(
                                "WAITING FOR FEATURE ID GENERATION. Feature Name :"
                                + feature_file_plus_feature_name
                            )
                        else:
                            self.logger.error(
                                "FEATURE ID NOT GENERATED. For Feature Name: "
                                + feature_file_plus_feature_name
                                + str(
                                    globals().get(
                                        "featureId_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name, None
                                    )
                                )
                                + " -- "
                                + str(os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST"))
                            )
                            self.cafe_logger.exception(
                                "FEATURE ID NOT GENERATED. For Feature Name: "
                                + feature_file_plus_feature_name
                                + str(
                                    globals().get(
                                        "featureId_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name, None
                                    )
                                )
                                + " -- "
                                + str(os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST"))
                            )
                            self.logger.info(
                                "Skipping scenario due to feature Id not Generated in time -Scenario Name: "
                                + pobj_scenario.name
                                + "  Feature File:"
                                + feature_file
                            )
                            pytest.skip(
                                "---Skipping the scenario due to feature Id not available-------"
                            )
                            break

                    if globals().get("skip_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name, None):
                        self.skip_test_bcz_feature_invalid(
                            feature_file,
                            globals().get("skip_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name, None),
                        )
                    self.logger.info(
                        "Feature Id exists. Proceeding with Scenario Push data. Feature Name "
                        + feature_file_plus_feature_name
                    )
                    scenario_details = {
                        "scenarioName": None,
                        "featureName": None,
                        "priorityTag": None,
                        "isOutline": 0,
                        "example": None,
                        "testingTypeTag": None,
                        "optionalTag": None,
                        "automationStatusTag": None,
                        "scenarioStatus": "IC",
                        "evidence": {},
                        "isDataDriven": 0,
                        "testDataType": None,
                    }
                    scenario_details["scenarioName"] = pobj_scenario.name
                    scenario_details["scenarioStartTime"] = (
                        globals().get(
                            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_start_time"
                        )
                        if globals().get(
                            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_start_time"
                        )
                        else self.get_current_date_time()
                    )
                    scenario_details["featureName"] = feature_file_plus_feature_name

                    scenario_details, example = self.get_data_set_info(
                        request, pobj_scenario, scenario_details, pobj_globaldict
                    )
                    globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_dataset"] = example
                    str_scenario_name_with_example = self.get_string_without_special_chars(
                        pobj_scenario.name + example
                    )
                    globals()[
                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "str_scenario_name_with_example"
                    ] = str_scenario_name_with_example
                    globals()[
                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "feature_file_plus_feature_name"
                    ] = feature_file_plus_feature_name
                    scenario_details["featureId"] = None
                    int_sc_iteration = 10
                    while scenario_details["featureId"] == "" or not scenario_details["featureId"]:
                        while True:
                            try:
                                asyncio.run(self.wait_async(1))
                                int_sc_iteration = int_sc_iteration - 1
                                if not globals().get(
                                    "featureId_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name, None
                                ):
                                    scenario_details["featureId"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                                        "featureId_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name,
                                        pstr_temp_feature_ids_filename,
                                    )
                                    globals()["featureId_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name] = (
                                        scenario_details["featureId"]
                                    )
                                else:
                                    scenario_details["featureId"] = globals().get(
                                        "featureId_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name, None
                                    )
                            except:
                                if int_sc_iteration < 0:
                                    break
                                continue
                            else:
                                self.logger.info(
                                    "Verifying Feature id value "
                                    + str(scenario_details["featureId"])
                                )
                                if int_sc_iteration < 0:
                                    break
                                if not scenario_details["featureId"]:
                                    continue
                                else:
                                    break

                        if (
                            scenario_details["featureId"] == ""
                            or not scenario_details["featureId"]
                            or int_sc_iteration < 0
                        ):
                            self.skip_if_value_is_none(
                                scenario_details["featureId"],
                                "Error reading featureId from json file for feature : "
                                + feature_file_plus_feature_name,
                            )
                            break

                    self.logger.info(
                        "Feature ID which will be used to push scenario is "
                        + str(scenario_details["featureId"])
                    )

                    p = t = a = s = None
                    remaining_tags = []
                    globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_feature_id"] = (
                        scenario_details["featureId"]
                    )
                    if len(pobj_scenario.tags) > 0:
                        p, t, a, s, remaining_tags = (
                            self.get_priority_testingtype_automation_status_scenario_category_codes(
                                pobj_scenario.tags
                            )
                        )
                    scenario_details["priorityTag"] = p
                    scenario_details["testingTypeTag"] = t
                    scenario_details["automationStatusTag"] = a
                    scenario_details["scenarioCategoryTag"] = s
                    if len(remaining_tags) > 0:
                        if len(s) > 0:
                            scenario_details["optionalTag"] = (
                                f"{self.get_optional_tags(remaining_tags)},{','.join(s)}"
                            )
                        else:
                            scenario_details["optionalTag"] = self.get_optional_tags(remaining_tags)
                    else:
                        scenario_details["optionalTag"] = ",".join(s)
                    str_skip_reason = self.do_we_need_to_skip_test_based_on_scenario_tags(p, t, a)
                    str_skip_reason_scenario_tags = ""
                    if not s:
                        str_skip_reason_scenario_tags = (
                            "\n"
                            + " \n"
                            + "The Scenario Category Tag is mandatory. However is missing from scenario"
                        )
                    if any("load" == tag.strip() for tag in pobj_scenario.tags):
                        str_skip_reason = ""
                        lst = ["api", "db", "mobile_app", "ui_thick_client", "ui_web"]
                        check = any(item in lst for item in pobj_scenario.tags)
                        if not check:
                            globals()[
                                os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "performance_test"
                            ] = "Yes"
                            if not self.check_key_exists_in_json(
                                "Performance", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                            ):
                                dict = {}
                                dict["isPerformanceExecution"] = 1
                                dict["executionStatus"] = "L"
                                dict["scenariosCount"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                                    "scenariosCount", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                                )
                                ed = globals().get("execution_details", {})
                                ed["isPerformanceExecution"] = 1
                                globals()["execution_details"] = ed
                                self.update_execution_data(dict)
                                self.add_key_value_in_json(
                                    "Performance", "", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                                )
                        else:
                            str_skip_reason = (
                                "Other testing type tags ('api', 'db', 'mobile_app, 'mobile_web', 'ui_thick_client', 'ui_web') found along with @load tag which is performance testing type tag. "
                                " Use only @load tag if its a performance test. "
                                "Otherwise, remove @load tag if its a automation test script."
                            )
                    if str_skip_reason:
                        str_skip_reason_scenario_tags = (
                            str_skip_reason + str_skip_reason_scenario_tags
                        )
                        scenario_details["evidence"]["exceptionEvidence"] = (
                            "Skipped  Reason : " + str_skip_reason_scenario_tags
                        )
                        scenario_details["evidence"]["errorType"] = CafeConstants.ERROR_CODE_TWO
                        print(str_skip_reason_scenario_tags)
                    elif not str_skip_reason and str_skip_reason_scenario_tags:
                        scenario_details["evidence"]["exceptionEvidence"] = (
                            "Warning! : " + str_skip_reason_scenario_tags
                        )
                        scenario_details["evidence"]["errorType"] = CafeConstants.ERROR_CODE_TWO
                        print(str_skip_reason_scenario_tags)

                    if not "--lf" in sys.argv:
                        self.logger.info("Push scenario data started with " + str(scenario_details))
                        self.push_scenario_data(scenario_details)
                        self.logger.info(
                            "Push scenario data completed with " + str(scenario_details)
                        )
                        self.save_scenario_details(scenario_details)
                        if str_skip_reason:
                            self.logger.info("Skipping Scenario due to " + str_skip_reason)
                            pytest.skip("Skipping Scenario due to " + str_skip_reason)
                    else:
                        self.logger.info("trying to push rerun scenario data")
                        config_util = ConfigUtils()
                        scenario_details["reRunIteration"] = config_util.base_config[
                            "rerun_iteration"
                        ]
                        globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id"] = (
                            self.get_value_from_json(
                                "failed_scenario_id_" + str_scenario_name_with_example,
                                pstr_temp_failed_scenario_ids,
                            )
                        )
                        self.logger.info(
                            "Failed scenario Id read from file is "
                            + str(
                                globals().get(
                                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id"
                                )
                            )
                        )
                        self.logger.info(
                            "Rerun update scenario data started" + str(scenario_details)
                        )
                        self.update_scenario_data(scenario_details)
                        self.logger.info("Rerun updated scenario data completed")

        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error in before_scenario_auto_dash_configuration-->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception(
                "Error in before_scenario_auto_dash_configuration-->" + str(e)
            )

    def skip_test_bcz_feature_invalid(self, feature_file, pstr_skip_reason):
        try:
            if pstr_skip_reason:
                self.logger.info(
                    "Skipping Scenarios from feature file: "
                    + feature_file
                    + "  as  "
                    + str(pstr_skip_reason)
                )
                pytest.skip(
                    "Skipping Scenarios from feature file: "
                    + feature_file
                    + "  as  "
                    + str(pstr_skip_reason)
                )
        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.cafe_logger.exception(
                "Skipping Scenarios from feature file: "
                + feature_file
                + "  as  "
                + str(pstr_skip_reason)
                + str(e)
            )

    def get_priority_testingtype_automation_status_scenario_category_codes(self, plst_tags):
        """
        Description: This method fetches the lookup codes for all priority, testing type and automation status tag.
        :param plst_tags: List of Scenario tags
        :return: Codes
        """

        try:

            priority_tag = None
            testing_type_tag = None
            automation_status_tag = None
            scenario_category_tag = []
            remaining_tags = list(plst_tags)
            for tag in plst_tags:
                strip_tag = tag.strip()
                if strip_tag in pytest.globalDict["priority_lookup"]:
                    priority_tag = pytest.globalDict["priority_lookup"][strip_tag]
                    remaining_tags.remove(tag)
                elif strip_tag in pytest.globalDict["testingtype_lookup"]:
                    testing_type_tag = pytest.globalDict["testingtype_lookup"][strip_tag]
                    remaining_tags.remove(tag)
                elif strip_tag in pytest.globalDict["automationstatus_lookup"]:
                    automation_status_tag = pytest.globalDict["automationstatus_lookup"][strip_tag]
                    remaining_tags.remove(tag)
                elif strip_tag in pytest.globalDict["scenariocategory_lookup"]:
                    scenario_category_tag.append(
                        pytest.globalDict["scenariocategory_lookup"][strip_tag]
                    )
                    remaining_tags.remove(tag)
            return (
                priority_tag,
                testing_type_tag,
                automation_status_tag,
                scenario_category_tag,
                remaining_tags,
            )
        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error in get_priority_testingtype_automation-->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in get_priority_testingtype_automation-->" + str(e))

    def get_test_data_type_value(self, pstr_name):
        try:
            if pstr_name in pytest.globalDict["testdatatype_lookup"]:
                return pytest.globalDict["testdatatype_lookup"][pstr_name]
        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error in get_test_data_type_value-->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in get_test_data_type_value-->" + str(e))

    def before_step_auto_dash_configuration(self, pobj_step):
        """
        Description:
            |  This method is to fetch headers of scenario out line step

        :param pobj_globaldict: pobj_globaldict is the pytest global dict object
        :type pobj_globaldict: dict
        :param pobj_scenario: pobj_scenario is the scenario object
        :type pobj_scenario: object
        :param pobj_step: pobj_step is the step object
        :type pobj_step: object
        """
        try:
            if self.is_report:
                str_step_name = pobj_step.name
                if len(str_step_name) > 1990:
                    str_step_name = pobj_step.name[0:1990]
                globals()[
                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_name"
                ] = str_step_name
                globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "failed_assert"] = "0"
                if "--lf" in sys.argv or os.environ["execution_id"]:
                    if os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id" in globals():
                        dict_example_set = {}
                        if os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "example_set" in globals():
                            dict_example_set = self.create_dict_from_comma_separated_string(
                                globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "example_set"]
                            )
                        step_details = {}
                        str_step_name = str(pobj_step).replace('"', "")
                        if "<" and ">" in str_step_name:
                            for k, v in dict_example_set.items():
                                if "<" + k.strip() + ">" in str_step_name:
                                    str_step_name = str_step_name.replace(
                                        "<" + k.strip() + ">", "<" + v.strip() + ">"
                                    )
                        if len(str_step_name) > 1990:
                            str_step_name = str_step_name[0:1990]
                        step_details["stepName"] = str_step_name
                        step_details["stepStatus"] = "IC"
                        pytest.globalDict["step_name"] = str_step_name
                        step_details["stepStartTime"] = self.get_current_date_time()
                        globals()[
                            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_stepStartTime"
                        ] = str(self.get_current_date_time())
                        step_details["stepType"] = str(pobj_step).strip().upper()[0:1]
                        if step_details["stepType"] not in ("G", "W", "T", "A"):
                            pytest.fail("Step Name does not start with Given, When, Then, And")
                        if "--lf" in sys.argv:
                            step_details["reRunIteration"] = self.config_utils.base_config[
                                "rerun_iteration"
                            ]
                        self.push_step_data(step_details)
                        self.save_step_details(step_details)
        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error in before_step_auto_dash_configuration-->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in before_step_auto_dash_configuration-->" + str(e))

    def after_step_auto_dash_configuration(self, pobj_step):
        """
        Description:
            |  this method is to get step status after a step get executes

        :param pobj_step: pobj_step is the step object which would be passed from the hooks
        :type pobj_step: object
        """
        try:
            if self.is_report:
                if "--lf" in sys.argv or os.environ["execution_id"]:
                    if os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id" in globals():
                        step_details = self.get_dict_obj("current_step_details")
                        step_details["stepStatus"] = self.get_step_status_based_on_asserts(
                            pobj_step
                        )
                        step_details["stepEndTime"] = self.get_current_date_time()
                        step_details["stepDuration"] = self.get_time_difference_seconds(
                            step_details["stepEndTime"],
                            globals()[
                                os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_stepStartTime"
                            ],
                        )
                        scen_tags = self.get_list_obj("scenario_tags")
                        step_details["evidence"] = {}
                        step_id = globals().get(
                            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"
                        )

                        if not int(
                            globals()[
                                os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + step_id + "_isAssertPresent"
                            ]
                        ):
                            step_details["isAssertPresent"] = 0
                            if any(item in self.take_screenshot_tags for item in scen_tags):
                                str_screenshot_path = self.getscreenshot(
                                    self.get_current_date_time(), scen_tags
                                )
                                step_details["evidence"]["screenshotEvidence"] = str_screenshot_path
                        else:
                            step_details["isAssertPresent"] = 1
                        step_details.pop("stepStartTime")
                        self.update_step_data(step_details)
                        globals()[
                            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_details"
                        ] = str(step_details)

        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error in after_step_auto_dash_configuration-->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in after_step_auto_dash_configuration-->" + str(e))
        finally:
            self.pop_value_from_globals(os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id")
            self.pop_value_from_globals(
                os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id" + "_isAssertPresent"
            )

    def get_step_status_based_on_asserts(self, pobj_step):
        """
        Description: This method is to get the step status based on assertions within the step.
        :param pobj_step: This is the pytest step object
        :return: String
        """
        try:
            assert_status = self.python_client_reporting_utils.get_assert_status(
                globals().get(os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id")
            )
            if not (assert_status == "Step Id Not Found"):
                if assert_status == "P":
                    return "P"
                elif assert_status == "F":
                    return "F"
                elif assert_status == "IC":
                    return "IC"
            elif pobj_step.failed:
                return "F"
            else:
                return "P"
        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error occured in get_step_status_based_on_asserts->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception(
                "Error occured in get_step_status_based_on_asserts->" + str(e)
            )

    def pytest_bdd_step_error(self):
        """
        Description: This is the pytest hook which is called after a step fails.
        :return: None
        """
        try:
            if self.is_report:
                if os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id" in globals():
                    step_id = globals().get(
                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"
                    )
                    step_details = self.get_dict_obj("current_step_details")
                    evidence = {}
                    evidence = self.get_evidence_details("step")
                    step_details["evidence"] = evidence
                    step_details["stepStatus"] = "F"
                    globals()[
                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_failed"
                    ] = "Yes"
                    step_details["stepEndTime"] = self.get_current_date_time()
                    step_details["stepDuration"] = self.get_time_difference_seconds(
                        step_details["stepEndTime"],
                        globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_stepStartTime"],
                    )
                    globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_details"] = str(
                        step_details
                    )
                    self.update_step_data(step_details)

        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error in bdd_step_error-->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in bdd_step_error-->" + str(e))

    def pytest_after_scenario_auto_dash_configuration(self, pobj_scenario, pobj_feature):
        """
        Description:
            |  this method is to perform a set of configuration  after a scenario get executes
        :param pobj_scenario: pobj_scenario is the scenario object which would be passed from the hooks
        :type pobj_scenario: object        :
        :param pobj_globaldict: pobj_feature is the pytest feature object
        :type pobj_globaldict: object
        """
        try:
            evidence = {}
            if self.is_report:
                self.logger.info(
                    "Inside after scenario auto dash. Scenario Name: " + pobj_scenario.name
                )
                if "--lf" in sys.argv or os.environ["execution_id"]:
                    self.logger.info("After Scenario Data collection Start")
                    str_scenario_name_with_example = globals().get(
                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "str_scenario_name_with_example"
                    )
                    feature_file, feature_file_plus_feature_name = (
                        self.get_feature_file_and_its_name(pobj_feature)
                    )
                    scenario_details = self.get_dict_obj("current_scenario_details")
                    if "scenarioStartTime" not in scenario_details:
                        scenario_details["scenarioStartTime"] = globals().get(
                            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_start_time"
                        )
                    if not globals().get("featureId_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name, None):
                        scenario_details["featureId"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                            "featureId_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name,
                            pstr_temp_feature_ids_filename,
                        )
                    else:
                        scenario_details["featureId"] = globals().get(
                            "featureId_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name, None
                        )
                    scenario_details["scenarioEndTime"] = self.get_current_date_time()
                    scenario_details["scenarioDuration"] = self.get_time_difference_seconds(
                        scenario_details["scenarioEndTime"], scenario_details["scenarioStartTime"]
                    )
                    step_details = self.get_dict_obj("current_step_details")
                    if step_details != {}:
                        if "stepStatus" not in step_details.keys():
                            step_details["stepStatus"] = "F"
                            scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] = "F"
                            step_details["stepEndTime"] = self.get_current_date_time()
                            step_details["stepDuration"] = self.get_time_difference_seconds(
                                step_details["stepEndTime"],
                                globals()[
                                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_stepStartTime"
                                ],
                            )
                            step_details["evidence"] = {}
                            step_id = globals().get(
                                os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"
                            )
                            evidence = {}
                            evidence = self.get_evidence_details("step")
                            step_details["evidence"] = evidence
                            self.update_step_data(step_details)
                        elif step_details["stepStatus"] == "F":
                            scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] = "F"
                        elif (
                            globals()[
                                os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_failed"
                            ]
                            == "Yes"
                        ):
                            scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] = "F"
                            scenario_details["evidence"] = self.get_evidence_details("scenario")
                        elif step_details["stepStatus"] == "IC":
                            scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] = "IC"
                            if sys.exc_info():
                                if "Failed" in str(sys.exc_info()[0]):
                                    step_details["stepStatus"] = "F"
                                    scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] = "F"
                                    step_details["stepEndTime"] = self.get_current_date_time()
                                    step_details["stepDuration"] = self.get_time_difference_seconds(
                                        step_details["stepEndTime"],
                                        globals()[
                                            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST")
                                            + "current_stepStartTime"
                                        ],
                                    )
                                    step_details["evidence"] = {}
                                    step_id = globals().get(
                                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"
                                    )
                                    evidence = {}
                                    evidence = self.get_evidence_details("step")
                                    step_details["evidence"] = evidence
                                    self.update_step_data(step_details)

                        elif (
                            globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_ic"]
                            == "Yes"
                        ):
                            scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] = "IC"
                        elif step_details["stepStatus"] == "P":
                            scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] = "P"

                    elif (
                        globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_failed"]
                        == "Yes"
                    ):
                        scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] = "F"
                        scenario_details["evidence"] = self.get_evidence_details("scenario")
                    elif (
                        globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_ic"]
                        == "Yes"
                    ):
                        scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] = "IC"
                    else:
                        scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] = "IC"

                    if (
                        globals().get(os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "performance_test")
                        == "Yes"
                    ):
                        filename = globals().get(
                            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "performance_stats_filename"
                        )
                        if os.path.isfile(self.str_project_path + os.sep + filename + ".json"):
                            dict_payload = {
                                "transactionName": "",
                                "_80percentile": "",
                                "_90percentile": "",
                                "averageResponseTime": "",
                                "minimumResponseTime": "",
                                "maxResponseTime": "",
                                "passCount": "",
                                "failCount": "",
                                "failDescription": "",
                                "totalRPS": "",
                                "duration": "",
                                "startTime": "",
                                "endTime": "",
                                "status": "",
                                "requestType": "",
                            }
                            str_upload_path = (
                                self.python_client_reporting_utils.upload_file_based_on_path(
                                    self.str_project_path + os.sep + filename + ".json"
                                )
                            )
                            evidence = {"additionalEvidence": str_upload_path}
                            scenario_details["evidence"] = evidence
                        else:
                            self.logger.error(
                                "Could not find the perf stats file in project dir. File Name "
                                + filename
                            )
                            self.cafe_logger.exception(
                                "Could not find the perf stats file in project dir. File Name "
                                + filename
                            )

                    if "--lf" in sys.argv:
                        scenario_details["reRunIteration"] = self.config_utils.base_config[
                            "rerun_iteration"
                        ]
                    self.logger.info("Going to update Scenario Data")
                    if "api" in pobj_scenario.tags:
                        if len(sys.exc_info()) >= 1:
                            if str(sys.exc_info()[0]).__contains__("Failed"):
                                if not globals()[
                                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST")
                                    + "scenario_failure_reason"
                                ]:
                                    globals()[
                                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST")
                                        + "scenario_failure_reason"
                                    ] = str(sys.exc_info()[1])

                        if (
                            len(
                                globals()[
                                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "scenario_data_modify"
                                ]
                            )
                            != 0
                        ):
                            globals()[
                                os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "scenario_data_modify"
                            ]["Scenario_Status"] = scenario_details["scenarioStatus"]
                            if globals()[
                                os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "scenario_failure_reason"
                            ]:
                                globals()[
                                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "scenario_data_modify"
                                ]["Scenario_Failure_Reason"] = globals().get(
                                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST")
                                    + "scenario_failure_reason"
                                )

                            # if len(globals()[os.environ.get('PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST') + "scenario_data_modify"]) != 0:
                            #     globals()[os.environ.get('PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST') + "scenario_data_modify"]['Scenario_Status'] = scenario_details['scenarioStatus']
                            #     if os.environ['scenario_failure_reason']:
                            #         globals()[os.environ.get('PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST') + "scenario_data_modify"]['Scenario_Failure_Reason'] = os.environ[
                            #             'scenario_failure_reason']

                            bool_artifacts = self.config_utils.is_api_artifacts()
                            if bool_artifacts:
                                self.scenario_add_key_value_in_json(
                                    globals()[
                                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST")
                                        + "scenario_data_modify"
                                    ],
                                    "Scenario_report_Execution.json",
                                )
                                if scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] == "F":
                                    self.scenario_add_key_value_in_json(
                                        globals()[
                                            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST")
                                            + "scenario_data_modify"
                                        ],
                                        "Scenario_report_Fail.json",
                                    )

                            scenario_details["evidence"] = evidence
                    self.update_scenario_data(scenario_details)
                    self.logger.info("Updated Scenario Data")
                    str_key_passed = feature_file_plus_feature_name + "_TotalPassed"
                    str_key_failed = feature_file_plus_feature_name + "_TotalFailed"
                    str_key_inconclusive = feature_file_plus_feature_name + "_TotalInconclusive"
                    while True:
                        try:
                            int_write_iteration = 10
                            lock = threading.Semaphore()
                            lock.acquire()
                            if pobj_scenario.failed:
                                if not "--lf" in sys.argv:
                                    self.increment_value_for_key(
                                        str_key_failed,
                                        pstr_temp_feature_details_pass_fail_count_filename,
                                    )
                                    self.increment_value_for_key(
                                        "Execution_TotalFail", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                                    )
                            elif scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] == "F":
                                if not "--lf" in sys.argv:
                                    self.increment_value_for_key(
                                        str_key_failed,
                                        pstr_temp_feature_details_pass_fail_count_filename,
                                    )
                                    self.increment_value_for_key(
                                        "Execution_TotalFail", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                                    )
                            elif scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] == "IC":
                                if not "--lf" in sys.argv:
                                    self.increment_value_for_key(
                                        str_key_inconclusive,
                                        pstr_temp_feature_details_pass_fail_count_filename,
                                    )
                                    self.increment_value_for_key(
                                        "Execution_TotalInconclusive", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                                    )
                            else:
                                self.increment_value_for_key(
                                    str_key_passed,
                                    pstr_temp_feature_details_pass_fail_count_filename,
                                )

                                if "--lf" in sys.argv:
                                    self.logger.info(
                                        "Decrementing the failed count for feature : "
                                        + pstr_temp_feature_details_pass_fail_count_filename
                                    )
                                    self.decrement_value_for_key(
                                        str_key_failed,
                                        pstr_temp_feature_details_pass_fail_count_filename,
                                    )

                                    while True:
                                        int_decrement_iteration = 4
                                        try:
                                            self.decrement_value_for_key(
                                                "Execution_TotalFail", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                                            )
                                        except:
                                            int_decrement_iteration = int_decrement_iteration - 1
                                            if int_decrement_iteration < 0:
                                                break
                                            continue
                                        else:
                                            break
                                    while True:
                                        int_increment_iteration = 4
                                        try:
                                            self.increment_value_for_key(
                                                "Execution_TotalPass", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                                            )
                                        except:
                                            int_increment_iteration = int_increment_iteration - 1
                                            if int_increment_iteration < 0:
                                                break
                                            continue
                                        else:
                                            break
                                else:
                                    self.increment_value_for_key(
                                        "Execution_TotalPass", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                                    )
                        except:
                            int_write_iteration = int_write_iteration - 1
                            lock.release()
                            if int_write_iteration < 0:
                                break
                            continue
                        else:
                            lock.release()
                            break

                    if scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] == "F":
                        if "rerun_failures" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
                            is_rerun = self.config_utils.base_config["rerun_failures"]
                            if is_rerun:
                                self.add_key_value_in_json(
                                    "failed_scenario_id_" + str_scenario_name_with_example,
                                    globals().get(
                                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST")
                                        + "current_scenario_id"
                                    ),
                                    pstr_temp_failed_scenario_ids,
                                )

                    self.logger.info("Going to update Feature Data")
                    self.update_the_feature(feature_file_plus_feature_name)
                    self.logger.info("Updated Feature Data")

                    if (
                        globals()[
                            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "Fail_Scenario_at_the_end"
                        ]
                        == "Yes"
                    ):
                        self.kibana_insert_step_failure(
                            globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "pstr_expectedvalue"],
                            globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "pstr_actualvalue"],
                            "Fail",
                        )

        except Exception as e:
            exc_type, exc_obj, exc_tb = sys.exc_info()
            self.logger.error(
                "Error in after_scenario_auto_dash_configuration-->"
                + str(e)
                + " Line Number: "
                + str(exc_tb.tb_lineno)
            )
            self.cafe_logger.exception(
                "Error in after_scenario_auto_dash_configuration-->"
                + str(e)
                + " Line Number: "
                + str(exc_tb.tb_lineno)
            )
            self.print_exception_information()
        finally:
            self.pop_scenario_end_values()

    def pop_scenario_end_values(self):
        try:
            str_test_name = os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST")
            self.pop_value_from_globals(str_test_name + "bool_api_scenarios")
            self.pop_value_from_globals(str_test_name + "current_scenario_id")
            self.pop_value_from_globals(str_test_name + "scenario_failure_reason")
            self.pop_value_from_globals(str_test_name + "failed_assert")
            self.pop_value_from_globals(str_test_name + "current_scenario_failed")
            self.pop_value_from_globals(str_test_name + "current_scenario_start_time")
            self.pop_value_from_globals(str_test_name + "str_scenario_name_with_example")
            self.pop_value_from_globals(str_test_name + "current_scenario_ic")
            self.pop_value_from_globals(str_test_name + "performance_stats_filename")
            self.pop_value_from_globals(str_test_name + "scenario_data_modify")
            self.pop_value_from_globals(str_test_name + "Fail_Scenario_at_the_end")
            self.pop_value_from_globals(str_test_name + "pstr_expectedvalue")
            self.pop_value_from_globals(str_test_name + "pstr_actualvalue")
        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error in pop_scenario_end_values-->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in pop_scenario_end_values-->" + str(e))

    def update_the_feature(self, feature_file_plus_feature_name):
        try:
            self.logger.info(
                "Inside update the feature. Feature name -" + feature_file_plus_feature_name
            )
            str_key_inconclusive = feature_file_plus_feature_name + "_TotalInconclusive"
            if not globals().get("startTime_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name):
                globals()["startTime_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name] = os.environ.get(
                    "executionStartTime"
                )
                feature_details = {
                    "executionStartTime": globals().get(
                        "startTime_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name
                    )
                }
            else:
                feature_details = {"executionStartTime": os.environ.get("executionStartTime")}
            if feature_details:
                feature_details["executionId"] = os.environ["execution_id"]
                feature_details["executionEndTime"] = self.get_current_date_time()
                int_scn_pass, int_scn_fail = self.get_pass_fail_count_for_a_feature(
                    feature_file_plus_feature_name
                )
                feature_details["featureDuration"] = self.get_time_difference_seconds(
                    feature_details["executionEndTime"], feature_details["executionStartTime"]
                )
                self.logger.info(
                    "Pass/Fail count is "
                    + feature_file_plus_feature_name
                    + "----"
                    + str(int_scn_pass)
                    + ","
                    + str(int_scn_fail)
                )
                feature_details["totalPassed"] = int_scn_pass
                feature_details["totalFailed"] = int_scn_fail
                feature_details["totalInconclusive"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                    str_key_inconclusive, pstr_temp_feature_details_pass_fail_count_filename
                )
                feature_details["totalScenarios"] = (
                    int_scn_pass
                    + int_scn_fail
                    + self.get_int_value(feature_details["totalInconclusive"])
                )
                if feature_details["totalScenarios"] == 0:
                    feature_details["totalScenarios"] = None
                feature_details["featureStatus"] = "IC"
                if int_scn_fail > 0:
                    feature_details["featureStatus"] = "F"
                elif feature_details["totalInconclusive"]:
                    feature_details["featureStatus"] = "IC"
                elif int_scn_pass > 0:
