                    feature_details["featureStatus"] = "P"
                self.update_feature_data(feature_details, feature_file_plus_feature_name)
        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error occured while updating feature data -->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error occured while updating feature data -->" + str(e))

    def get_pass_fail_count_for_a_feature(self, pstr_feature_file_plus_feature_name):
        """
        Description: This method returns the passed failed scenarios count based on feature name
        :param pobj_feature: This is the pytest feature object
        :return: total_passed, total_failed
        """
        try:
            self.logger.info("Getting pass/fail count for " + pstr_feature_file_plus_feature_name)
            int_iteration = 3
            while True:
                try:
                    passed = self.get_value_from_json(
                        pstr_feature_file_plus_feature_name + "_TotalPassed",
                        pstr_temp_feature_details_pass_fail_count_filename,
                    )
                    failed = self.get_value_from_json(
                        pstr_feature_file_plus_feature_name + "_TotalFailed",
                        pstr_temp_feature_details_pass_fail_count_filename,
                    )
                except:
                    int_iteration = int_iteration - 1
                    if int_iteration < -1:
                        break
                    continue

                else:
                    break
            self.logger.info("Got pass fail count -- >" + str(passed) + " / " + str(failed))
            if passed:
                total_passed = int(passed)
            else:
                total_passed = 0
            if failed:
                total_failed = int(failed)
            else:
                total_failed = 0
            return total_passed, total_failed

        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error in get_pass_fail_count_for_a_feature-->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in get_pass_fail_count_for_a_feature-->" + str(e))

    def set_collected_count(self, session):
        """
        Description: This method sets the execution total scenarios count. i.e how many scenarios are collected for execution.
        :param session: this is pytest session object
        :return: None
        """
        try:
            if self.is_report:
                if not "--lf" in sys.argv:
                    if (os.environ.get("PYTEST_XDIST_WORKER", "master") == "master") or (
                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_XDIST_WORKER", "master") == "gw0"
                    ):
                        self.logger.info(
                            "Checking Node value "
                            + str(os.environ.get("PYTEST_XDIST_WORKER", "master"))
                        )
                        if os.environ.get("execution_id"):
                            self.logger.info("Updating the Scenarios Count")
                            execution_details = {}
                            execution_details["scenariosCount"] = len(session.items)
                            self.logger.info(
                                "Collected Scenarios count is " + str(len(session.items))
                            )
                            execution_details["executionStatus"] = "L"
                            if len(session.items) > 0:
                                self.add_key_value_in_json(
                                    "scenariosCount",
                                    len(session.items),
                                    pstr_temp_execution_filename,
                                )
                                self.update_execution_data(execution_details)
                                execution_details["isPerformanceExecution"] = 0
                                self.logger.info("Updated the Scenarios Count")
        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error in set_collected_count-->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in set_collected_count-->" + str(e))

    def session_finish_auto_dash_configuration(self, session):
        """
        Description: This method is to update the execution details of a particular execution.
        :param session: This is the pytest session object
        :return:None
        """
        try:
            pbool_execution_complete = False
            if self.is_report:
                if os.environ.get("PYTEST_XDIST_WORKER", "master") == "master":
                    if os.environ.get("execution_id"):
                        self.logger.info("Inside session finish auto dash")
                        if not "--lf" in sys.argv:
                            ctDetails = {}
                            end_time = self.get_current_date_time()
                            try:
                                if (
                                    int(os.environ["isCTBuild"])
                                    and os.environ["ctBuildId"] != "null"
                                    and os.environ["ctBuildId"] != None
                                    and os.environ["ctBuildId"]
                                ):
                                    ctDetails["executionEndTime"] = end_time
                                    self.python_client_reporting_utils.update_ct_details(
                                        ctDetails, os.environ["ctBuildId"]
                                    )
                            except Exception as e1:
                                self.logger.warning(
                                    "CT details could not be updated. Error -> " + str(e1)
                                )
                            reporter = session.config.pluginmanager.get_plugin("terminalreporter")
                            execution_details = globals().get("execution_details", {})
                            execution_details["executionEndTime"] = end_time
                            execution_details["executionDuration"] = (
                                self.get_time_difference_seconds(
                                    execution_details["executionEndTime"],
                                    execution_details["executionStartTime"],
                                )
                            )

                            execution_details["totalInconclusive"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                                "Execution_TotalInconclusive", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                            )

                            execution_details["totalSkipped"] = 0
                            execution_details["skippedTests"] = []
                            execution_details["scenariosCount"] = session.testscollected
                            if execution_details["scenariosCount"] == 0:
                                execution_details["scenariosCount"] = None
                            self.add_key_value_in_json(
                                "scenariosCount",
                                execution_details["scenariosCount"],
                                pstr_temp_execution_filename,
                            )
                            execution_details["totalPass"] = 0
                            if session.testscollected == 0 or session.exitstatus in range(2, 6):
                                execution_details["executionStatus"] = "A"
                            if "passed" in reporter.stats:
                                execution_details["totalPass"] = len(reporter.stats["passed"])
                            if "skipped" in reporter.stats:
                                execution_details["totalSkipped"] = len(reporter.stats["skipped"])
                                self.add_key_value_in_json(
                                    "totalSkipped",
                                    execution_details["totalSkipped"],
                                    pstr_temp_execution_filename,
                                )
                                for eachlist in reporter.stats["skipped"]:
                                    execution_details["skippedTests"].append(
                                        eachlist.fspath.replace("features/tests/", "").replace(
                                            "features\\tests", ""
                                        )
                                        + " ->  Module Name : "
                                        + eachlist.head_line.replace("'", "")
                                    )

                            if execution_details["totalInconclusive"]:
                                execution_details["totalPass"] = self.get_int_value(
                                    execution_details["totalPass"]
                                ) - self.get_int_value(execution_details["totalInconclusive"])
                            if "failed" in reporter.stats:
                                execution_details["totalFail"] = len(reporter.stats["failed"])
                            else:
                                execution_details["totalFail"] = 0
                            if "rerun_failures" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
                                config_utils = self.config_utils.base_config
                                need_to_rerun = config_utils["rerun_failures"]
                                if need_to_rerun and execution_details["totalFail"] > 0:
                                    self.logger.info(
                                        "Keeping the status of execution Live as we need to rerun few cases"
                                    )
                                    execution_details["executionStatus"] = "L"
                                else:
                                    execution_details["executionStatus"] = "C"
                                    os.environ["execution_complete"] = "Yes"
                                    pbool_execution_complete = True
                            else:
                                execution_details["executionStatus"] = "C"
                                pbool_execution_complete = True
                                os.environ["execution_complete"] = "Yes"

                            self.logger.info(
                                "Going to update execution Data " + str(execution_details)
                            )
                            execution_details.pop("executionStartTime")
                            execution_details.pop("ctDetails")
                            self.update_execution_data(execution_details)
                            self.add_key_value_in_json(
                                "Execution_TotalPass",
                                execution_details["totalPass"],
                                pstr_temp_execution_filename,
                            )
                            self.add_key_value_in_json(
                                "Execution_TotalFail",
                                execution_details["totalFail"],
                                pstr_temp_execution_filename,
                            )
                            self.delete_file_lock_files()
                            need_to_rerun = False
                            if "rerun_failures" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
                                config_utils = self.config_utils.base_config
                                need_to_rerun = config_utils["rerun_failures"]
                                if not need_to_rerun or execution_details["totalFail"] == 0:
                                    self.remove_temp_json_files()

                            else:
                                self.remove_temp_json_files()

                        else:
                            self.logger.info("Inside session finish for rerun")
                            self.logger.info("Checking if all reruns are done")
                            pbool_execution_complete = False

                            ed = {}
                            ed["totalPass"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                                "Execution_TotalPass", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                            )
                            ed["totalFail"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                                "Execution_TotalFail", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                            )
                            ed["scenariosCount"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                                "scenariosCount", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                            )
                            if ed["scenariosCount"] == 0:
                                ed["scenariosCount"] = None
                            ed["executionStatus"] = "L"
                            ed["totalSkipped"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                                "totalSkipped", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                            )
                            ed["totalInconclusive"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                                "Execution_TotalInconclusive", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                            )
                            ed["executionEndTime"] = self.get_current_date_time()
                            ed["executionDuration"] = self.get_time_difference_seconds(
                                ed["executionEndTime"],
                                self.get_value_from_json(
                                    "executionStartTime", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                                ),
                            )

                            config_utils = ConfigUtils(os.getcwd())
                            int_rerun_count = config_utils.base_config["rerun_failures_count"]
                            self.logger.info("Got rerun count " + str(int_rerun_count))
                            int_rerun_iteration = config_utils.base_config["rerun_iteration"]
                            self.logger.info("Got rerun iteration " + str(int_rerun_iteration))
                            pbool_failure_still_exists = self.check_failure_tests_exists()
                            self.logger.info(
                                "Got pbool_failure_still_exists " + str(pbool_failure_still_exists)
                            )
                            if (
                                int_rerun_count == int_rerun_iteration
                            ) or not pbool_failure_still_exists:
                                self.logger.info("Rerun completed. So deleting files")
                                ed["executionStatus"] = "C"
                                os.environ["execution_complete"] = "Yes"
                                pbool_execution_complete = True
                                self.remove_temp_json_files()
                            self.logger.info("Going to update rerun execution data")
                            self.update_execution_data(ed)

        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error in session_finish_auto_dash_configuration-->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception(
                "Error in session_finish_auto_dash_configuration-->" + str(e)
            )
        finally:
            if pbool_execution_complete:
                self.upload_execution_log_file()
                self.python_client_reporting_utils.terminate_token()

    def update_execution_data(self, pdict_data):
        """
        Description: This method is to call the api to update the execution data after execution is completed
        :param pdict_data: This is the payload containing details to be pushed
        :return: None
        """
        try:
            self.logger.info("Inside update execution Data " + str(pdict_data))
            if os.environ.get("execution_id"):
                self.python_client_reporting_utils.update_execution_details(
                    pdict_data, os.environ["execution_id"]
                )
            if pdict_data["executionStatus"] == "C":
                self.add_key_value_in_json("ExecutionComplete", True, pstr_temp_execution_filename)

        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Execution data was " + str(pdict_data))
            self.logger.error("Error in update_execution_details-->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Execution data was " + str(pdict_data))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in update_execution_details-->" + str(e))

    def insert_step(
        self,
        pstr_expectedvalue="NA",
        pstr_actualvalue="NA",
        pstr_status="IC",
        pstr_exception_log=None,
        pdict_perfstats="NA",
        pobj_api_response=None,
        pstr_scenario_level_log=False,
        plist_result_dataframes=None,
        pbool_takescreenshot=True,
        pstr_trim_exception_detail=None,
        pstr_exception_detail=None,
        **kwargs,
    ):
        """
        Description: This method is to insert custom assertion/step into the reporting.
        :param pstr_expectedvalue: It is the expected value for an insertion assert
        :param pstr_actualvalue: It is the Actual value for an insertion assert
        :param pstr_status:  It is the status for an insertion assert
        :param pobj_api_response: This is the api response object. In case user needs to push it to reporting
        :param plist_result_dataframes: This is the db result object/dataframe. In case user needs to push it to reporting
        :return: None
        """

        try:
            pbool_execute_next_step_after_failure = kwargs.get(
                "pbool_execute_next_step_after_failure", False
            )
            str_grid_evidence = kwargs.get("str_grid_evidence", None)
            if str(pstr_status).strip().lower() not in ("fail", "pass"):
                pstr_status = "IC"
            pytest.globalDict["expected_scenariovalue"] = pstr_expectedvalue
            pytest.globalDict["actual_scenariovalue"] = pstr_actualvalue
            pytest.globalDict["step_status"] = pstr_status
            operation_id = None
            if self.is_report:
                pbool_stepid_exist = False
                self.logger = self.get_logger_for_this_file()
                if len(str(pstr_actualvalue)) > 1000:
                    pstr_actualvalue = str(pstr_actualvalue)[0:990]
                if len(str(pstr_expectedvalue)) > 1000:
                    pstr_expectedvalue = str(pstr_expectedvalue)[0:990]
                if os.environ.get("execution_id"):
                    if pdict_perfstats != "NA":
                        self.push_performance_stats(pdict_perfstats)
                    if globals().get(os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id"):
                        if os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id" in globals():
                            pbool_stepid_exist = True
                            step_id = globals().get(
                                os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"
                            )
                            scen_tags = self.get_list_obj("scenario_tags")
                            str_evidence_path = None
                            str_additional_evidence = None
                            self.logger.info("Insert Step Data for " + str(pstr_actualvalue))
                            if any(item in self.take_screenshot_tags for item in scen_tags):
                                if pstr_status.lower() == "fail":
                                    operation_id = self.captureOperationID()
                                    if operation_id:
                                        operation_id = (
                                            "**************************************************************************************************"
                                            + "\n"
                                            + "Operation ID: "
                                            + str(operation_id)
                                            + "\n"
                                            + "**************************************************************************************************"
                                        )
                                if pbool_takescreenshot:
                                    try:
                                        str_evidence_path = self.getscreenshot(
                                            self.get_current_date_time(), scen_tags
                                        )
                                    except Exception as e1:
                                        str_evidence_path = None
                                        self.logger.info(
                                            "Attaching screenshot error - > " + str(e1)
                                        )
                                        if pstr_exception_detail:
                                            pstr_exception_detail = (
                                                str(pstr_exception_detail)
                                                + "\n"
                                                + "----ALSO NOTE ----"
                                                + "\n"
                                                + str(e1)
                                            )
                                        else:
                                            pstr_exception_detail = (
                                                "\n" + "----ALSO NOTE ----" + "\n" + str(e1)
                                            )
                            elif ("api" in scen_tags) and pobj_api_response != None:
                                try:
                                    str_evidence_path = self.attach_api_request_response(
                                        pobj_api_response
                                    )
                                except Exception as e2:
                                    str_evidence_path = None
                                    self.logger.info("Attaching API response error - > " + str(e2))
                                    if pstr_exception_detail:
                                        pstr_exception_detail = (
                                            str(pstr_exception_detail)
                                            + "\n"
                                            + "----ALSO NOTE ----"
                                            + "\n"
                                            + str(e2)
                                        )
                                    else:
                                        pstr_exception_detail = (
                                            "\n" + "----ALSO NOTE ----" + "\n" + str(e2)
                                        )
                            elif ("db" in scen_tags) and plist_result_dataframes != None:
                                str_source_label = kwargs.get(
                                    "pstr_source_label", "Source_To_Target"
                                )
                                str_target_label = kwargs.get(
                                    "pstr_target_label", "Target_To_Source"
                                )
                                str_common_label = kwargs.get("pstr_common_label", "Common")
                                try:
                                    str_additional_evidence = self.__upload_dataframe_s3(
                                        plist_result_dataframes,
                                        pstr_source_label=str_source_label,
                                        pstr_target_label=str_target_label,
                                        pstr_common_label=str_common_label,
                                    )
                                except Exception as e3:
                                    self.logger.info(
                                        "Attaching dataframe evidence error - > " + str(e3)
                                    )
                                    str_additional_evidence = None
                                    if pstr_exception_detail:
                                        pstr_exception_detail = (
                                            str(pstr_exception_detail)
                                            + "\n"
                                            + "----ALSO NOTE ----"
                                            + "\n"
                                            + str(e3)
                                        )
                                    else:
                                        pstr_exception_detail = (
                                            "\n" + "----ALSO NOTE ----" + "\n" + str(e3)
                                        )
                            str_exception_path = None

                            str_inconclusive_test = "This is Inconclusive because either user has passed IC as the status of this insert step or has not passed status parameter while calling this insert_step method or status other than (pass /fail) was passed. So default status is IC"
                            if pstr_status == "IC":
                                if pstr_trim_exception_detail:
                                    pstr_trim_exception_detail = (
                                        str(pstr_trim_exception_detail)
                                        + "\n"
                                        + "----ALSO NOTE ----"
                                        + "\n"
                                        + str_inconclusive_test
                                    )
                                else:
                                    pstr_trim_exception_detail = str_inconclusive_test
                            if pstr_trim_exception_detail:
                                if len(pstr_trim_exception_detail) > 3990:
                                    pstr_trim_exception_detail = pstr_trim_exception_detail[0:3990]
                                if (
                                    pstr_trim_exception_detail != "Exception Occured"
                                    and not globals()[
                                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST")
                                        + "scenario_failure_reason"
                                    ]
                                ):
                                    globals()[
                                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST")
                                        + "scenario_failure_reason"
                                    ] = pstr_trim_exception_detail

                            if not pstr_exception_detail and operation_id:
                                pstr_exception_detail = operation_id
                            if pstr_exception_detail:
                                if operation_id and pstr_exception_detail != operation_id:
                                    pstr_exception_detail = pstr_exception_detail + operation_id
                                try:
                                    if pstr_status == "IC":
                                        pstr_exception_detail = (
                                            str(pstr_exception_detail)
                                            + "\n\n\n"
                                            + "----ALSO NOTE ----"
                                            + "\n"
                                            + str_inconclusive_test
                                        )

                                    if not globals()[
                                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST")
                                        + "scenario_failure_reason"
                                    ]:
                                        globals()[
                                            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST")
                                            + "scenario_failure_reason"
                                        ] = pstr_exception_detail

                                    str_exception_path = (
                                        self.upload_exception_for_step_error_or_exception(
                                            pstr_exception_detail
                                        )
                                    )

                                    globals()[
                                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "failed_assert"
                                    ] = "1"
                                except Exception as e4:
                                    self.logger.info(
                                        "Error in upload_exception_for_step_error_or_exception error - > "
                                        + str(e4)
                                    )
                            if not str_additional_evidence:
                                str_additional_evidence = str_grid_evidence
                            str_error_code = kwargs.get("pstr_error", CafeConstants.ERROR_CODE_ZERO)

                            self.python_client_reporting_utils.insert_assertion_data(
                                pstr_expectedvalue,
                                pstr_actualvalue,
                                pstr_status,
                                pstr_evidence_path=str_evidence_path,
                                pstr_exception_path=str_exception_path,
                                pstr_trim_exception=pstr_trim_exception_detail,
                                pstr_additional_evidence=str_additional_evidence,
                                pstr_error=str_error_code,
                                pstr_step_id=step_id,
                            )
                            globals()[
                                os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + step_id + "_isAssertPresent"
                            ] = "1"
                            self.logger.info(
                                "Insert Step Data Complete for " + str(pstr_actualvalue)
                            )

        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            step_id = globals().get(os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id", "")
            if self.is_report:
                self.logger.error(
                    f"Insert step error. Expected was {str(pstr_expectedvalue)} , actual was {str(pstr_actualvalue)}, str_evidence_path : {str(str_evidence_path)}, additional evidence: {str(str_additional_evidence)}, trim exception :{str(pstr_trim_exception_detail)} , StepId: {str(step_id)}"
                )
                self.cafe_logger.exception(
                    f"Insert step error. Expected was {str(pstr_expectedvalue)} , actual was {str(pstr_actualvalue)}, str_evidence_path : {str(str_evidence_path)}, additional evidence: {str(str_additional_evidence)}, trim exception :{str(pstr_trim_exception_detail)} , StepId: {str(step_id)}"
                )
            self.logger.error(
                "Error occcured in insert_step -->" + f" Step id : {step_id} . Error is " + str(e)
            )
            self.cafe_logger.exception(
                "Error occcured in insert_step -->" + f" Step id : {step_id} . Error is " + str(e)
            )
        finally:
            if self.is_report:
                if pstr_status.lower() == "fail":
                    globals()[
                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_failed"
                    ] = "Yes"
                    if pbool_stepid_exist:
                        self.set_step_failure()
                    if not pbool_execute_next_step_after_failure and pbool_stepid_exist:
                        self.kibana_insert_step_failure(
                            pstr_expectedvalue, pstr_actualvalue, pstr_status
                        )
                    else:
                        globals()[
                            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "Fail_Scenario_at_the_end"
                        ] = "Yes"
                        globals()[
                            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "pstr_expectedvalue"
                        ] = pstr_expectedvalue
                        globals()[
                            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "pstr_actualvalue"
                        ] = pstr_actualvalue
                if pstr_status.lower() == "ic":
                    globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_ic"] = "Yes"

    def kibana_insert_step_failure(self, pstr_expectedvalue, pstr_actualvalue, pstr_status):
        try:
            pytest.fail(
                "Expected: "
                + str(pstr_expectedvalue)
                + ",  Actual: "
                + str(pstr_actualvalue)
                + " , Status : "
                + str(pstr_status)
            )
        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in kibana_insert_step_failure. Error ->" + str(e))

    def set_step_failure(self):
        try:
            if os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id" in globals():
                step_id = globals().get(os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id")
                step_details = self.get_dict_obj("current_step_details")
                evidence = {}
                evidence = self.get_evidence_details("step")
                step_details["evidence"] = evidence
                step_details["stepStatus"] = "F"
                globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_failed"] = "Yes"
                step_details["stepEndTime"] = self.get_current_date_time()
                step_details["stepDuration"] = self.get_time_difference_seconds(
                    step_details["stepEndTime"],
                    globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_stepStartTime"],
                )
                globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_details"] = str(
                    step_details
                )
                self.update_step_data(step_details)
        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error in set_step_failure --> " + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in set_step_failure --> " + str(e))

    def get_list_obj(self, pstr_name):
        """
        Description: This is to convert the string object to list stored in globals variables
        :param pstr_name: This is the name of the variable with which the value is stored in globals variables.
        :return: list
        """
        try:
            str_name = pstr_name
            lst_object = ""
            if os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + str_name in globals():
                lst_object = globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + str_name]
            items = list()
            if lst_object != "":
                lst_object.replace("'", '"')
                lst_object = eval(lst_object)
                return list(lst_object)
            else:
                return items
        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error in get_list_obj-->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in get_list_obj-->" + str(e))

    def push_scenario_data(self, pdict_data):
        """
        Description: This method is used to push scenario data to Reporting
        :param pdict_data: This is the payload i.e the details to be pushed to reporting
        :return: None
        """
        try:
            globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id"] = (
                self.python_client_reporting_utils.push_scenario_details(pdict_data)
            )
            if (
                globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id"] is not None
                and globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id"]
                != "None"
                and globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id"] != ""
            ):
                self.logger.info(
                    "New Scenario ID Generated -> "
                    + str(globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id"])
                )
            else:
                self.logger.error(
                    "Scenario Id not generated . Scenario Data tried to push was -> "
                    + str(pdict_data)
                )
                self.cafe_logger.exception(
                    "Scenario Id not generated . Scenario Data tried to push was -> "
                    + str(pdict_data)
                )

        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Scenario Data is -> " + str(pdict_data))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Scenario Data is -> " + str(pdict_data))
            self.logger.error("Error in push_scenario_data-->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in push_scenario_data-->" + str(e))

    def update_scenario_data(self, pdict_data):
        """
        Description: This method is used to update scenario data to Reporting
        :param pdict_data: This is the payload i.e the scenario details to be updated to reporting
        :return: None
        """
        try:
            int_iteration = 0
            while True:
                int_iteration += 1
                if globals().get(os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id"):
                    self.logger.info("Going to update scenario data with data " + str(pdict_data))
                    self.python_client_reporting_utils.update_scenario_details(
                        pdict_data,
                        globals().get(
                            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id"
                        ),
                    )
                    self.logger.info(
                        "Scenario ID Updated -> "
                        + str(
                            globals().get(
                                os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id"
                            )
                        )
                    )
                    break
                elif int_iteration > 5:
                    self.logger.info(
                        "Scenario ID could not be Updated -> as current_scenario_id is:  "
                        + str(
                            globals().get(
                                os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id"
                            )
                        )
                    )
                    break

        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Scenario Data was -> " + str(pdict_data))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Scenario Data was -> " + str(pdict_data))
            self.logger.error("Error in update_scenario_data-->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in update_scenario_data-->" + str(e))

    def push_step_data(self, pdict_data):
        """
        Description: This method is used to push step data to Reporting
        :param pdict_data: This is the payload i.e the step details to be pushed to reporting
        :return: None
        """
        try:
            if os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id" in globals():
                pdict_data["scenarioId"] = globals()[
                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id"
                ]
                self.logger.info("Pushing step data is " + str(pdict_data))
                globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"] = (
                    self.python_client_reporting_utils.push_step_details(pdict_data)
                )
                if (
                    globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"] is not None
                    and globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"]
                    != "None"
                    and globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"] != ""
                ):
                    step_id = globals().get(
                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"
                    )
                    globals()[
                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + step_id + "_isAssertPresent"
                    ] = "0"
                    self.logger.info(
                        "New Step ID Generated -> "
                        + str(globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"])
                    )
                else:
                    self.logger.error(
                        "Step ID was not generated while pushing the data-> "
                        + str(globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"])
                    )
                    self.cafe_logger.exception(
                        "Step ID was not generated while pushing the data-> "
                        + str(globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"])
                    )
                    self.logger.error("Step Data tried to push was -> " + str(pdict_data))
                    self.cafe_logger.exception("Step Data tried to push was -> " + str(pdict_data))

        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Step data was " + str(pdict_data))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Step data was " + str(pdict_data))
            self.logger.error("Error in push_step_data-->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in push_step_data-->" + str(e))

    def update_step_data(self, pdict_data):
        """
        Description: This method is used to update step data to Reporting
        :param pdict_data: This is the payload i.e the step details to be updated to reporting
        :return: None
        """

        try:
            self.logger.info("Updating step data is " + str(pdict_data))
            if os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id" in globals():
                self.python_client_reporting_utils.update_step_details(
                    pdict_data, globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"]
                )

            else:
                self.logger.error("Skipping Update step Data as Scenario Id is None")
                self.cafe_logger.exception("Skipping Update step Data as Scenario Id is None")

        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Step data was " + str(pdict_data))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Step data was " + str(pdict_data))
            self.logger.error("Error in update_step_data-->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in update_step_data-->" + str(e))

    def update_feature_data(self, pdict_data, pstr_feature_file_name):
        """
        Description: This method is used to update feaure data to Reporting
        :param pdict_data: This is the payload i.e the feature details to be updated to reporting
        :return: None
        """
        try:
            self.logger.info(
                "Updating the feature data for -" + pstr_feature_file_name + " : " + str(pdict_data)
            )
            if os.environ.get("execution_id"):
                if not globals().get("featureId_" + pstr_feature_file_name, None):
                    featureid = self.get_value_from_json(
                        "featureId_" + pstr_feature_file_name, pstr_temp_feature_ids_filename
                    )
                else:
                    featureid = globals().get("featureId_" + pstr_feature_file_name, None)

                int_iteration = 5
                while int_iteration > 0:
                    int_iteration = int_iteration - 1
                    if not featureid:
                        self.logger.warning(
                            "Feature could not be read from Execution.json file. Trying again for feature name->"
                            + pstr_feature_file_name
                            + " featureid value -> "
                            + str(featureid)
                        )
                        int_iteration_count = 5
                        while True:
                            try:
                                if not globals().get("featureId_" + pstr_feature_file_name, None):
                                    featureid = self.get_value_from_json(
                                        "featureId_" + pstr_feature_file_name,
                                        pstr_temp_feature_ids_filename,
                                    )
                                else:
                                    featureid = globals().get(
                                        "featureId_" + pstr_feature_file_name, None
                                    )
                            except:
                                int_iteration_count = int_iteration_count - 1
                                if int_iteration_count < 0:
                                    break
                                continue
                            else:
                                break
                    else:
                        break
                if featureid is not None and featureid != "None" and featureid != "":
                    globals()["featureId_" + pstr_feature_file_name] = featureid
                    self.logger.info(
                        "Updating the feature data with feature Id "
                        + str(featureid)
                        + " and the data is "
                        + str(pdict_data)
                    )
                    self.python_client_reporting_utils.update_feature_details(pdict_data, featureid)
                    self.logger.info("Feature ID Updated ->" + str(featureid))
                else:
                    self.logger.error(
                        "Not Updating the feature data with feature Id "
                        + str(featureid)
                        + "Feature File Name: "
                        + pstr_feature_file_name
                    )
                    self.cafe_logger.exception(
                        "Not Updating the feature data with feature Id "
                        + str(featureid)
                        + "Feature File Name: "
                        + pstr_feature_file_name
                    )

            else:
                self.logger.warning(
                    "Feature data was not udpated as there is no Execution Id in environ variables"
                )

        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Feature data was " + str(pdict_data))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Feature data was " + str(pdict_data))
            self.logger.error("Error in update_feature_data-->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in update_feature_data-->" + str(e))

    def push_execution_data(self, pdict_data, str_dashboard_ui_url):
        """
        Description: This method is used to push execution data to Reporting
        :param pdict_data: This is the payload i.e the execution details to be pushed to reporting
        :return: None
        """
        try:
            os.environ["execution_id"], os.environ["ctBuildId"] = (
                self.python_client_reporting_utils.push_execution_details(pdict_data)
            )
            if not os.environ["execution_id"]:
                pytest.exit(
