    def delete_file_lock_files(self):
        """
        Description: This method deletes all the lock files created during locking a Execution.json file
        :return: None
        """
        try:
            pattern = str(os.environ.get("computername")) + "*"
            pstr_path = self.automation_log_path
            files = os.listdir(pstr_path)
            for name in files:
                bln_found = fnmatch.fnmatch(name, pattern)
                if bln_found:
                    os.remove(pstr_path + os.sep + name)
        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error occured in delete_file_lock_files-> " + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error occured in delete_file_lock_files-> " + str(e))

    def delete_execution_files(self):
        """
        Description: This method deletes the Execution.json and resets the content of log file
        :return: None
        """
        try:

            pstr_path = self.automation_log_path
            files = os.listdir(pstr_path)
            for name in files:
                if name.startswith("Temp_") or name == "Execution.json":
                    os.remove(pstr_path + os.sep + name)
            with open(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_log_file_name, "w") as somefile:
                somefile.write("")
                somefile.close()

        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error occured in delete_execution_files-> " + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error occured in delete_execution_files-> " + str(e))

    def get_platform_team_tag(self, pstr_feature_tags):
        """
        Description: This method will collect the platform,functionality,team IDs from feature tags
        :return: PlatformId,FunctionalityId,TeamId
        """
        try:
            self.logger.info("Inside get platform and team tag " + str(pstr_feature_tags))
            platform_id = None
            team_id = None
            product_id = None
            remaining_tags = pstr_feature_tags
            if not pytest.globalDict["platformtag_lookup"]:
                self.logger.info("Earlier global data was not set for platformtag_lookup")
                pytest.globalDict["platformtag_lookup"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                    "platformtag_lookup", pstr_temp_platform_tag_file
                )
            if not pytest.globalDict["team_lookup"]:
                self.logger.info("Earlier global data was not set for team_lookup")
                pytest.globalDict["team_lookup"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                    "team_lookup", pstr_temp_team_tag_file
                )
            plst_feature_tags = list(pstr_feature_tags)
            for tag in plst_feature_tags:
                strip_tag = tag.strip()
                if any(
                    d["platformTagName"] == strip_tag
                    for d in pytest.globalDict["platformtag_lookup"]
                ):
                    remaining_tags.remove(tag)
                    lst_platform_ids = [
                        x["platformTagId"]
                        for x in pytest.globalDict["platformtag_lookup"]
                        if any(item == strip_tag for item in x.values())
                    ]
                    lst_product_ids = [
                        x["productId"]
                        for x in pytest.globalDict["platformtag_lookup"]
                        if any(item == strip_tag for item in x.values())
                    ]
                    if len(lst_platform_ids) > 0:
                        if not platform_id:
                            platform_id = str(lst_platform_ids[0])
                        else:
                            platform_id = str(platform_id) + "," + str(lst_platform_ids[0])
                    if len(lst_product_ids) > 0:
                        if not product_id:
                            product_id = str(lst_product_ids[0])
                        else:
                            product_id = str(product_id) + "," + str(lst_product_ids[0])

                elif any(
                    d.strip().lower() == strip_tag.lower()
                    for d in pytest.globalDict["team_lookup"].keys()
                ):
                    if team_id:
                        for item in pytest.globalDict["team_lookup"].keys():
                            if item.strip().lower() == strip_tag.lower():
                                id = pytest.globalDict["team_lookup"][item]
                                team_id = str(team_id) + "," + str(id)
                    else:
                        for item in pytest.globalDict["team_lookup"].keys():
                            if item.strip().lower() == strip_tag.lower():
                                team_id = pytest.globalDict["team_lookup"][item]

            if "," in str(platform_id):
                platform_id = None

            if "," in str(team_id):
                team_id = None

            if "," in str(product_id):
                product_id = None

            return platform_id, team_id, product_id, remaining_tags

        except Exception as e:
            self.logger.error("Error in get_platform_functionality_team_tag-->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in get_platform_functionality_team_tag-->" + str(e))
            return platform_id, team_id, product_id, remaining_tags
        self.print_exception_information()

    def get_functionality_tag(self, pstr_feature_tags, product_id, remaining_tags):

        try:
            functionality_tag_id = None
            if not product_id:
                return functionality_tag_id, remaining_tags
            if not pytest.globalDict["functionality_lookup"]:
                self.logger.info("Earlier global data was not set for functionality_lookup")
                pytest.globalDict["functionality_lookup"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                    "functionality_lookup", pstr_temp_functional_tag_file
                )

            plst_feature_tags = list(pstr_feature_tags)
            for tag in plst_feature_tags:
                strip_tag = tag.strip()
                if any(
                    str(d["functionalityGroupName"]).strip().lower() == strip_tag.lower()
                    for d in pytest.globalDict["functionality_lookup"]
                ):
                    remaining_tags.remove(tag)
                    lst_functionality_tag_ids = [
                        x["functionalityGroupId"]
                        for x in pytest.globalDict["functionality_lookup"]
                        if (
                            (str(x["productId"]) == str(product_id))
                            and (
                                (
                                    str(x["functionalityGroupName"]).strip().lower()
                                    == str(strip_tag).lower()
                                )
                            )
                        )
                    ]

                    if len(lst_functionality_tag_ids) > 0:
                        if not functionality_tag_id:
                            functionality_tag_id = str(lst_functionality_tag_ids[0])
                        else:
                            functionality_tag_id = (
                                str(functionality_tag_id) + "," + str(lst_functionality_tag_ids[0])
                            )

            if "," in str(functionality_tag_id):
                functionality_tag_id = None

            return functionality_tag_id, remaining_tags
        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error in get_functionality_tag-->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in get_functionality_tag-->" + str(e))
            return functionality_tag_id, remaining_tags

                )

                )

                pytest.globalDict["platform_lookup"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                    "platform_lookup", pstr_temp_misc
                )

        except Exception as e:

            self.logger.error("Error in set_lookup_content_globally-->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in set_lookup_content_globally-->" + str(e))

    async def wait_async(self, pint_time_seconds):
        try:
            await asyncio.sleep(pint_time_seconds)
        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error occured in wait_async->  " + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error occured in wait_async->  " + str(e))

    def skip_if_value_is_none(self, pstr_value, pstr_error_message):
        try:
            self.logger.info("Checking if value is None")
            if not pstr_value or pstr_value == "null" or pstr_value == "None":
                self.logger.warning(pstr_error_message)
                pytest.skip(pstr_error_message)

        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error in skip_if_value_is_none-->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in skip_if_value_is_none-->" + str(e))

    def get_data_set_info(self, request, pobj_scenario, pdict_scenario_details, pobj_globaldict):
        """
        Description: This is the method used for collecting the data set info
        :param request: pytest request object
        :param pdict_scenario_details: scenario details dictionary
        :param pobj_globaldict: Global Dictionary Object
        :return:
        """
        try:
            str_testdatatype_full_value = None
            headers = []
            pdict_scenario_details["isDataDriven"] = 0
            if "data_driven_keys" in pobj_globaldict.keys():
                headers = pytest.globalDict["data_driven_keys"]
            if len(request.node.funcargs) > 1:
                pdict_scenario_details["isDataDriven"] = 1

            if len(pobj_scenario.examples.examples) > 0:
                pdict_scenario_details["isOutline"] = 1
                pdict_scenario_details["isDataDriven"] = 0
                str_testdatatype_full_value = "Outline"
            else:
                pdict_scenario_details["isOutline"] = 0

            example = ""
            if len(pobj_scenario.examples.examples) > 0 or pdict_scenario_details["isDataDriven"]:
                data_set = copy.copy(request.node.funcargs)
                if "request" in data_set:
                    data_set.pop("request")
                data_set = str(dict(sorted(data_set.items()))).replace("'", "")
                name_request = str(request)
                first_square_bracket = name_request.find("[")
                last_square_bracket = name_request.rfind("]")
                example = name_request[first_square_bracket + 1 : last_square_bracket]
                if not example:
                    pdict_scenario_details["example"] = None
                else:
                    if len(data_set) > 7990:
                        pdict_scenario_details["example"] = str(data_set)[0:7990]
                        first_curly_bracket = data_set.find("{")
                        last_curly_bracket = data_set.rfind("}")
                        data_set = data_set[first_curly_bracket + 1 : last_curly_bracket]
                        globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "example_set"] = data_set
                    else:
                        pdict_scenario_details["example"] = str(data_set)
                        first_curly_bracket = data_set.find("{")
                        last_curly_bracket = data_set.rfind("}")
                        data_set = data_set[first_curly_bracket + 1 : last_curly_bracket]
                        globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "example_set"] = data_set

            if str_testdatatype_full_value:
                pdict_scenario_details["testDataType"] = self.get_test_data_type_value(
                    str_testdatatype_full_value
                )

            return pdict_scenario_details, example

        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error in get_data_set_info -->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in get_data_set_info -->" + str(e))

    def create_dict_from_comma_separated_string(self, pstr_value):
        try:
            mydict = {}
            if isinstance(pstr_value, str):
                if ", " in pstr_value:
                    lst_values = pstr_value.split(", ")
                    for value in lst_values:
                        if ":" in value:
                            new_list = value.split(":")
                            mydict[new_list[0]] = new_list[1]
                elif ":" in pstr_value:
                    new_list = pstr_value.split(":")
                    mydict[new_list[0]] = new_list[1]
            else:
                self.logger.warning(
                    "Only string values are accepted in create_dict_from_comma_separated_string"
                )

            return mydict
        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error in create_dict_from_comma_separated_string -->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception(
                "Error in create_dict_from_comma_separated_string -->" + str(e)
            )

    def check_failure_tests_exists(self):
        """
        Description: Check is failed test cases exist
        :return: Boolean
        """
        try:
            projectpath = self.config_utils.get_project_path()
            with open(projectpath + "/" + ".pytest_cache/v/cache/lastfailed", "r") as f:
                b = f.read()
                f.close()
            d = json.loads(b)
            up_json = {}
            for k, v in d.items():
                if len(k) != 0:
                    up_json[k] = v
            if len(up_json) > 0:
                return True
            else:
                return False
        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error in check_failure_tests_exists -->" + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in check_failure_tests_exists -->" + str(e))
            return False

    def do_we_need_to_skip_test_based_on_feature_tags(
        self,
        pstr_platform_tag,
        pstr_functionality_tag,
        pstr_team_tag,
        feature_file_plus_feature_name,
        feature_file,
        pbool_valid_feature,
    ):
        try:
            skip_reason = ""

            if not pbool_valid_feature:
                skip_reason = (
                    skip_reason
                    + "\n"
                    + " \n"
                    + "Unable to collect feature level tags as there is no space between Feature keyword and Feature Name. Feature File name: "
                    + feature_file
                    + "\n"
                    + "For example: "
                    + "\n\n"
                    + "Feature:feature Name --->incorrect"
                    + "\n"
                    + "Feature: feature Name --->correct"
                    + "\n\n"
                    + " OR "
                    + "\n\n"
                    + "Feature has zero tags. Feature File Name : "
                    + feature_file
                    + "\n\n OR "
                    + "\n\n"
                    + "Feature is not formatted properly due to copy paste from another source. Feature File Name : "
                    + feature_file
                )

                self.add_key_value_in_json(
                    "skip_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name,
                    skip_reason,
                    pstr_temp_skip_feature_names_with_reason,
                )
            else:
                if not pstr_platform_tag:
                    skip_reason = (
                        skip_reason
                        + "\n"
                        + " \n"
                        + "Platform tag not found in feature file or is invalid or multiple platform tags are found."
                        + "\n"
                        + "Feature File Name : "
                        + feature_file
                    )

                if not pstr_functionality_tag:
                    skip_reason = (
                        skip_reason
                        + "\n"
                        + " \n"
                        + "Mapping between platform tag and functionality tag might be wrong. OR  Functional tag is missing/invalid/multiple functionality tags found. "
                        + "\n"
                        + "Feature File Name : "
                        + feature_file
                    )

                if not pstr_team_tag:
                    skip_reason = (
                        skip_reason
                        + "\n"
                        + " \n"
                        + "Team tag not found in feature file or is invalid or multiple team tags found."
                        + "\n"
                        + "Feature File Name : "
                        + feature_file
                    )
                if skip_reason:
                    self.add_key_value_in_json(
                        "skip_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name,
                        skip_reason,
                        pstr_temp_skip_feature_names_with_reason,
                    )
            return skip_reason

        except Exception as e:
            self.logger.error(
                "Error occured in do_we_need_to_skip_test_based_on_feature_tags-> " + str(e)
            )
            self.cafe_logger.exception(
                "Error occured in do_we_need_to_skip_test_based_on_feature_tags-> " + str(e)
            )

    def do_we_need_to_skip_test_based_on_scenario_tags(
        self, pstr_priority_tag, pstr_testingtype_tag, pstr_automation_status_tag
    ):
        try:
            skip_reason = ""
            if not pstr_priority_tag:
                skip_reason = (
                    skip_reason
                    + "\n"
                    + " \n"
                    + "The Priority Tag is mandatory. However is missing from scenario"
                )
            if not pstr_testingtype_tag:
                skip_reason = (
                    skip_reason
                    + "\n"
                    + " \n"
                    + "The Testing Type Tag is mandatory. However is missing from scenario"
                )

            if not pstr_automation_status_tag:
                skip_reason = (
                    skip_reason
                    + "\n"
                    + " \n"
                    + "The Automation Status Tag is mandatory. However is missing from scenario"
                )
            if skip_reason:
                return skip_reason

        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error(
                "Error occured in do_we_need_to_skip_test_based_on_scenario_tags-> " + str(e)
            )
            self.cafe_logger.exception(
                "Error occured in do_we_need_to_skip_test_based_on_scenario_tags-> " + str(e)
            )

    def remove_temp_json_files(self):
        try:

            pattern = "Temp_" + "*"
            pstr_path = self.automation_log_path
            files = os.listdir(pstr_path)
            for name in files:
                bln_found = fnmatch.fnmatch(name, pattern)
                if bln_found:
                    os.remove(pstr_path + os.sep + name)

        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error occured in remove_temp_json_files-> " + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error occured in remove_temp_json_files-> " + str(e))

    def delete_file_name(self, pstr_filename):
        try:
            if os.path.exists(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_filename):
                os.remove(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_filename)
        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error occured in delete_file_name-> " + str(e))

    def pop_value_from_globals(self, pstr_pop_value):
        try:
            if pstr_pop_value in globals():
                globals().pop(pstr_pop_value)
        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error occured in pop_value_from_globals-> " + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error occured in pop_value_from_globals-> " + str(e))

    def get_logger_for_this_file(self):
        """
        Description: This is to get logs for this kibana_reporting.py file
        :return: logging
        """
        try:
            log_level = logging.ERROR
            if "kibana_log_level" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
                str_level = self.config_utils.base_config["kibana_log_level"]
                if str_level.lower() == "error":
                    log_level = logging.ERROR
                elif str_level.lower() == "info":
                    log_level = logging.INFO
                elif str_level.lower() == "debug":
                    log_level = logging.DEBUG
            logger = logging.getLogger("kibana_logger")
            logger.setLevel(log_level)
            hdlr = logging.handlers.RotatingFileHandler(
                self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_log_file_name,
                maxBytes=50000000,
                backupCount=3,
            )
            formatter = logging.Formatter(
                "[%(asctime)s] - %(levelname)s - [%(module)s] %(message)s"
            )
            hdlr.setFormatter(formatter)
            if logger.hasHandlers():
                logger.handlers.clear()
            logger.addHandler(hdlr)
            logger.propagate = False
            return logger

        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            raise Exception("Error occured while setting and getting logging " + str(e))

    def abort_last_terminated_execution(self):
        try:
            if os.path.exists(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_temp_execution_filename):
                str_execution_id = self.get_value_from_json(
                    "executionId", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                )
                data = self.python_client_reporting_utils.get_execution_status_by_execution_id(
                    str_execution_id
                )
                if data:
                    str_status = data.get("executionStatus")
                    if str_status == "L":
                        self.python_client_reporting_utils.generate_token()
                        dict_data = {"executionStatus": "A"}
                        self.python_client_reporting_utils.update_execution_details(
                            dict_data, str_execution_id
                        )
        except Exception as ex:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error updating last terminated execution " + str(ex))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Error updating last terminated execution " + str(ex))

    def get_platform_name_based_on_product_id(self, pstr_product_id):
        try:
            if pstr_product_id:
                str_platform_id = None
                pytest.globalDict["product_lookup"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                    "product_lookup", pstr_temp_products
                )
                if pytest.globalDict["product_lookup"]:
                    str_platform_name = [
                        x["platformName"]
                        for x in pytest.globalDict["product_lookup"]
                        if (str(pstr_product_id) == str(x["productId"]))
                    ]

                    if str_platform_name:
                        if not pytest.globalDict["platform_lookup"]:
                            pytest.globalDict["platform_lookup"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                                "platform_lookup", pstr_temp_misc
                            )
                        str_platform_id = [
                            x["platformId"]
                            for x in pytest.globalDict["platform_lookup"]
                            if (str(str_platform_name[0]) == str(x["platformName"]))
                        ]
                        return str_platform_name[0], str_platform_id[0]
                else:
                    return None, str_platform_id
            else:
                return None, None
        except Exception as ex:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Error in get_platform_name_based_on_product_id. Error -> " + str(ex))
            self.cafe_logger.exception(
                "Error in get_platform_name_based_on_product_id. Error -> " + str(ex)
            )
            return None, None

    def captureOperationID(self):
        try:
            pstr_operationid = pytest.driver.execute_script("return MILoggingStats.id")
            if pstr_operationid:
                return pstr_operationid
        except Exception as e:
            self.cafe_logger.exception("capture id was not captured. Because " + str(e))
            return None

    def push_performance_stats(self, pdict_stats):
        try:
            dict_payload = {
                "executionId": "",
                "featureId": "",
                "scenarioId": "",
                "transactionName": "",
                "_80Percentile": "",
                "_90Percentile": "",
                "averageResponseTime": "",
                "minimumResponseTime": "",
                "maxResponseTime": "",
                "passCount": "",
                "failCount": "",
                "failDescription": "",
                "rpsData": "",
                "duration": "",
                "host": "",
                "users": "",
                "startTime": "",
                "endTime": "",
                "performanceStatus": "",
                "requestType": "",
            }
            dict_payload["executionId"] = os.environ["execution_id"]
            dict_payload["featureId"] = globals().get(
                os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_feature_id"
            )
            dict_payload["scenarioId"] = globals().get(
                os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id"
            )
            dict_payload["transactionName"] = pdict_stats.get("txn_name")
            dict_payload["_80Percentile"] = pdict_stats.get("80_percentile")
            dict_payload["_90Percentile"] = pdict_stats.get("90_percentile")
            dict_payload["averageResponseTime"] = pdict_stats.get("avg_response_time")
            dict_payload["minimumResponseTime"] = pdict_stats.get("min_response_time")
            dict_payload["maximumResponseTime"] = pdict_stats.get("max_response_time")
            dict_payload["passCount"] = pdict_stats.get("num_requests_pass")
            dict_payload["failCount"] = pdict_stats.get("num_requests_fail")
            dict_payload["executionEnvironment"] = os.environ["execution_environment"][0:1].upper()
            try:
                for k, v in pdict_stats.get("failures").items():
                    for item_list in v:
                        for key, val in item_list.items():
                            if key == "error":
                                dict_payload["failDescription"] = val
                                break
            except Exception as e:
                self.cafe_logger.exception("Unable to get the failure error in locust")
            dict_payload["rpsData"] = pdict_stats.get("total_rps")
            dict_payload["duration"] = pdict_stats.get("duration")
            dict_payload["host"] = pdict_stats.get("locust_host")
            dict_payload["users"] = pdict_stats.get("users")
            dict_payload["startTime"] = pdict_stats.get("start_time")
            dict_payload["endTime"] = pdict_stats.get("end_time")
            dict_payload["performanceStatus"] = pdict_stats.get("status")
            dict_payload["requestType"] = pdict_stats.get("request_type")
            dict_payload["sla"] = pdict_stats.get("SLA")
            try:
                self.python_client_reporting_utils.push_locust_details(dict_payload)
            except Exception as e:
                self.print_exception_information()
                self.logger.error("Exception occured in pushing locust details. " + str(e))
                self.cafe_logger.exception("Exception occured in pushing locust details. " + str(e))
        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Exception occured in push_performance_stats " + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Exception occured in push_performance_stats " + str(e))

    def save_execution_details(self, pstr_execution_details):
        try:
            temp = pstr_execution_details
            keys_to_remove = [
                "executionTags",
                "isDebugExecution",
                "isReRun",
                "runCommand",
                "isBdd",
                "frameworkId",
                "browser",
                "isCTBuild",
                "executionEnvironment",
                "isGrid",
                "environment",
                "machineName",
                "user",
                "isParallel",
            ]
            for key in keys_to_remove:
                temp.pop(key)
            globals()["execution_details"] = temp
        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error("Exception occured in save_execution_details " + str(e))
            self.cafe_logger.exception("Exception occured in save_execution_details " + str(e))

    def get_execution_environment_code_based_on_platformname_env_and_type(
        self, pstr_platform_name, pstr_execution_env, pstr_env_type
    ):
        try:
            env_data = self.get_value_from_json("environment_type_lookup", pstr_temp_misc)
            str_code = [
                item["environmentId"]
                for item in env_data
                if (
                    str(pstr_platform_name).strip() == str(item["platformName"].strip())
                    and (
                        str(pstr_execution_env).strip().lower()
                        == str(item["environmentName"]).strip().lower()
                    )
                    and str(pstr_env_type).strip() == str(item["environmentType"]).strip()
                )
            ]

            if str_code:
                return str_code[0]
            else:
                return None

        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.logger.error(
                "Exception occured in get_execution_environment_code_based_on_platformname_env_and_type "
                + str(e)
            )
            self.cafe_logger.exception(
                "Exception occured in get_execution_environment_code_based_on_platformname_env_and_type "
                + str(e)
            )

    def upload_execution_log_file(self):
        try:
            pattern = pstr_log_file_name + "*"
            pstr_path = self.automation_log_path
            files = os.listdir(pstr_path)
            for file_name in files:
                bln_found = fnmatch.fnmatch(file_name, pattern)
                if bln_found:
                    with open(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + file_name, "r") as file:
                        data = file.read()
                    if len(str(data)) > 0:
                        target_path = (
                            self.python_client_reporting_utils.str_bucket_directory
                            + str(self.python_client_reporting_config.reporting_server)[-4:]
                            + "_"
                            + str(os.environ.get("execution_id"))
                            + "/"
                            + file_name.replace(".", "")
                        )
                        self.python_client_reporting_utils.upload_file_based_on_path(
                            self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_log_file_name, target_path
                        )

        except Exception as e:
            self.print_exception_information()
            self.cafe_logger.exception(
                "Exception occured while upload_execution_log_file " + str(e)
            )

    def print_exception_information(self):
        try:
            exc_type, exc_obj, exc_tb = sys.exc_info()
            self.logger.error(str(sys.exc_info()) + "\n Line Number: " + str(exc_tb.tb_lineno))
            self.cafe_logger.exception(
                str(sys.exc_info()) + "\n Line Number: " + str(exc_tb.tb_lineno)
            )
        except Exception as e:
            self.cafe_logger.exception(
                "Exception occured in print_exception_information. " + str(e)
            )

    def __decrypt_password(self, pstr_password, pstr_secret_key):
    """
    Description: This method is to decrypt the encrypted password.
    :param pstr_password: The decrypted password
    :param pstr_secret_key: The secret key with which the password was encrypted
    :return: Password (String)
    """
    try:
        cipher = AES.new(pstr_secret_key.encode("utf8"), AES.MODE_ECB)
        decoded = cipher.decrypt(base64.b64decode(pstr_password))
        password = (decoded.decode()).strip()
        return password.replace("\b", "").strip()
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        raise Exception(e)

    def __generate_autoexpo_filename(self):
    """
    Description:
        |  This method is to generate name of csv file which will be used for s3 export

    """
    try:
        scenarioname = pytest.globalDict["scenario_name"]
        str_randnum = "".join(random.choice("0123456789ABCDEF") for i in range(5))
        filename = str((datetime.datetime.now()).strftime("%Y_%m_%dT%H_%M_%S_%f"))
        file_scenario_name = (
            str(scenarioname).replace(" ", "_")
            + filename
            + str_randnum
            + "_"
            + "result"
            + ".csv"
        )
        return file_scenario_name
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error in __generate_autoexpo_filename" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in __generate_autoexpo_filename" + str(e))

    def __upload_dataframe_s3(self, plist_result_dataframes, **kwargs):
    """
    Description:
        |  This method is to upload dataframe to s3,this method is for internal purpose.

    :param plist_result_dataframes: plist_result_dataframes is the list of data frames
    :type plist_result_dataframes: list
    :param pstr_source_label: this kwarg parametr is the source label for source to target data on csv file
    :type pstr_source_label: String
    :param pstr_target_label: this kwarg parametr is the target label for target to source data on csv file
    :type pstr_target_label: String
    :param pstr_common_label: this kwarg parametr is the common label for common data on csv file
    :type pstr_common_label: String

    """
    try:
        filename = self.__generate_autoexpo_filename()
        outputfile_ = (
            self.config_utils.get_auto_export_dir_path() + os.sep + "AutoExpo_" + filename
        )
        str_source_label = kwargs.get("pstr_source_label")
        str_target_label = kwargs.get("pstr_target_label")
        str_common_label = kwargs.get("pstr_common_label")
        if isinstance(plist_result_dataframes, list):
            mynewlist = [s for s in plist_result_dataframes if isinstance(s, pd.DataFrame)]
            if (
                len(mynewlist) == len(plist_result_dataframes)
                and len(plist_result_dataframes) <= 2
            ):
                frames = mynewlist
                result = pd.concat(
                    frames, keys=[str_source_label, str_target_label, str_common_label]
                )
                print(result)
                result.to_csv(outputfile_)
                pstr_execution_id = os.environ["execution_id"]

                filepath = self.python_client_reporting_utils.upload_dataframes(
                    pstr_execution_id, filename, outputfile_
                )
                return filepath
            else:
                raise Exception(
                    "Data Type should be DataFrame type and length can't be exceeded more than 2."
                )
        else:
            raise Exception(
                "For Auto Exporting Results plist_result_dataframes param must be a list type"
            )
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error in __upload_dataframe_s3" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in __upload_dataframe_s3" + str(e))

    def add_feature_return_success_failure(self, pstr_key, pstr_filename):
    """
    Description: This is internal method to write into the json file once any scenario is called from a feature file
    :param pstr_key: This is the key which gets updated
    :param pstr_filename: This is the filename which needs to be updated
    :return: Boolean
    """
    try:
        pbool_lock_acquired = False
        lock = LockFile(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_filename)
        while not lock.i_am_locking():
            try:
                lock.acquire(timeout=240)
            except LockTimeout:
                lock.break_lock()
                lock.acquire()
        if lock.i_am_locking():
            pbool_lock_acquired = True
        with open(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_filename, "r") as readfile:
            data = json.load(readfile)
            readfile.close()
        temp = data
        if pstr_key in temp:
            return False
        temp[pstr_key] = ""
        json_data = json.dumps(temp, indent=4)
        with open(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_filename, "w") as writefile:
            writefile.write(json_data)
            writefile.close()
            return True
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error occcured in add_feature_return_success_failure-->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception(
            "Error occcured in add_feature_return_success_failure-->" + str(e)
        )
    finally:
        if pbool_lock_acquired:
            lock.release()

    def add_key_value_in_json(self, pstr_key, pstr_value, pstr_filename):
    """
    Description: This is the method which adds the key value pair in json file
    :param pstr_key: This is the key to be added
    :param pstr_value: This is the value to be added
    :param pstr_filename: This is the filename in which key value to be added
    :return: None
    """
    try:
        thread_lock = threading.Semaphore()
        thread_lock.acquire()
        pbool_lock_acquired = False
        lock = LockFile(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_filename)
        while not lock.i_am_locking():
            try:
                lock.acquire(timeout=240)

            except LockTimeout:
                lock.break_lock()
                lock.acquire()
        if lock.i_am_locking():
            pbool_lock_acquired = True
        with open(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_filename, "r") as readfile:
            data = json.load(readfile)
            readfile.close()
        temp = data

        temp[pstr_key] = pstr_value
        json_data = json.dumps(temp, indent=4)
        with open(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_filename, "w") as writefile:
            writefile.write(json_data)
            writefile.close()

    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error occcured in add_key_value_in_json-->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error occcured in add_key_value_in_json-->" + str(e))
    finally:
        if pbool_lock_acquired:
            lock.release()
        thread_lock.release()

    def after_step_auto_dash_configuration(self, pobj_step):
    """
    Description:
        |  this method is to get step status after a step get executes

    :param pobj_step: pobj_step is the step object which would be passed from the hooks
    :type pobj_step: object
    """
    try:
        if self.is_report:
            if "--lf" in sys.argv or os.environ["execution_id"]:
                if os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id" in globals():
                    step_details = self.get_dict_obj("current_step_details")
                    step_details["stepStatus"] = self.get_step_status_based_on_asserts(
                        pobj_step
                    )
                    step_details["stepEndTime"] = self.get_current_date_time()
                    step_details["stepDuration"] = self.get_time_difference_seconds(
                        step_details["stepEndTime"],
                        globals()[
                            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_stepStartTime"
                        ],
                    )
                    scen_tags = self.get_list_obj("scenario_tags")
                    step_details["evidence"] = {}
                    step_id = globals().get(
                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"
                    )

                    if not int(
                        globals()[
                            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + step_id + "_isAssertPresent"
                        ]
                    ):
                        step_details["isAssertPresent"] = 0
                        if any(item in self.take_screenshot_tags for item in scen_tags):
                            str_screenshot_path = self.getscreenshot(
                                self.get_current_date_time(), scen_tags
                            )
                            step_details["evidence"]["screenshotEvidence"] = str_screenshot_path
                    else:
                        step_details["isAssertPresent"] = 1
                    step_details.pop("stepStartTime")
                    self.update_step_data(step_details)
                    globals()[
                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_details"
                    ] = str(step_details)

    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error in after_step_auto_dash_configuration-->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in after_step_auto_dash_configuration-->" + str(e))
    finally:
        self.pop_value_from_globals(os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id")
        self.pop_value_from_globals(
            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id" + "_isAssertPresent"
        )

    def attach_api_request_response(self, pobj_api_response):
    """
    Description:
        |  This method creates documentation of an API call into a json file and uploads it onto the FTP location

    :param pobj_api_response: API Response Object
    :type pobj_api_response: Response
    :return: None
    """
    try:

        scenario_details = {}
        step_details_api = []
        req_response_details = {}
        step_timer_details = []
        step_timer = {}

        pstr_step = (
            str((datetime.datetime.now()).strftime("%H:%M:%S.%f"))
            .replace("-", "")
            .replace(" ", "")
            .replace("+", "")
            .replace(":", "")
            .replace(".", "")
        )
        scenarioname_sid = (
            str(
                globals().get(os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_name")
            ).replace(" ", "_")
            + "_"
        )
        scenarioname_sid1 = "Scenario_Id_" + globals().get(
            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id"
        )

        req_response_details["StepName"] = globals().get(
            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_name"
        )
        req_response_details["Current_Dataset"] = globals().get(
            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_dataset"
        )
        req_response_details["Request_Method"] = pobj_api_response.request.method
        req_response_details["Request_URL"] = pobj_api_response.request.url
        req_response_details["Request_Headers"] = pobj_api_response.request.headers
        if bool(pobj_api_response.request._cookies._cookies):
            req_response_details.update(
                {"Request_Cookies": str(pobj_api_response.request._cookies._cookies)}
            )
        if bool(pobj_api_response.request.body):
            req_response_details.update(
                {"Request_Payload": str(pobj_api_response.request.body)}
            )

        req_response_details["Response_Code"] = pobj_api_response.status_code
        req_response_details["Response_Time"] = pobj_api_response.elapsed.total_seconds()
        req_response_details["Response_Headers"] = pobj_api_response.headers
        req_response_details["Response_Text"] = pobj_api_response.text
        step_timer_details.append(req_response_details)
        current_step_id = globals().get(
            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"
        )
        step_details_api.append({current_step_id: step_timer_details})

        if (
            "feature_name"
            not in globals()[
                os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "scenario_data_modify"
            ].keys()
        ):
            globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "scenario_data_modify"][
                "Feature_Name"
            ] = globals().get(os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_feature_name")
        if (
            "scenario_name"
            not in globals()[
                os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "scenario_data_modify"
            ].keys()
        ):
            globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "scenario_data_modify"][
                "Scenario_Name"
            ] = globals().get(os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_name")

        try:
            if (
                scenarioname_sid1
                not in globals()[
                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "scenario_data_modify"
                ].keys()
            ):
                globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "scenario_data_modify"][
                    scenarioname_sid1
                ] = step_details_api
            else:
                globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "scenario_data_modify"][
                    scenarioname_sid1
                ].extend(step_details_api)
        except Exception as e1:
            globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "scenario_data_modify"] = {
                scenarioname_sid1: step_details_api
            }

        binary = str(step_details_api)
        binary1 = ast.literal_eval(binary)
        binary1 = json.dumps(binary1)
        self.json_path_value = (
            self.set_endtime()
            .replace("-", "")
            .replace(" ", "")
            .replace("+", "")
            .replace(":", "")
            .replace(".", "")
        )
        session = self.python_client_reporting_utils.open_aws_session()
        self.cli = self.python_client_reporting_utils.open_s3_client(session)
        pstr_execution_id = os.environ["execution_id"]
        encoded = base64.b64encode(binary1.encode("utf_8"))

        return self.python_client_reporting_utils.save_api_response(
            self.cli, encoded, pstr_execution_id, self.json_path_value
        )

    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error(
            "Exception occurred while extracting and uploading the api response evidence ->"
            + str(e)
        )
        self.cafe_logger.exception(
            "Exception occurred while extracting and uploading the api response evidence ->"
            + str(e)
        )
        raise Exception(
            "Exception occurred while extracting and uploading the api response evidence  ->"
            + str(e)
        )

    def before_step_auto_dash_configuration(self, pobj_step):
    """
    Description:
        |  This method is to fetch headers of scenario out line step

    :param pobj_globaldict: pobj_globaldict is the pytest global dict object
    :type pobj_globaldict: dict
    :param pobj_scenario: pobj_scenario is the scenario object
    :type pobj_scenario: object
    :param pobj_step: pobj_step is the step object
    :type pobj_step: object
    """
    try:
        if self.is_report:
            str_step_name = pobj_step.name
            if len(str_step_name) > 1990:
                str_step_name = pobj_step.name[0:1990]
            globals()[
                os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_name"
            ] = str_step_name
            globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "failed_assert"] = "0"
            if "--lf" in sys.argv or os.environ["execution_id"]:
                if os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id" in globals():
                    dict_example_set = {}
                    if os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "example_set" in globals():
                        dict_example_set = self.create_dict_from_comma_separated_string(
                            globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "example_set"]
                        )
                    step_details = {}
                    str_step_name = str(pobj_step).replace('"', "")
                    if "<" and ">" in str_step_name:
                        for k, v in dict_example_set.items():
                            if "<" + k.strip() + ">" in str_step_name:
                                str_step_name = str_step_name.replace(
                                    "<" + k.strip() + ">", "<" + v.strip() + ">"
                                )
                    if len(str_step_name) > 1990:
                        str_step_name = str_step_name[0:1990]
                    step_details["stepName"] = str_step_name
                    step_details["stepStatus"] = "IC"
                    pytest.globalDict["step_name"] = str_step_name
                    step_details["stepStartTime"] = self.get_current_date_time()
                    globals()[
                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_stepStartTime"
                    ] = str(self.get_current_date_time())
                    step_details["stepType"] = str(pobj_step).strip().upper()[0:1]
                    if step_details["stepType"] not in ("G", "W", "T", "A"):
                        pytest.fail("Step Name does not start with Given, When, Then, And")
                    if "--lf" in sys.argv:
                        step_details["reRunIteration"] = self.config_utils.base_config[
                            "rerun_iteration"
                        ]
                    self.push_step_data(step_details)
                    self.save_step_details(step_details)
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error in before_step_auto_dash_configuration-->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in before_step_auto_dash_configuration-->" + str(e))

    def check_failure_tests_exists(self):
    """
    Description: Check is failed test cases exist
    :return: Boolean
    """
    try:
        projectpath = self.config_utils.get_project_path()
        with open(projectpath + "/" + ".pytest_cache/v/cache/lastfailed", "r") as f:
            b = f.read()
            f.close()
        d = json.loads(b)
        up_json = {}
        for k, v in d.items():
            if len(k) != 0:
                up_json[k] = v
        if len(up_json) > 0:
            return True
        else:
            return False
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error in check_failure_tests_exists -->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in check_failure_tests_exists -->" + str(e))
        return False

    def check_key_exists_in_json(self, pstr_key_name, pstr_filename):
    """
    Description: This is the method to check if the key exists in json file
    :param pstr_key_name: This is the key name which needs to be checked
    :param pstr_filename: This is the filename which needs to be verified
    :return: Boolean
    """
    try:
        lock = LockFile(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_filename)
        pbool_lock_acquired = False
        while not lock.i_am_locking():
            try:
                lock.acquire(timeout=240)

            except LockTimeout:
                lock.break_lock()
                lock.acquire()
        if lock.i_am_locking():
            pbool_lock_acquired = True
        with open(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_filename, "r") as readfile:
            data = json.load(readfile)
            readfile.close()
        if pstr_key_name in data:
            return True
        else:
            return False
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error occcured in check_key_exists_in_json-->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error occcured in check_key_exists_in_json-->" + str(e))
    finally:
        if pbool_lock_acquired:
            lock.release()

    def collect_feature_details(self, pobj_feature, feature_file, feature_file_plus_feature_name):
    """
    Description: This is the method to collect feature details from a feature object
    :param request: This is the pytest request object
    :param pobj_feature: This is the pytest feature object
    :param pobj_scenario: This is the pytest scenario object
    :return: None
    """
    try:
        self.logger.info("Inside Collect feature details")
        str_key = "WorkingWith_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name
        lock = threading.Semaphore()
        lock.acquire()
        if self.add_feature_return_success_failure(
            str_key, pstr_temp_feature_data_to_push_filename
        ):
            lock.release()
            self.logger.info("Collecting feature details for " + feature_file_plus_feature_name)
            pbool_valid_feature = True
            if len(pobj_feature.tags) == 0:
                pbool_valid_feature = False
            feature_details = {}
            evidence = {}
            feature_details["evidence"] = evidence
            feature_details["executionId"] = os.environ["execution_id"]
            feature_details["featureName"] = feature_file_plus_feature_name
            feature_details["featureDescription"] = pobj_feature.description
            feature_details["executionStartTime"] = self.get_current_date_time()
            globals()["startTime_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name] = feature_details[
                "executionStartTime"
            ]
            feature_details["featureStatus"] = "IC"
            feature_details["totalPassed"] = 0
            feature_details["totalFailed"] = 0
            feature_details["executionEndTime"] = ""
            feature_details["featureDuration"] = 0
            feature_details["environmentId"] = None
            feature_details["optionalTag"] = None
            feature_details["productId"] = None
            feature_details["platformName"] = None
            platform_tag_id, team_tag_id, product_id, remaining_tags = (
                self.get_platform_team_tag(pobj_feature.tags)
            )
            functionality_tag_id, remaining_tags = self.get_functionality_tag(
                pobj_feature.tags, product_id, remaining_tags
            )

            optional_tag = self.get_feature_optional_tags(remaining_tags)
            feature_details["productId"] = product_id
            if optional_tag:
                feature_details["optionalTag"] = optional_tag
            str_platform_name, platform_id = self.get_platform_name_based_on_product_id(
                product_id
            )
            feature_details["platformId"] = platform_id
            if platform_tag_id:
                if not self.check_key_exists_in_json(
                    platform_tag_id, pstr_temp_platform_tag_file
                ):
                    if str_platform_name:
                        feature_details["environmentId"] = (
                            self.get_execution_environment_code_based_on_platformname_env_and_type(
                                str_platform_name,
                                os.environ["execution_environment"],
                                os.environ["environment_type"],
                            )
                        )
                        self.add_key_value_in_json(
                            platform_tag_id,
                            feature_details["environmentId"],
                            pstr_temp_platform_tag_file,
                        )
                else:
                    feature_details["environmentId"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                        platform_tag_id, pstr_temp_platform_tag_file
                    )
            feature_details["platformTag"] = platform_tag_id
            feature_details["functionalityTag"] = functionality_tag_id
            feature_details["teamTag"] = team_tag_id

            str_skip_reason = self.do_we_need_to_skip_test_based_on_feature_tags(
                platform_tag_id,
                functionality_tag_id,
                team_tag_id,
                feature_file_plus_feature_name,
                feature_file,
                pbool_valid_feature,
            )
            if not pytest.globalDict["releasesprint_tag_name_lookup"]:
                pytest.globalDict["releasesprint_tag_name_lookup"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                    "releasesprint_tag_name_lookup", pstr_team_release_tag_names_file
                )
            release_sprint, feature_details["releaseSprintId"] = (
                self.get_release_sprint_id_from_tag_name(
                    pobj_feature.tags,
                    feature_file,
                    pytest.globalDict["releasesprint_tag_name_lookup"],
                )
            )
            feature_details["releaseSprintTag"] = release_sprint
            if str_skip_reason:
                if len(str_skip_reason) > 3995:
                    str_skip_reason = str_skip_reason[0:3995]
                evidence["errorType"] = CafeConstants.ERROR_CODE_TWO
                evidence["exceptionEvidence"] = str_skip_reason
            feature_details["evidence"] = evidence

            self.logger.info("Pushing feature details with data " + str(feature_details))
            self.push_feature_data(feature_details, feature_file_plus_feature_name)
            self.logger.info("Pushed feature details " + str(feature_details))
            self.save_feature_details(feature_details)

            if str_skip_reason:
                feature_details["executionEndTime"] = self.get_current_date_time()
                feature_details["featureDuration"] = self.get_time_difference_seconds(
                    feature_details["executionEndTime"], feature_details["executionStartTime"]
                )
                feature_details.pop("executionStartTime")
                self.update_feature_data(feature_details, feature_file_plus_feature_name)
                self.logger.info(
                    "Skipping Scenarios from feature file: "
                    + feature_file
                    + "  as  "
                    + str(str_skip_reason)
                )
                pytest.skip(
                    "Skipping Scenarios from feature file: "
                    + feature_file
                    + "  as  "
                    + str(str_skip_reason)
                )
        else:
            globals()[
                "startTime_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name
            ] = self.get_current_date_time()
            lock.release()

    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error occured in collect_feature_details-->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error occured in collect_feature_details-->" + str(e))

    def collect_lookup_info(self):
    """
    Description: This method is to collect the lookup information.
    :return: None
    """
    try:
        try:
            self.python_client_reporting_utils.generate_token()
        except Exception as e1:
            self.logger.info("Exception occured while generating token " + str(e1))
            pytest.exit(str(e1))
        map_priorities_lookup = self.python_client_reporting_utils.get_lookup_values("priority")
        map_automationstatus_lookup = self.python_client_reporting_utils.get_lookup_values(
            "automationstatus"
        )
        map_testingtype_lookup = self.python_client_reporting_utils.get_lookup_values(
            "testingtype"
        )
        map_optionaltags_lookup = self.python_client_reporting_utils.get_lookup_values(
            "optional"
        )
        map_scenariocategory_lookup = self.python_client_reporting_utils.get_lookup_values(
            "scenariocategory"
        )
        map_testdatatype_lookup = self.python_client_reporting_utils.get_lookup_values(
            "testdatatype"
        )
        map_featureoptionaltag_lookup = self.python_client_reporting_utils.get_lookup_values(
            "feature_optionaltag"
        )
        map_acceptable_env_lookup = (
            self.python_client_reporting_utils.get_acceptable_environment_lookup()
        )
        map_release_sprint_id_lookup = (
            self.python_client_reporting_utils.get_release_sprint_code_values()
        )
        map_release_sprint_tag_names_lookup = (
            self.python_client_reporting_utils.get_release_sprint_tag_name_values()
        )
        list_dict_platformtag_lookup = (
            self.python_client_reporting_utils.get_platform_tag_lookup_values()
        )
        lst_of_dict_functionality_tag_lookup = (
            self.python_client_reporting_utils.get_functionality_tag_lookup_values()
        )
        map_team_tag_lookup = self.python_client_reporting_utils.get_team_tag_lookup_values()
        map_product_lookup = self.python_client_reporting_utils.get_product_lookup_values()
        map_framework_lookup = self.python_client_reporting_utils.get_framework_master_data()
        map_env_types_lookup = self.python_client_reporting_utils.get_environment_types()
        map_platform_lookup = self.python_client_reporting_utils.get_platform_lookup_values()

        if map_platform_lookup:
            self.add_key_value_in_json("platform_lookup", map_platform_lookup, pstr_temp_misc)

        if map_env_types_lookup:
            self.add_key_value_in_json(
                "environment_type_lookup", map_env_types_lookup, pstr_temp_misc
            )

        if map_framework_lookup:
            self.add_key_value_in_json("framework_lookup", map_framework_lookup, pstr_temp_misc)

        if map_optionaltags_lookup:
            self.add_key_value_in_json(
                "optionaltags_lookup", map_optionaltags_lookup, pstr_temp_execution_filename
            )
        if map_scenariocategory_lookup:
            self.add_key_value_in_json(
                "scenariocategory_lookup",

                pstr_temp_execution_filename,
            )
        if map_featureoptionaltag_lookup:
            self.add_key_value_in_json(
                "feature_optionaltags_lookup",
                map_featureoptionaltag_lookup,
                pstr_temp_execution_filename,
            )

        if map_release_sprint_id_lookup:
            self.add_key_value_in_json(
                "releasesprint_lookup", map_release_sprint_id_lookup, pstr_temp_release_tag_file
            )

        if map_release_sprint_tag_names_lookup:
            self.add_key_value_in_json(
                "releasesprint_tag_name_lookup",
                map_release_sprint_tag_names_lookup,
                pstr_team_release_tag_names_file,
            )

        if list_dict_platformtag_lookup:
            self.add_key_value_in_json(
                "platformtag_lookup", list_dict_platformtag_lookup, pstr_temp_platform_tag_file

        if lst_of_dict_functionality_tag_lookup:
            self.add_key_value_in_json(

            )
        if map_acceptable_env_lookup:

    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()

    def create_exception_log_file_s3(self, pstr_execution_id):
    """
    Description:
            |  This method creates a an empty file on ftp and returns complete path of the created file

    :param pstr_execution_id: This parameter takes execution id
    :type pstr_execution_id: String
    :param pbyte_buffer: This content of FTP file
    :type pbyte_buffer: Byte

    :return: String
    """
    try:
        str_exception_value = (
            self.set_endtime()
            .replace("-", "")
            .replace(" ", "")
            .replace("+", "")
            .replace(":", "")
            .replace(".", "")
        )
        dict1 = self.python_client_reporting_utils.read_content_from_s3_for_execution_Id(
            pstr_execution_id
        )
        str_exception_log_file_name = str_exception_value + ".json"
        if str_exception_log_file_name in dict1:
            self.cafe_logger.info(
                f"The file {str_exception_log_file_name} already exists in S3"
            )
            str_exception_value = (
                self.set_endtime()
                .replace("-", "")
                .replace(" ", "")
                .replace("+", "")
                .replace(":", "")
                .replace(".", "")
            )
            str_exception_log_file_name = str_exception_value + ".json"

        str_final_path = (
            self.str_virtual_directory_path
            + self.str_bucket_directory
            + pstr_execution_id
            + "%2F"
            + str_exception_log_file_name
        )
        self.cafe_logger.info(f"Created exception log file {str_final_path} on S3")
        return str_final_path
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error(f"Error while creating exception log file on Kibana-->{str(e)}")
        self.cafe_logger.exception(
            f"Error while creating exception log file on Kibana-->{str(e)}"
        )

    def decrement_value_for_key(self, pstr_key_name, pstr_filename):
    """
    Description: This method decrements the count of a key in json
    :param pstr_key_name: This is the key to be decremented
    :param pstr_filename: This is the filename in which the key exists
    :return: None
    """
    try:
        pbool_lock_acquired = False
        lock = LockFile(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_filename)
        while not lock.i_am_locking():
            try:
                lock.acquire(timeout=240)
                # wait up to 240 seconds
            except LockTimeout:
                lock.break_lock()
                lock.acquire()
        if lock.i_am_locking():
            pbool_lock_acquired = True
        with open(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_filename, "r") as readfile:
            data = json.load(readfile)
            readfile.close()
        temp = data
        if pstr_key_name in temp:
            int_count = int(temp[pstr_key_name])
            if int_count != 0:
                temp[pstr_key_name] = int_count - 1
        else:
            temp[pstr_key_name] = 0
        json_data = json.dumps(temp, indent=4)
        with open(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_filename, "w") as writefile:
            writefile.write(json_data)
            writefile.close()
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error occcured in decrement_value_for_key-->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error occcured in decrement_value_for_key-->" + str(e))
        raise Exception("Error occcured in decrement_value_for_key-->" + str(e))
    finally:
        if pbool_lock_acquired:
            lock.release()

    def delete_execution_files(self):
    """
    Description: This method deletes the Execution.json and resets the content of log file
    :return: None
    """
    try:

        pstr_path = self.automation_log_path
        files = os.listdir(pstr_path)
        for name in files:
            if name.startswith("Temp_") or name == "Execution.json":
                os.remove(pstr_path + os.sep + name)
        with open(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_log_file_name, "w") as somefile:
            somefile.write("")
            somefile.close()

    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error occured in delete_execution_files-> " + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error occured in delete_execution_files-> " + str(e))

    def delete_file_lock_files(self):
    """
    Description: This method deletes all the lock files created during locking a Execution.json file
    :return: None
    """
    try:
        pattern = str(os.environ.get("computername")) + "*"
        pstr_path = self.automation_log_path
        files = os.listdir(pstr_path)
        for name in files:
            bln_found = fnmatch.fnmatch(name, pattern)
            if bln_found:
                os.remove(pstr_path + os.sep + name)
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error occured in delete_file_lock_files-> " + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error occured in delete_file_lock_files-> " + str(e))

    def get_data_set_info(self, request, pobj_scenario, pdict_scenario_details, pobj_globaldict):
    """
    Description: This is the method used for collecting the data set info
    :param request: pytest request object
    :param pdict_scenario_details: scenario details dictionary
    :param pobj_globaldict: Global Dictionary Object
    :return:
    """
    try:
        str_testdatatype_full_value = None
        headers = []
        pdict_scenario_details["isDataDriven"] = 0
        if "data_driven_keys" in pobj_globaldict.keys():
            headers = pytest.globalDict["data_driven_keys"]
        if len(request.node.funcargs) > 1:
            pdict_scenario_details["isDataDriven"] = 1

        if len(pobj_scenario.examples.examples) > 0:
            pdict_scenario_details["isOutline"] = 1
            pdict_scenario_details["isDataDriven"] = 0
            str_testdatatype_full_value = "Outline"
        else:
            pdict_scenario_details["isOutline"] = 0

        example = ""
        if len(pobj_scenario.examples.examples) > 0 or pdict_scenario_details["isDataDriven"]:
            data_set = copy.copy(request.node.funcargs)
            if "request" in data_set:
                data_set.pop("request")
            data_set = str(dict(sorted(data_set.items()))).replace("'", "")
            name_request = str(request)
            first_square_bracket = name_request.find("[")
            last_square_bracket = name_request.rfind("]")
            example = name_request[first_square_bracket + 1 : last_square_bracket]
            if not example:
                pdict_scenario_details["example"] = None
            else:
                if len(data_set) > 7990:
                    pdict_scenario_details["example"] = str(data_set)[0:7990]
                    first_curly_bracket = data_set.find("{")
                    last_curly_bracket = data_set.rfind("}")
                    data_set = data_set[first_curly_bracket + 1 : last_curly_bracket]
                    globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "example_set"] = data_set
                else:
                    pdict_scenario_details["example"] = str(data_set)
                    first_curly_bracket = data_set.find("{")
                    last_curly_bracket = data_set.rfind("}")
                    data_set = data_set[first_curly_bracket + 1 : last_curly_bracket]
                    globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "example_set"] = data_set

        if str_testdatatype_full_value:
            pdict_scenario_details["testDataType"] = self.get_test_data_type_value(
                str_testdatatype_full_value
            )

        return pdict_scenario_details, example

    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error in get_data_set_info -->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in get_data_set_info -->" + str(e))

    def get_dict_obj(self, pstr_name):
    """
    Description: This is to convert the string object to dict stored in globals variables
    :param pstr_name: This is the name of the variable with which the value is stored in globals variables.
    :return: dict
    """
    try:
        str_name = pstr_name
        json_object = ""
        if os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + str_name in globals():
            json_object = globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + str_name]
        items = dict()
        if json_object != "":
            json_object.replace("'", '"')
            json_object = ast.literal_eval(json_object)
            return json_object
        else:
            return items
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error in get_dict_obj-->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in get_dict_obj-->" + str(e))

    def get_dict_obj_from_environ(self, pstr_name):
    """
    Description: This is to convert the string object to dict stored in environment variables
    :param pstr_name: This is the name of the variable with which the value is stored in environment variables.
    :return: dict
    """
    try:
        str_name = pstr_name
        json_object = ""
        if str_name in os.environ:
            json_object = os.environ[str_name]
        items = dict()
        if json_object != "":
            json_object.replace("'", '"')
            json_object = ast.literal_eval(json_object)
            return json_object
        else:
            return items
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
