    def get_evidence_details(self, pstr_evidence_type):
    """
    Description: This method is to collect the excpetion/screenshot evidence
    :param pstr_evidence_type: This is variable to decide what type of evidence is needed.
    :return: Dict
    """
    try:
        evidence = {}
        if len(sys.exc_info()) > 0:
            tb = sys.exc_info()[2]
            try:
                evidence["exceptionEvidence"] = None
                while tb:
                    if not tb.tb_next:
                        break
                    tb = tb.tb_next
                bool_failed_assert = self.get_int_value(
                    globals().get(os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "failed_assert")
                )
                if (tb and pstr_evidence_type in ("scenario")) or (
                    tb and not bool_failed_assert
                ):
                    evidence["detailException"] = (
                        self.upload_exception_for_step_error_or_exception(
                            str(traceback.format_exc())
                        )
                    )
                    if "e" in sys.exc_info()[2].tb_frame.f_locals:
                        exception_in_tb = repr(sys.exc_info()[2].tb_frame.f_locals["e"])
                        error_type = self.obj_error_category.get_error_code_from_exception(
                            exception_in_tb
                        )
                        evidence["errorType"] = error_type
                        evidence["exceptionEvidence"] = repr(
                            sys.exc_info()[2].tb_frame.f_locals["e"]
                        )
                    elif "exception" in sys.exc_info()[2].tb_frame.f_locals:
                        exception_in_tb = repr(sys.exc_info()[2].tb_frame.f_locals["exception"])
                        evidence["exceptionEvidence"] = repr(
                            sys.exc_info()[2].tb_frame.f_locals["exception"]
                        )
                        error_type = self.obj_error_category.get_error_code_from_exception(
                            exception_in_tb
                        )
                        evidence["errorType"] = error_type
                    else:
                        evidence["exceptionEvidence"] = "Exception Occured"
                        evidence["errorType"] = CafeConstants.ERROR_CODE_ZERO

            except Exception as e:
                self.logger.error("Get evidence -> " + str(e))
                self.cafe_logger.exception("Get evidence -> " + str(e))
            scen_tags = self.get_list_obj("scenario_tags")
            str_screenshot_path = None
            if pstr_evidence_type in ("step"):
                if tb:
                    temp = ""
                    if traceback.format_list(traceback.extract_stack(limit=1000)):
                        for i in traceback.format_list(traceback.extract_stack(limit=1000)):
                            if (
                                (
                                    f"{os.sep}cafe{os.sep}" in i
                                    or f"{os.sep}features{os.sep}" in i
                                )
                                and "get_evidence_details" not in i
                                and "pytest_after_scenario_auto_dash_configuration" not in i
                            ):
                                temp += i
                    str_exception = str(traceback.format_exc())
                    if temp:
                        str_exception = (
                            temp
                            + "\n "
                            + "==========================================\n"
                            + str(traceback.format_exc())
                        )
                    evidence["detailException"] = (
                        self.upload_exception_for_step_error_or_exception(str_exception)
                    )
                step_id = globals().get(
                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"
                )
                if not int(
                    globals()[
                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + step_id + "_isAssertPresent"
                    ]
                ):
                    if any(item in self.take_screenshot_tags for item in scen_tags):
                        try:
                            str_screenshot_path = self.getscreenshot(
                                self.get_current_date_time(), scen_tags
                            )
                        except Exception as ex:
                            if evidence["exceptionEvidence"]:
                                evidence["exceptionEvidence"] = (
                                    str(evidence["exceptionEvidence"])
                                    + "\n"
                                    + "----ALSO NOTE ----"
                                    + "\n"
                                    + str(ex)
                                )
                            else:
                                evidence["exceptionEvidence"] = (
                                    "\n" + "----ALSO NOTE ----" + "\n" + str(ex)
                                )
            elif pstr_evidence_type in ("scenario"):
                if any(item in self.take_screenshot_tags for item in scen_tags):
                    try:
                        str_screenshot_path = self.getscreenshot(
                            self.get_current_date_time(), scen_tags
                        )
                        if not ".png" in str_screenshot_path:
                            str_screenshot_path = None
                    except Exception as ex1:
                        if evidence["exceptionEvidence"]:
                            evidence["exceptionEvidence"] = (
                                str(evidence["exceptionEvidence"])
                                + "\n"
                                + "----ALSO NOTE ----"
                                + "\n"
                                + str(ex1)
                            )
                        else:
                            evidence["exceptionEvidence"] = (
                                "\n" + "----ALSO NOTE ----" + "\n" + str(ex1)
                            )
                        self.cafe_logger.exception(
                            "Could not take screenshot. Exception occured" + str(ex1)
                        )

            evidence["evidence"] = str_screenshot_path

        if "exceptionEvidence" in evidence.keys() and evidence["exceptionEvidence"]:
            if len(evidence["exceptionEvidence"]) > 3995:
                evidence["exceptionEvidence"] = (evidence["exceptionEvidence"])[:3995]

        if not globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "scenario_failure_reason"]:
            if "exceptionEvidence" in evidence.keys():
                if (
                    evidence["exceptionEvidence"]
                    and evidence["exceptionEvidence"] != "Exception Occured"
                ):
                    globals()[
                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "scenario_failure_reason"
                    ] = evidence["exceptionEvidence"]
            if not globals()[
                os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "scenario_failure_reason"
            ] and ("detailException" in evidence.keys() and evidence["detailException"]):
                globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "scenario_failure_reason"] = (
                    str(traceback.format_exc())
                )
        return evidence

    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error occured in get_evidence_details " + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error occured in get_evidence_details " + str(e))

    def get_execution_mode(self):
    """
    Description: This method is called
    :return:
    """
    try:
        if "is_debug_execution" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
            debug_execution = self.config_utils.base_config["is_debug_execution"]
            if str(debug_execution) in ("True", "true", "TRUE"):
                return 1
        else:
            self.cafe_logger.warning(
                "Warning!!! Please add 'is_debug_execution' key in config.yml file. This will ensure there is no junk data in Reporting"
            )
        if "Debug" in str(sys.stdin):
            return 1
        else:
            return 0
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error occured in get_execution_mode -->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error occured in get_execution_mode -->" + str(e))

    def get_feature_file_and_its_name(self, pobj_feature):
    """
    Description: This is the method to fetch the file name and filename plus feature name from a feature object
    :param pobj_feature: This is the pytest feature object
    :return: Strings
    """
    try:
        filename = pobj_feature.rel_filename
        int_last_forward_slash = filename.rfind("/")
        int_last_backward_slash = filename.rfind("\\")
        int_last_slash = max(int_last_forward_slash, int_last_backward_slash)
        feature_file = filename[int_last_slash + 1 :].replace(".feature", "")
        feature_file_plus_feature_name = (
            filename[int_last_slash + 1 :]
            + " :: "
            + str(pobj_feature.name).replace('"', "").replace("'", "")
        )

        return feature_file, feature_file_plus_feature_name
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error occured in get_feature_file_and_its_name-->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error occured in get_feature_file_and_its_name-->" + str(e))

    def get_feature_optional_tags(self, pstr_tags):
    """
    Description: This method returns the optional tags code value
    :param pstr_tags: Remaning tags after taking out functional, team, platformtag
    :param pstr_scenario_tags: All the scenario tags available
    :return: Optional Tag Code (String)
    """
    try:

        if not pytest.globalDict["feature_optionaltags_lookup"]:
            pytest.globalDict["feature_optionaltags_lookup"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                "feature_optionaltags_lookup", pstr_temp_execution_filename
            )
        optional_tag = None
        if not pstr_tags:
            return None
        for tag in pstr_tags:
            tag = tag.strip()
            if tag in pytest.globalDict["feature_optionaltags_lookup"]:
                if not optional_tag:
                    optional_tag = pytest.globalDict["feature_optionaltags_lookup"][tag]
                else:
                    optional_tag = (
                        optional_tag
                        + ","
                        + str(pytest.globalDict["feature_optionaltags_lookup"][tag])
                    )
        return optional_tag
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error occured in get_feature_optional_tags -->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error occured in get_feature_optional_tags -->" + str(e))

    def get_list_obj(self, pstr_name):
    """
    Description: This is to convert the string object to list stored in globals variables
    :param pstr_name: This is the name of the variable with which the value is stored in globals variables.
    :return: list
    """
    try:
        str_name = pstr_name
        lst_object = ""
        if os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + str_name in globals():
            lst_object = globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + str_name]
        items = list()
        if lst_object != "":
            lst_object.replace("'", '"')
            lst_object = eval(lst_object)
            return list(lst_object)
        else:
            return items
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error in get_list_obj-->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in get_list_obj-->" + str(e))

    def get_logger_for_this_file(self):
    """
    Description: This is to get logs for this kibana_reporting.py file
    :return: logging
    """
    try:
        log_level = logging.ERROR
        if "kibana_log_level" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
            str_level = self.config_utils.base_config["kibana_log_level"]
            if str_level.lower() == "error":
                log_level = logging.ERROR
            elif str_level.lower() == "info":
                log_level = logging.INFO
            elif str_level.lower() == "debug":
                log_level = logging.DEBUG
        logger = logging.getLogger("kibana_logger")
        logger.setLevel(log_level)
        hdlr = logging.handlers.RotatingFileHandler(
            self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_log_file_name,
            maxBytes=50000000,
            backupCount=3,
        )
        formatter = logging.Formatter(
            "[%(asctime)s] - %(levelname)s - [%(module)s] %(message)s"
        )
        hdlr.setFormatter(formatter)
        if logger.hasHandlers():
            logger.handlers.clear()
        logger.addHandler(hdlr)
        logger.propagate = False
        return logger

    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        raise Exception("Error occured while setting and getting logging " + str(e))

    def get_pass_fail_count_for_a_feature(self, pstr_feature_file_plus_feature_name):
    """
    Description: This method returns the passed failed scenarios count based on feature name
    :param pobj_feature: This is the pytest feature object
    :return: total_passed, total_failed
    """
    try:
        self.logger.info("Getting pass/fail count for " + pstr_feature_file_plus_feature_name)
        int_iteration = 3
        while True:
            try:
                passed = self.get_value_from_json(
                    pstr_feature_file_plus_feature_name + "_TotalPassed",
                    pstr_temp_feature_details_pass_fail_count_filename,
                )
                failed = self.get_value_from_json(
                    pstr_feature_file_plus_feature_name + "_TotalFailed",
                    pstr_temp_feature_details_pass_fail_count_filename,
                )
            except:
                int_iteration = int_iteration - 1
                if int_iteration < -1:
                    break
                continue

            else:
                break
        self.logger.info("Got pass fail count -- >" + str(passed) + " / " + str(failed))
        if passed:
            total_passed = int(passed)
        else:
            total_passed = 0
        if failed:
            total_failed = int(failed)
        else:
            total_failed = 0
        return total_passed, total_failed

    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error in get_pass_fail_count_for_a_feature-->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in get_pass_fail_count_for_a_feature-->" + str(e))

    def get_platform_team_tag(self, pstr_feature_tags):
    """
    Description: This method will collect the platform,functionality,team IDs from feature tags
    :return: PlatformId,FunctionalityId,TeamId
    """
    try:
        self.logger.info("Inside get platform and team tag " + str(pstr_feature_tags))
        platform_id = None
        team_id = None
        product_id = None
        remaining_tags = pstr_feature_tags
        if not pytest.globalDict["platformtag_lookup"]:
            self.logger.info("Earlier global data was not set for platformtag_lookup")
            pytest.globalDict["platformtag_lookup"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                "platformtag_lookup", pstr_temp_platform_tag_file
            )
        if not pytest.globalDict["team_lookup"]:
            self.logger.info("Earlier global data was not set for team_lookup")
            pytest.globalDict["team_lookup"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                "team_lookup", pstr_temp_team_tag_file
            )
        plst_feature_tags = list(pstr_feature_tags)
        for tag in plst_feature_tags:
            strip_tag = tag.strip()
            if any(
                d["platformTagName"] == strip_tag
                for d in pytest.globalDict["platformtag_lookup"]
            ):
                remaining_tags.remove(tag)
                lst_platform_ids = [
                    x["platformTagId"]
                    for x in pytest.globalDict["platformtag_lookup"]
                    if any(item == strip_tag for item in x.values())
                ]
                lst_product_ids = [
                    x["productId"]
                    for x in pytest.globalDict["platformtag_lookup"]
                    if any(item == strip_tag for item in x.values())
                ]
                if len(lst_platform_ids) > 0:
                    if not platform_id:
                        platform_id = str(lst_platform_ids[0])
                    else:
                        platform_id = str(platform_id) + "," + str(lst_platform_ids[0])
                if len(lst_product_ids) > 0:
                    if not product_id:
                        product_id = str(lst_product_ids[0])
                    else:
                        product_id = str(product_id) + "," + str(lst_product_ids[0])

            elif any(
                d.strip().lower() == strip_tag.lower()
                for d in pytest.globalDict["team_lookup"].keys()
            ):
                if team_id:
                    for item in pytest.globalDict["team_lookup"].keys():
                        if item.strip().lower() == strip_tag.lower():
                            id = pytest.globalDict["team_lookup"][item]
                            team_id = str(team_id) + "," + str(id)
                else:
                    for item in pytest.globalDict["team_lookup"].keys():
                        if item.strip().lower() == strip_tag.lower():
                            team_id = pytest.globalDict["team_lookup"][item]

        if "," in str(platform_id):
            platform_id = None

        if "," in str(team_id):
            team_id = None

        if "," in str(product_id):
            product_id = None

        return platform_id, team_id, product_id, remaining_tags

    except Exception as e:
        self.logger.error("Error in get_platform_functionality_team_tag-->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in get_platform_functionality_team_tag-->" + str(e))
        return platform_id, team_id, product_id, remaining_tags
    self.print_exception_information()

    def get_priority_testingtype_automation_status_scenario_category_codes(self, plst_tags):
    """
    Description: This method fetches the lookup codes for all priority, testing type and automation status tag.
    :param plst_tags: List of Scenario tags
    :return: Codes
    """

    try:

        priority_tag = None
        testing_type_tag = None
        automation_status_tag = None
        scenario_category_tag = []
        remaining_tags = list(plst_tags)
        for tag in plst_tags:
            strip_tag = tag.strip()
            if strip_tag in pytest.globalDict["priority_lookup"]:
                priority_tag = pytest.globalDict["priority_lookup"][strip_tag]
                remaining_tags.remove(tag)
            elif strip_tag in pytest.globalDict["testingtype_lookup"]:
                testing_type_tag = pytest.globalDict["testingtype_lookup"][strip_tag]
                remaining_tags.remove(tag)
            elif strip_tag in pytest.globalDict["automationstatus_lookup"]:
                automation_status_tag = pytest.globalDict["automationstatus_lookup"][strip_tag]
                remaining_tags.remove(tag)
            elif strip_tag in pytest.globalDict["scenariocategory_lookup"]:
                scenario_category_tag.append(
                    pytest.globalDict["scenariocategory_lookup"][strip_tag]
                )
                remaining_tags.remove(tag)
        return (
            priority_tag,
            testing_type_tag,
            automation_status_tag,
            scenario_category_tag,
            remaining_tags,
        )
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error in get_priority_testingtype_automation-->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in get_priority_testingtype_automation-->" + str(e))

    def get_release_sprint_id_from_tag_name(
    self, pstr_feature_tags, pstr_feature_file, release_sprint_tags_lookup
):
    """
    Description: This method fetches the release sprint id associated with the release sprint tag name
    :param pstr_feature_tags: These are the feature tags
    :param pstr_feature_file: Feature File Name and Its Feature Name
    :return: Release Sprint tag name (str), Release Sprint ID (int)
    """
    try:
        release_sprint_tag = ""
        release_sprint_tag_name = None
        release_sprint_tag_id = None
        release_sprint_tags_lookup_lower = {
            tag_full_name.lower(): tag_id
            for tag_full_name, tag_id in release_sprint_tags_lookup.items()
        }
        count_release_tags = [
            value.lower()
            for value in pstr_feature_tags
            if value.lower() in release_sprint_tags_lookup_lower
        ]
        if len(count_release_tags) > 0:
            if len(count_release_tags) > 1:
                self.cafe_logger.info(
                    f"\n Note : More than one Release sprint tag [{','.join(count_release_tags)}] found in feature File. Feature File name: {pstr_feature_file}"
                )
                print(
                    f"\n Note : More than one Release sprint tag [{','.join(count_release_tags)}] found in feature File. Feature File name:  {pstr_feature_file}"
                )
            else:
                release_sprint_tag = count_release_tags[0]
        if release_sprint_tag in release_sprint_tags_lookup_lower:
            release_sprint_tag_name = release_sprint_tag
            release_sprint_tag_id = release_sprint_tags_lookup_lower[release_sprint_tag]
        elif any(r_tag_.lower().startswith("release_sprint") for r_tag_ in pstr_feature_tags):
            release_sprint_tags_ = [
                r_tag_.lower()
                for r_tag_ in pstr_feature_tags
                if r_tag_.lower().startswith("release_sprint")
            ]
            if len(release_sprint_tags_) > 1:
                self.cafe_logger.info(
                    f"\n Note : More than one Release sprint tag [{','.join(release_sprint_tags_)}] found in feature File. Feature File name: {pstr_feature_file}"
                )
                print(
                    f"\n Note : More than one Release sprint tag [{','.join(release_sprint_tags_)}] found in feature File. Feature File name:  {pstr_feature_file}"
                )
            elif len(release_sprint_tags_) == 0:
                self.cafe_logger.info(
                    f"\n Note : Release sprint tag not found in feature File or provided invalid json tag. Feature File name: {pstr_feature_file}"
                )
                print(
                    f"\n Note : Release sprint tag not found in feature File or provided invalid json tag. Feature File name:  {pstr_feature_file}"
                )
            else:
                release_sprint_tag = release_sprint_tags_[0]
                str_tag = str(release_sprint_tag).strip()
                temp_tag = str_tag.replace("release_sprint_", "")
                if "." in temp_tag and "_" not in temp_tag:
                    lst_tags = temp_tag.split(".")
                elif "_" in temp_tag and "." not in temp_tag:
                    lst_tags = temp_tag.split("_")
                else:
                    lst_tags = []
                    self.cafe_logger.info(
                        f"\n Given Release sprint tag {release_sprint_tag} is not a valid json tag in feature File. '.' or '_' delimiters are not used, Feature File name: {pstr_feature_file}"
                    )
                    print(
                        f"\n Given Release sprint tag {release_sprint_tag} is not a valid json tag in feature File. '.' or '_' delimiters are not used, Feature File name: {pstr_feature_file}"
                    )
                if len(lst_tags) == 3:
                    temp = []
                    for value in lst_tags:
                        if len(value) == 1 and value.isnumeric():
                            temp.append("0" + str(value))
                        else:
                            temp.append(value)
                    temp_tag_ = (
                        "release_sprint_"
                        + str(temp[0])
                        + "."
                        + str(temp[1])
                        + "."
                        + str(temp[2])
                    )
                    if temp_tag_ in release_sprint_tags_lookup_lower:
                        release_sprint_tag_name = temp_tag_
                        release_sprint_tag_id = release_sprint_tags_lookup_lower[temp_tag_]
                    else:
                        self.cafe_logger.info(
                            f"\n Given Release sprint tag {temp_tag_} is not a valid json tag in feature File. Feature File name: {pstr_feature_file}"
                        )
                        print(
                            f"\n Given Release sprint tag {temp_tag_} is not a valid json tag in feature File. Feature File name: {pstr_feature_file}"
                        )
                else:
                    release_sprint_tag_name = release_sprint_tag
                    self.cafe_logger.info(
                        f"\n Given Release tag {release_sprint_tag} is not a valid json tag in feature File. Feature File name: {pstr_feature_file}"
                    )
                    print(
                        f"\n Given Release tag {release_sprint_tag} is not a valid json tag in feature File. Feature File name: {pstr_feature_file}"
                    )
        else:
            self.cafe_logger.info(
                f"\n Release tag is not provided in the feature file or provided a invalid json tag. Feature File name: {pstr_feature_file}"
            )
            print(
                f"\n Release tag is not provided in the feature file or provided a invalid json tag. Feature File name: {pstr_feature_file}"
            )
        if release_sprint_tag_name:
            if release_sprint_tag_id is None:
                release_sprint_tags = list(release_sprint_tags_lookup_lower.keys())
                nearest_matches = difflib.get_close_matches(
                    release_sprint_tag_name, release_sprint_tags, n=3
                )
                self.cafe_logger.info(
                    f"\n Do you mean any of these tags: {','.join(nearest_matches)}"
                )
                self.cafe_logger.info(
                    f"\n Warning! - This feature will not appear in Charts as this release_sprint_tag is not a valid json tag. Feature File Name : {pstr_feature_file}"
                )
                print(f"\n Do you mean any of these tags: {','.join(nearest_matches)}")
                print(
                    f"\n Warning! - This feature will not appear in Charts as this release_sprint_tag is not a valid json tag. Feature File Name : {pstr_feature_file}"
                )
        return release_sprint_tag_name, release_sprint_tag_id
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error occured in get_release_sprint_id_from_tag_name -->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception(
            "Error occured in get_release_sprint_id_from_tag_name -->" + str(e)
        )

    def get_step_status_based_on_asserts(self, pobj_step):
    """
    Description: This method is to get the step status based on assertions within the step.
    :param pobj_step: This is the pytest step object
    :return: String
    """
    try:
        assert_status = self.python_client_reporting_utils.get_assert_status(
            globals().get(os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id")
        )
        if not (assert_status == "Step Id Not Found"):
            if assert_status == "P":
                return "P"
            elif assert_status == "F":
                return "F"
            elif assert_status == "IC":
                return "IC"
        elif pobj_step.failed:
            return "F"
        else:
            return "P"
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error occured in get_step_status_based_on_asserts->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception(
            "Error occured in get_step_status_based_on_asserts->" + str(e)
        )

    def get_string_without_special_chars(self, pstr_string):
    """
    Description: This methdd is to remove special characters from a string
    :param pstr_string: This is the string from which special characters to be removed
    :return: String
    """
    try:
        str_string = str(pstr_string)
        return "".join(achar for achar in str_string if achar.isalnum())
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error occured in get_string_without_special_chars--> " + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception(
            "Error occured in get_string_without_special_chars--> " + str(e)
        )

    def get_time_difference_seconds(self, end, start):
    """
    Description: This method returns the time difference in ms between two times
    :param end:
    :param start:
    :return:
    """
    try:
        end = parser.parse(str(end))
        start = parser.parse(str(start))
        diff = end - start
        diff_in_seconds = diff.days * 24 * 60 * 60 + diff.seconds
        return diff_in_seconds
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error in get_time_difference_seconds-->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in get_time_difference_seconds-->" + str(e))

    def get_value_from_json(self, pstr_key, pstr_filename):
    """
    Description: This is the method to read value from json based on key
    :param pstr_key: This is the key whose value to read
    :param pstr_filename: This is the filename where the key exists
    :return: Value(String)
    """
    try:
        pbool_i_am_locking = False
        lock = LockFile(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_filename)
        while not lock.i_am_locking():
            try:
                lock.acquire(timeout=240)

            except LockTimeout:
                lock.break_lock()
                lock.acquire()
        if lock.i_am_locking():
            pbool_i_am_locking = True
        with open(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_filename, "r") as readfile:
            data = json.load(readfile)
            readfile.close()
        if pstr_key in data:
            return data[pstr_key]
        else:
            return None
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error occcured in get_value_from_json-->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error occcured in get_value_from_json-->" + str(e))
    finally:
        if pbool_i_am_locking:
            lock.release()

    def getscreenshot(self, pstr_end_time, pstr_tags):
    """
    Description:
        |  This Method is used to fetch the screenshot path

    :param pstr_path: This parameter takes the screenshot save directory as path
    :type pstr_path: string
    :param pstr_tags: This parameter takes Tags as input
    :type pstr_tags: string
    :param pstr_end_time: This parameter takes the end date of execution as input
    :type pstr_end_time: String

    :return: Returns the Screen shot path to the user
    """
    try:
        pstr_tags = list(pstr_tags)
        if "ui_web" in pstr_tags:
            self.str_path = self.savescreenshotweb_s3(
                pstr_end_time, pytest.globalDict["driver"]
            )
        elif "ui_thick_client" in pstr_tags:
            self.str_path = self.savescreenshot_s3(pstr_end_time)
        elif "mobile_web" in pstr_tags:
            self.str_path = self.savescreenshotweb_s3(
                pstr_end_time, pytest.globalDict["mobile_driver"]
            )
        elif "mobile_app".lower() in pstr_tags:
            self.str_path = self.savescreenshotweb_s3(
                pstr_end_time, pytest.globalDict["mobile_driver"]
            )
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.str_path = str(e)
        raise Exception(e)
    return self.str_path

    def increment_value_for_key(self, pstr_key_name, pstr_filename):
    """
    Description: This method increments the count of a key in json
    :param pstr_key_name: This is the key to be incremented
    :param pstr_filename: This is the filename in which the key exists
    :return: None
    """
    try:
        thread_lock = threading.Semaphore()
        thread_lock.acquire()
        pbool_lock_acquired = False
        lock = LockFile(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_filename)
        while not lock.i_am_locking():
            try:
                lock.acquire(timeout=240)

                # wait up to 120 seconds
            except LockTimeout:
                lock.break_lock()
                lock.acquire()
        if lock.i_am_locking():
            pbool_lock_acquired = True
        with open(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_filename, "r") as readfile:
            data = json.load(readfile)
            readfile.close()
        temp = data
        if pstr_key_name in temp:
            int_count = int(temp[pstr_key_name])
            temp[pstr_key_name] = int_count + 1
        else:
            temp[pstr_key_name] = 1
        json_data = json.dumps(temp, indent=4)
        with open(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_filename, "w") as writefile:
            writefile.write(json_data)
            writefile.close()
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error occcured in increment_value_for_key-->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error occcured in increment_value_for_key-->" + str(e))
        raise Exception("Error occcured in increment_value_for_key-->" + str(e))
    finally:
        if pbool_lock_acquired:
            lock.release()
        thread_lock.release()

    insert_step(pstr_expectedvalue='NA', pstr_actualvalue='NA', pstr_status='IC', pstr_exception_log=None, pdict_perfstats='NA', pobj_api_response=None, pstr_scenario_level_log=False, plist_result_dataframes=None, pbool_takescreenshot=True, pstr_trim_exception_detail=None, pstr_exception_detail=None, **kwargs)

    Description: This method is to insert custom assertion/step into the reporting. :param pstr_expectedvalue: It is the expected value for an insertion assert :param pstr_actualvalue: It is the Actual value for an insertion assert :param pstr_status: It is the status for an insertion assert :param pobj_api_response: This is the api response object. In case user needs to push it to reporting :param plist_result_dataframes: This is the db result object/dataframe. In case user needs to push it to reporting :return: None

    def insert_step(
    self,
    pstr_expectedvalue="NA",
    pstr_actualvalue="NA",
    pstr_status="IC",
    pstr_exception_log=None,
    pdict_perfstats="NA",
    pobj_api_response=None,
    pstr_scenario_level_log=False,
    plist_result_dataframes=None,
    pbool_takescreenshot=True,
    pstr_trim_exception_detail=None,
    pstr_exception_detail=None,
    **kwargs,
):
    """
    Description: This method is to insert custom assertion/step into the reporting.
    :param pstr_expectedvalue: It is the expected value for an insertion assert
    :param pstr_actualvalue: It is the Actual value for an insertion assert
    :param pstr_status:  It is the status for an insertion assert
    :param pobj_api_response: This is the api response object. In case user needs to push it to reporting
    :param plist_result_dataframes: This is the db result object/dataframe. In case user needs to push it to reporting
    :return: None
    """

    try:
        pbool_execute_next_step_after_failure = kwargs.get(
            "pbool_execute_next_step_after_failure", False
        )
        str_grid_evidence = kwargs.get("str_grid_evidence", None)
        if str(pstr_status).strip().lower() not in ("fail", "pass"):
            pstr_status = "IC"
        pytest.globalDict["expected_scenariovalue"] = pstr_expectedvalue
        pytest.globalDict["actual_scenariovalue"] = pstr_actualvalue
        pytest.globalDict["step_status"] = pstr_status
        operation_id = None
        if self.is_report:
            pbool_stepid_exist = False
            self.logger = self.get_logger_for_this_file()
            if len(str(pstr_actualvalue)) > 1000:
                pstr_actualvalue = str(pstr_actualvalue)[0:990]
            if len(str(pstr_expectedvalue)) > 1000:
                pstr_expectedvalue = str(pstr_expectedvalue)[0:990]
            if os.environ.get("execution_id"):
                if pdict_perfstats != "NA":
                    self.push_performance_stats(pdict_perfstats)
                if globals().get(os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id"):
                    if os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id" in globals():
                        pbool_stepid_exist = True
                        step_id = globals().get(
                            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"
                        )
                        scen_tags = self.get_list_obj("scenario_tags")
                        str_evidence_path = None
                        str_additional_evidence = None
                        self.logger.info("Insert Step Data for " + str(pstr_actualvalue))
                        if any(item in self.take_screenshot_tags for item in scen_tags):
                            if pstr_status.lower() == "fail":
                                operation_id = self.captureOperationID()
                                if operation_id:
                                    operation_id = (
                                        "**************************************************************************************************"
                                        + "\n"
                                        + "Operation ID: "
                                        + str(operation_id)
                                        + "\n"
                                        + "**************************************************************************************************"
                                    )
                            if pbool_takescreenshot:
                                try:
                                    str_evidence_path = self.getscreenshot(
                                        self.get_current_date_time(), scen_tags
                                    )
                                except Exception as e1:
                                    str_evidence_path = None
                                    self.logger.info(
                                        "Attaching screenshot error - > " + str(e1)
                                    )
                                    if pstr_exception_detail:
                                        pstr_exception_detail = (
                                            str(pstr_exception_detail)
                                            + "\n"
                                            + "----ALSO NOTE ----"
                                            + "\n"
                                            + str(e1)
                                        )
                                    else:
                                        pstr_exception_detail = (
                                            "\n" + "----ALSO NOTE ----" + "\n" + str(e1)
                                        )
                        elif ("api" in scen_tags) and pobj_api_response != None:
                            try:
                                str_evidence_path = self.attach_api_request_response(
                                    pobj_api_response
                                )
                            except Exception as e2:
                                str_evidence_path = None
                                self.logger.info("Attaching API response error - > " + str(e2))
                                if pstr_exception_detail:
                                    pstr_exception_detail = (
                                        str(pstr_exception_detail)
                                        + "\n"
                                        + "----ALSO NOTE ----"
                                        + "\n"
                                        + str(e2)
                                    )
                                else:
                                    pstr_exception_detail = (
                                        "\n" + "----ALSO NOTE ----" + "\n" + str(e2)
                                    )
                        elif ("db" in scen_tags) and plist_result_dataframes != None:
                            str_source_label = kwargs.get(
                                "pstr_source_label", "Source_To_Target"
                            )
                            str_target_label = kwargs.get(
                                "pstr_target_label", "Target_To_Source"
                            )
                            str_common_label = kwargs.get("pstr_common_label", "Common")
                            try:
                                str_additional_evidence = self.__upload_dataframe_s3(
                                    plist_result_dataframes,
                                    pstr_source_label=str_source_label,
                                    pstr_target_label=str_target_label,
                                    pstr_common_label=str_common_label,
                                )
                            except Exception as e3:
                                self.logger.info(
                                    "Attaching dataframe evidence error - > " + str(e3)
                                )
                                str_additional_evidence = None
                                if pstr_exception_detail:
                                    pstr_exception_detail = (
                                        str(pstr_exception_detail)
                                        + "\n"
                                        + "----ALSO NOTE ----"
                                        + "\n"
                                        + str(e3)
                                    )
                                else:
                                    pstr_exception_detail = (
                                        "\n" + "----ALSO NOTE ----" + "\n" + str(e3)
                                    )
                        str_exception_path = None

                        str_inconclusive_test = "This is Inconclusive because either user has passed IC as the status of this insert step or has not passed status parameter while calling this insert_step method or status other than (pass /fail) was passed. So default status is IC"
                        if pstr_status == "IC":
                            if pstr_trim_exception_detail:
                                pstr_trim_exception_detail = (
                                    str(pstr_trim_exception_detail)
                                    + "\n"
                                    + "----ALSO NOTE ----"
                                    + "\n"
                                    + str_inconclusive_test
                                )
                            else:
                                pstr_trim_exception_detail = str_inconclusive_test
                        if pstr_trim_exception_detail:
                            if len(pstr_trim_exception_detail) > 3990:
                                pstr_trim_exception_detail = pstr_trim_exception_detail[0:3990]
                            if (
                                pstr_trim_exception_detail != "Exception Occured"
                                and not globals()[
                                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST")
                                    + "scenario_failure_reason"
                                ]
                            ):
                                globals()[
                                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST")
                                    + "scenario_failure_reason"
                                ] = pstr_trim_exception_detail

                        if not pstr_exception_detail and operation_id:
                            pstr_exception_detail = operation_id
                        if pstr_exception_detail:
                            if operation_id and pstr_exception_detail != operation_id:
                                pstr_exception_detail = pstr_exception_detail + operation_id
                            try:
                                if pstr_status == "IC":
                                    pstr_exception_detail = (
                                        str(pstr_exception_detail)
                                        + "\n\n\n"
                                        + "----ALSO NOTE ----"
                                        + "\n"
                                        + str_inconclusive_test
                                    )

                                if not globals()[
                                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST")
                                    + "scenario_failure_reason"
                                ]:
                                    globals()[
                                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST")
                                        + "scenario_failure_reason"
                                    ] = pstr_exception_detail

                                str_exception_path = (
                                    self.upload_exception_for_step_error_or_exception(
                                        pstr_exception_detail
                                    )
                                )

                                globals()[
                                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "failed_assert"
                                ] = "1"
                            except Exception as e4:
                                self.logger.info(
                                    "Error in upload_exception_for_step_error_or_exception error - > "
                                    + str(e4)
                                )
                        if not str_additional_evidence:
                            str_additional_evidence = str_grid_evidence
                        str_error_code = kwargs.get("pstr_error", CafeConstants.ERROR_CODE_ZERO)

                        self.python_client_reporting_utils.insert_assertion_data(
                            pstr_expectedvalue,
                            pstr_actualvalue,
                            pstr_status,
                            pstr_evidence_path=str_evidence_path,
                            pstr_exception_path=str_exception_path,
                            pstr_trim_exception=pstr_trim_exception_detail,
                            pstr_additional_evidence=str_additional_evidence,
                            pstr_error=str_error_code,
                            pstr_step_id=step_id,
                        )
                        globals()[
                            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + step_id + "_isAssertPresent"
                        ] = "1"
                        self.logger.info(
                            "Insert Step Data Complete for " + str(pstr_actualvalue)
                        )

    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        step_id = globals().get(os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id", "")
        if self.is_report:
            self.logger.error(
                f"Insert step error. Expected was {str(pstr_expectedvalue)} , actual was {str(pstr_actualvalue)}, str_evidence_path : {str(str_evidence_path)}, additional evidence: {str(str_additional_evidence)}, trim exception :{str(pstr_trim_exception_detail)} , StepId: {str(step_id)}"
            )
            self.cafe_logger.exception(
                f"Insert step error. Expected was {str(pstr_expectedvalue)} , actual was {str(pstr_actualvalue)}, str_evidence_path : {str(str_evidence_path)}, additional evidence: {str(str_additional_evidence)}, trim exception :{str(pstr_trim_exception_detail)} , StepId: {str(step_id)}"
            )
        self.logger.error(
            "Error occcured in insert_step -->" + f" Step id : {step_id} . Error is " + str(e)
        )
        self.cafe_logger.exception(
            "Error occcured in insert_step -->" + f" Step id : {step_id} . Error is " + str(e)
        )
    finally:
        if self.is_report:
            if pstr_status.lower() == "fail":
                globals()[
                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_failed"
                ] = "Yes"
                if pbool_stepid_exist:
                    self.set_step_failure()
                if not pbool_execute_next_step_after_failure and pbool_stepid_exist:
                    self.kibana_insert_step_failure(
                        pstr_expectedvalue, pstr_actualvalue, pstr_status
                    )
                else:
                    globals()[
                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "Fail_Scenario_at_the_end"
                    ] = "Yes"
                    globals()[
                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "pstr_expectedvalue"
                    ] = pstr_expectedvalue
                    globals()[
                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "pstr_actualvalue"
                    ] = pstr_actualvalue
            if pstr_status.lower() == "ic":
                globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_ic"] = "Yes"

    is_parallel_execution(plist_argslist)

    def is_parallel_execution(self, plist_argslist):
    """
    Description:
        |  This method is to check parallel execution

    :param plist_argslist: plist_argslist is the command line argumens
    :type plist_argslist: list

    :return: boolean
    """
    try:
        pbool_parallel = 0
        if "-c" in plist_argslist:
            pbool_parallel = 1
        for i in plist_argslist:
            if "-n=" in i:
                pbool_parallel = 1
                break
            if "--tests-per-worker" in i:
                pbool_parallel = 1
                break
            if "--workers" in i:
                pbool_parallel = 1
                break
            if "-n" == i:
                pbool_parallel = 1
                break

        return pbool_parallel
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error in is_parallel_execution-->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in is_parallel_execution-->" + str(e))

    def push_execution_data(self, pdict_data, str_dashboard_ui_url):
    """
    Description: This method is used to push execution data to Reporting
    :param pdict_data: This is the payload i.e the execution details to be pushed to reporting
    :return: None
    """
    try:
        os.environ["execution_id"], os.environ["ctBuildId"] = (
            self.python_client_reporting_utils.push_execution_details(pdict_data)
        )
        if not os.environ["execution_id"]:
            pytest.exit(
                "Execution ID could not be generated. Something wrong with the Reporting. Request you to turn off reporting flag and execute tests for now."
            )

        self.add_key_value_in_json(
            "executionId", os.environ["execution_id"], pstr_temp_execution_filename
        )
        print("EXECUTION ID : " + os.environ["execution_id"])
        self.cafe_logger.info("EXECUTION ID : " + os.environ["execution_id"])
        print("Results Dashboard Link : " + str_dashboard_ui_url + os.environ["execution_id"])
        self.cafe_logger.info(
            "Results Dashboard Link : " + str_dashboard_ui_url + os.environ["execution_id"]
        )
        os.environ["executionStartTime"] = self.get_current_date_time()

    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Execution data was " + str(pdict_data))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Execution data was " + str(pdict_data))
        self.logger.error("Error in push_execution_data-->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in push_execution_data-->" + str(e))
        pytest.exit("Error in push_execution_data-->" + str(e))

    def push_feature_data(self, pdict_data, pstr_feature_file_name):
    """
    Description: This method is to push the feature details to reporting
    :param pdict_data:  This is the payload that contains details to be pushed
    :param pstr_feature_file_name: This is the feature file name
    :return: None
    """
    try:
        if "execution_id" in os.environ:
            self.logger.info("Generating FeatureId")
            feature_id = self.python_client_reporting_utils.push_feature_details(pdict_data)

            if feature_id is not None and feature_id != "None" and feature_id != "":
                self.logger.info(
                    "New Feature ID Generated -> "
                    + str(feature_id)
                    + " for "
                    + pstr_feature_file_name
                )
                globals()["featureId_" + pstr_feature_file_name] = feature_id
                self.add_key_value_in_json(
                    "featureId_" + pstr_feature_file_name,
                    str(feature_id),
                    pstr_temp_feature_ids_filename,
                )
            else:
                self.logger.error(
                    "Feature ID was not generated while pushing the data  for feature file -"
                    + pstr_feature_file_name
                    + " --- Feature ID-> "
                    + str(feature_id)
                )
                self.logger.error("Feature Data tried to push was -> " + str(pdict_data))
                self.cafe_logger.exception(
                    "Feature ID was not generated while pushing data for feature file -"
                    + pstr_feature_file_name
                    + " --- Feature ID-> "
                    + str(feature_id)
                )
                self.cafe_logger.exception(
                    "Feature Data tried to push was -> " + str(pdict_data)
                )
        else:
            self.logger.warning(
                "Skipping push feature details as execution details were not sent. Could be due     to server down"
            )

    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Feature data was " + str(pdict_data))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Feature data was " + str(pdict_data))
        self.logger.error("Error occured in push_feature_data-->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error occured in push_feature_data-->" + str(e))

    def push_scenario_data(self, pdict_data):
    """
    Description: This method is used to push scenario data to Reporting
    :param pdict_data: This is the payload i.e the details to be pushed to reporting
    :return: None
    """
    try:
        globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id"] = (
            self.python_client_reporting_utils.push_scenario_details(pdict_data)
        )
        if (
            globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id"] is not None
            and globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id"]
            != "None"
            and globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id"] != ""
        ):
            self.logger.info(
                "New Scenario ID Generated -> "
                + str(globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id"])
            )
        else:
            self.logger.error(
                "Scenario Id not generated . Scenario Data tried to push was -> "
                + str(pdict_data)
            )
            self.cafe_logger.exception(
                "Scenario Id not generated . Scenario Data tried to push was -> "
                + str(pdict_data)
            )

    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Scenario Data is -> " + str(pdict_data))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Scenario Data is -> " + str(pdict_data))
        self.logger.error("Error in push_scenario_data-->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in push_scenario_data-->" + str(e))

    def push_step_data(self, pdict_data):
    """
    Description: This method is used to push step data to Reporting
    :param pdict_data: This is the payload i.e the step details to be pushed to reporting
    :return: None
    """
    try:
        if os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id" in globals():
            pdict_data["scenarioId"] = globals()[
                os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id"
            ]
            self.logger.info("Pushing step data is " + str(pdict_data))
            globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"] = (
                self.python_client_reporting_utils.push_step_details(pdict_data)
            )
            if (
                globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"] is not None
                and globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"]
                != "None"
                and globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"] != ""
            ):
                step_id = globals().get(
                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"
                )
                globals()[
                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + step_id + "_isAssertPresent"
                ] = "0"
                self.logger.info(
                    "New Step ID Generated -> "
                    + str(globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"])
                )
            else:
                self.logger.error(
                    "Step ID was not generated while pushing the data-> "
                    + str(globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"])
                )
                self.cafe_logger.exception(
                    "Step ID was not generated while pushing the data-> "
                    + str(globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"])
                )
                self.logger.error("Step Data tried to push was -> " + str(pdict_data))
                self.cafe_logger.exception("Step Data tried to push was -> " + str(pdict_data))

    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Step data was " + str(pdict_data))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Step data was " + str(pdict_data))
        self.logger.error("Error in push_step_data-->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in push_step_data-->" + str(e))

    def pytest_after_scenario_auto_dash_configuration(self, pobj_scenario, pobj_feature):
    """
    Description:
        |  this method is to perform a set of configuration  after a scenario get executes
    :param pobj_scenario: pobj_scenario is the scenario object which would be passed from the hooks
    :type pobj_scenario: object        :
    :param pobj_globaldict: pobj_feature is the pytest feature object
    :type pobj_globaldict: object
    """
    try:
        evidence = {}
        if self.is_report:
            self.logger.info(
                "Inside after scenario auto dash. Scenario Name: " + pobj_scenario.name
            )
            if "--lf" in sys.argv or os.environ["execution_id"]:
                self.logger.info("After Scenario Data collection Start")
                str_scenario_name_with_example = globals().get(
                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "str_scenario_name_with_example"
                )
                feature_file, feature_file_plus_feature_name = (
                    self.get_feature_file_and_its_name(pobj_feature)
                )
                scenario_details = self.get_dict_obj("current_scenario_details")
                if "scenarioStartTime" not in scenario_details:
                    scenario_details["scenarioStartTime"] = globals().get(
                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_start_time"
                    )
                if not globals().get("featureId_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name, None):
                    scenario_details["featureId"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                        "featureId_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name,
                        pstr_temp_feature_ids_filename,
                    )
                else:
                    scenario_details["featureId"] = globals().get(
                        "featureId_" + feature_file_plus_feature_name, None
                    )
                scenario_details["scenarioEndTime"] = self.get_current_date_time()
                scenario_details["scenarioDuration"] = self.get_time_difference_seconds(
                    scenario_details["scenarioEndTime"], scenario_details["scenarioStartTime"]
                )
                step_details = self.get_dict_obj("current_step_details")
                if step_details != {}:
                    if "stepStatus" not in step_details.keys():
                        step_details["stepStatus"] = "F"
                        scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] = "F"
                        step_details["stepEndTime"] = self.get_current_date_time()
                        step_details["stepDuration"] = self.get_time_difference_seconds(
                            step_details["stepEndTime"],
                            globals()[
                                os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_stepStartTime"
                            ],
                        )
                        step_details["evidence"] = {}
                        step_id = globals().get(
                            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"
                        )
                        evidence = {}
                        evidence = self.get_evidence_details("step")
                        step_details["evidence"] = evidence
                        self.update_step_data(step_details)
                    elif step_details["stepStatus"] == "F":
                        scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] = "F"
                    elif (
                        globals()[
                            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_failed"
                        ]
                        == "Yes"
                    ):
                        scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] = "F"
                        scenario_details["evidence"] = self.get_evidence_details("scenario")
                    elif step_details["stepStatus"] == "IC":
                        scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] = "IC"
                        if sys.exc_info():
                            if "Failed" in str(sys.exc_info()[0]):
                                step_details["stepStatus"] = "F"
                                scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] = "F"
                                step_details["stepEndTime"] = self.get_current_date_time()
                                step_details["stepDuration"] = self.get_time_difference_seconds(
                                    step_details["stepEndTime"],
                                    globals()[
                                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST")
                                        + "current_stepStartTime"
                                    ],
                                )
                                step_details["evidence"] = {}
                                step_id = globals().get(
                                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"
                                )
                                evidence = {}
                                evidence = self.get_evidence_details("step")
                                step_details["evidence"] = evidence
                                self.update_step_data(step_details)

                    elif (
                        globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_ic"]
                        == "Yes"
                    ):
                        scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] = "IC"
                    elif step_details["stepStatus"] == "P":
                        scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] = "P"

                elif (
                    globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_failed"]
                    == "Yes"
                ):
                    scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] = "F"
                    scenario_details["evidence"] = self.get_evidence_details("scenario")
                elif (
                    globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_ic"]
                    == "Yes"
                ):
                    scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] = "IC"
                else:
                    scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] = "IC"

                if (
                    globals().get(os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "performance_test")
                    == "Yes"
                ):
                    filename = globals().get(
                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "performance_stats_filename"
                    )
                    if os.path.isfile(self.str_project_path + os.sep + filename + ".json"):
                        dict_payload = {
                            "transactionName": "",
                            "_80percentile": "",
                            "_90percentile": "",
                            "averageResponseTime": "",
                            "minimumResponseTime": "",
                            "maxResponseTime": "",
                            "passCount": "",
                            "failCount": "",
                            "failDescription": "",
                            "totalRPS": "",
                            "duration": "",
                            "startTime": "",
                            "endTime": "",
                            "status": "",
                            "requestType": "",
                        }
                        str_upload_path = (
                            self.python_client_reporting_utils.upload_file_based_on_path(
                                self.str_project_path + os.sep + filename + ".json"
                            )
                        )
                        evidence = {"additionalEvidence": str_upload_path}
                        scenario_details["evidence"] = evidence
                    else:
                        self.logger.error(
                            "Could not find the perf stats file in project dir. File Name "
                            + filename
                        )
                        self.cafe_logger.exception(
                            "Could not find the perf stats file in project dir. File Name "
                            + filename
                        )

                if "--lf" in sys.argv:
                    scenario_details["reRunIteration"] = self.config_utils.base_config[
                        "rerun_iteration"
                    ]
                self.logger.info("Going to update Scenario Data")
                if "api" in pobj_scenario.tags:
                    if len(sys.exc_info()) >= 1:
                        if str(sys.exc_info()[0]).__contains__("Failed"):
                            if not globals()[
                                os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST")
                                + "scenario_failure_reason"
                            ]:
                                globals()[
                                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST")
                                    + "scenario_failure_reason"
                                ] = str(sys.exc_info()[1])

                    if (
                        len(
                            globals()[
                                os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "scenario_data_modify"
                            ]
                        )
                        != 0
                    ):
                        globals()[
                            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "scenario_data_modify"
                        ]["Scenario_Status"] = scenario_details["scenarioStatus"]
                        if globals()[
                            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "scenario_failure_reason"
                        ]:
                            globals()[
                                os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "scenario_data_modify"
                            ]["Scenario_Failure_Reason"] = globals().get(
                                os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST")
                                + "scenario_failure_reason"
                            )

                        # if len(globals()[os.environ.get('PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST') + "scenario_data_modify"]) != 0:
                        #     globals()[os.environ.get('PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST') + "scenario_data_modify"]['Scenario_Status'] = scenario_details['scenarioStatus']
                        #     if os.environ['scenario_failure_reason']:
                        #         globals()[os.environ.get('PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST') + "scenario_data_modify"]['Scenario_Failure_Reason'] = os.environ[
                        #             'scenario_failure_reason']

                        bool_artifacts = self.config_utils.is_api_artifacts()
                        if bool_artifacts:
                            self.scenario_add_key_value_in_json(
                                globals()[
                                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST")
                                    + "scenario_data_modify"
                                ],
                                "Scenario_report_Execution.json",
                            )
                            if scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] == "F":
                                self.scenario_add_key_value_in_json(
                                    globals()[
                                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST")
                                        + "scenario_data_modify"
                                    ],
                                    "Scenario_report_Fail.json",
                                )

                        scenario_details["evidence"] = evidence
                self.update_scenario_data(scenario_details)
                self.logger.info("Updated Scenario Data")
                str_key_passed = feature_file_plus_feature_name + "_TotalPassed"
                str_key_failed = feature_file_plus_feature_name + "_TotalFailed"
                str_key_inconclusive = feature_file_plus_feature_name + "_TotalInconclusive"
                while True:
                    try:
                        int_write_iteration = 10
                        lock = threading.Semaphore()
                        lock.acquire()
                        if pobj_scenario.failed:
                            if not "--lf" in sys.argv:
                                self.increment_value_for_key(
                                    str_key_failed,
                                    pstr_temp_feature_details_pass_fail_count_filename,
                                )
                                self.increment_value_for_key(
                                    "Execution_TotalFail", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                                )
                        elif scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] == "F":
                            if not "--lf" in sys.argv:
                                self.increment_value_for_key(
                                    str_key_failed,
                                    pstr_temp_feature_details_pass_fail_count_filename,
                                )
                                self.increment_value_for_key(
                                    "Execution_TotalFail", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                                )
                        elif scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] == "IC":
                            if not "--lf" in sys.argv:
                                self.increment_value_for_key(
                                    str_key_inconclusive,
                                    pstr_temp_feature_details_pass_fail_count_filename,
                                )
                                self.increment_value_for_key(
                                    "Execution_TotalInconclusive", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                                )
                        else:
                            self.increment_value_for_key(
                                str_key_passed,
                                pstr_temp_feature_details_pass_fail_count_filename,
                            )

                            if "--lf" in sys.argv:
                                self.logger.info(
                                    "Decrementing the failed count for feature : "
                                    + pstr_temp_feature_details_pass_fail_count_filename
                                )
                                self.decrement_value_for_key(
                                    str_key_failed,
                                    pstr_temp_feature_details_pass_fail_count_filename,
                                )

                                while True:
                                    int_decrement_iteration = 4
                                    try:
                                        self.decrement_value_for_key(
                                            "Execution_TotalFail", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                                        )
                                    except:
                                        int_decrement_iteration = int_decrement_iteration - 1
                                        if int_decrement_iteration < 0:
                                            break
                                        continue
                                    else:
                                        break
                                while True:
                                    int_increment_iteration = 4
                                    try:
                                        self.increment_value_for_key(
                                            "Execution_TotalPass", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                                        )
                                    except:
                                        int_increment_iteration = int_increment_iteration - 1
                                        if int_increment_iteration < 0:
                                            break
                                        continue
                                    else:
                                        break
                            else:
                                self.increment_value_for_key(
                                    "Execution_TotalPass", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                                )
                    except:
                        int_write_iteration = int_write_iteration - 1
                        lock.release()
                        if int_write_iteration < 0:
                            break
                        continue
                    else:
                        lock.release()
                        break

                if scenario_details["scenarioStatus"] == "F":
                    if "rerun_failures" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
                        is_rerun = self.config_utils.base_config["rerun_failures"]
                        if is_rerun:
                            self.add_key_value_in_json(
                                "failed_scenario_id_" + str_scenario_name_with_example,
                                globals().get(
                                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST")
                                    + "current_scenario_id"
                                ),
                                pstr_temp_failed_scenario_ids,
                            )

                self.logger.info("Going to update Feature Data")
                self.update_the_feature(feature_file_plus_feature_name)
                self.logger.info("Updated Feature Data")

                if (
                    globals()[
                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "Fail_Scenario_at_the_end"
                    ]
                    == "Yes"
                ):
                    self.kibana_insert_step_failure(
                        globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "pstr_expectedvalue"],
                        globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "pstr_actualvalue"],
                        "Fail",
                    )

    except Exception as e:
        exc_type, exc_obj, exc_tb = sys.exc_info()
        self.logger.error(
            "Error in after_scenario_auto_dash_configuration-->"
            + str(e)
            + " Line Number: "
            + str(exc_tb.tb_lineno)
        )
        self.cafe_logger.exception(
            "Error in after_scenario_auto_dash_configuration-->"
            + str(e)
            + " Line Number: "
            + str(exc_tb.tb_lineno)
        )
        self.print_exception_information()
    finally:
        self.pop_scenario_end_values()

    pytest_bdd_step_error()
