    def pytest_bdd_step_error(self):
    """
    Description: This is the pytest hook which is called after a step fails.
    :return: None
    """
    try:
        if self.is_report:
            if os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id" in globals():
                step_id = globals().get(
                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_id"
                )
                step_details = self.get_dict_obj("current_step_details")
                evidence = {}
                evidence = self.get_evidence_details("step")
                step_details["evidence"] = evidence
                step_details["stepStatus"] = "F"
                globals()[
                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_failed"
                ] = "Yes"
                step_details["stepEndTime"] = self.get_current_date_time()
                step_details["stepDuration"] = self.get_time_difference_seconds(
                    step_details["stepEndTime"],
                    globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_stepStartTime"],
                )
                globals()[os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_step_details"] = str(
                    step_details
                )
                self.update_step_data(step_details)

    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error in bdd_step_error-->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in bdd_step_error-->" + str(e))

    pytest_session_start_auto_dash_configuration(session)

    def pytest_session_start_auto_dash_configuration(self, session):
    """
    Description:
        |  this method is to session_start_auto_dash_configuration

    """
    try:
        env_config_util = ConfigUtils(os.getcwd())
        if self.is_report:
            if not os.path.exists(self.automation_log_path):
                os.mkdir(self.automation_log_path)
            self.logger = self.get_logger_for_this_file()
            if os.environ.get("PYTEST_XDIST_WORKER", "master") == "master":

                if os.path.isfile(
                    self.automation_log_path + os.sep + "Scenario_report_Execution.json"
                ):
                    os.remove(
                        self.automation_log_path + os.sep + "Scenario_report_Execution.json"
                    )
                if os.path.isfile(
                    self.automation_log_path + os.sep + "Scenario_report_Execution.json.lock"
                ):
                    os.remove(
                        self.automation_log_path
                        + os.sep
                        + "Scenario_report_Execution.json.lock"
                    )
                if os.path.isfile(
                    self.automation_log_path + os.sep + "Scenario_report_Fail.json"
                ):
                    os.remove(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + "Scenario_report_Fail.json")
                if os.path.isfile(
                    self.automation_log_path + os.sep + "Scenario_report_Fail.json.lock"
                ):
                    os.remove(
                        self.automation_log_path + os.sep + "Scenario_report_Fail.json.lock"
                    )

                if not "--lf" in sys.argv:
                    self.abort_last_terminated_execution()
                    self.delete_file_lock_files()
                    self.delete_execution_files()
                    self.create_empty_json(
                        self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_temp_execution_filename
                    )
                    self.create_empty_json(
                        self.automation_log_path
                        + os.sep
                        + pstr_temp_feature_details_pass_fail_count_filename
                    )
                    self.create_empty_json(
                        self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_temp_feature_ids_filename
                    )
                    self.create_empty_json(
                        self.automation_log_path
                        + os.sep
                        + pstr_temp_feature_data_to_push_filename
                    )
                    self.create_empty_json(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_temp_misc)
                    self.create_empty_json(
                        self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_temp_release_tag_file
                    )
                    self.create_empty_json(
                        self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_team_release_tag_names_file
                    )
                    self.create_empty_json(
                        self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_temp_functional_tag_file
                    )
                    self.create_empty_json(
                        self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_temp_team_tag_file
                    )
                    self.create_empty_json(
                        self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_temp_platform_tag_file
                    )
                    self.create_empty_json(
                        self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_temp_products
                    )
                    self.create_empty_json(
                        self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_temp_failed_scenario_ids
                    )
                    self.create_empty_json(
                        self.automation_log_path
                        + os.sep
                        + pstr_temp_skip_feature_names_with_reason
                    )
                    self.add_key_value_in_json(
                        "ExecutionComplete", False, pstr_temp_execution_filename
                    )
                    self.logger.info("Collecting the look up info")
                    self.collect_lookup_info()
                    self.logger.info("Collected lookup info")
                    execution_details = {
                        "executionStatus": "L",
                        "executionStartTime": None,
                        "executionDuration": 0,
                        "runCommand": None,
                        "executionTags": None,
                        "isBdd": 1,
                        "frameworkId": None,
                        "browser": self.config_utils.fetch_current_browser(),
                        "isCTBuild": 1,
                        "isReRun": 0,
                        "isPerformanceExecution": 0,
                    }
                    ctDetails = {}
                    exec_start_time = self.get_current_date_time()
                    if "rerun_failures" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
                        is_rerun = self.config_utils.base_config["rerun_failures"]
                        if is_rerun:
                            execution_details["isReRun"] = 1
                    os.environ["isCTBuild"] = "0"
                    if session.config.option.jenkins_build:
                        os.environ["isCTBuild"] = "1"
                        execution_details["isCTBuild"] = 2
                        ctDetails["triggeredBy"] = session.config.option.triggeredby
                        ctDetails["jenkinsSlaveName"] = session.config.option.jenkinsslavename
                        ctDetails["repoName"] = session.config.option.reponame
                        ctDetails["branchName"] = session.config.option.branchname
                        if (
                            session.config.option.devbuildnumber == "null"
                            or session.config.option.devbuildnumber == ""
                        ):
                            ctDetails["devBuildNumber"] = None
                        else:
                            ctDetails["devBuildNumber"] = session.config.option.devbuildnumber
                        ctDetails["jobBuildId"] = session.config.option.jenkins_build
                        ctDetails["executionStartTime"] = exec_start_time
                    cafe_version = importlib.metadata.version("cafe")
                    try:
                        python_client_version = importlib.metadata.version("python_client")
                    except Exception as e:
                        raise Exception(
                            "Python Client is not installed in the system. Please install the correct python client version. The error that occured while fetching python client version is "
                            + str(e)
                        )
                    execution_details["frameworkId"] = "4.0.0"
                    execution_details["clientVersion"] = python_client_version
                    execution_details["ctDetails"] = ctDetails
                    execution_details["isDebugExecution"] = self.get_execution_mode()
                    execution_details["executionStartTime"] = exec_start_time
                    self.add_key_value_in_json(
                        "executionStartTime", exec_start_time, pstr_temp_execution_filename
                    )
                    str_exec_env = (
                        str(env_config_util.base_config["execution_environment"])
                        .strip()
                        .lower()
                    )
                    os.environ["execution_environment"] = str_exec_env
                    execution_details["executionEnvironment"] = (
                        self.python_client_reporting_utils.get_execution_environment_code(
                            str_exec_env
                        )
                    )
                    if not execution_details["executionEnvironment"]:
                        pytest.globalDict["acceptable_environment_lookup"] = (
                            self.get_value_from_json(
                                "acceptable_environment_lookup", pstr_temp_misc
                            )
                        )
                        pytest.globalDict["acceptable_environment_values"] = pytest.globalDict[
                            "acceptable_environment_lookup"
                        ].keys()

                        self.cafe_logger.info(
                            "\n"
                            + "Your Execution Environment: ' "
                            + str_exec_env
                            + "' is not in list of acceptable environment. List of acceptable environments are "
                            + str(pytest.globalDict["acceptable_environment_values"])
                            + "\n"
                            + "Report will be generated but execution wont be considered for metrics charts in Executive Analsis Tab of QA Automation Dashboard"
                            + "\n"
                        )

                    if "use_grid" in env_config_util.base_config.keys():
                        execution_details["isGrid"] = int(
                            env_config_util.base_config["use_grid"]
                        )
                    else:
                        execution_details["isGrid"] = 0

                    execution_details["environment"] = (
                        env_config_util.base_config["environment"]
                        if "environment" in env_config_util.base_config.keys()
                        else None
                    )
                    execution_details["machineName"] = platform.uname()[1]
                    try:
                        if "userdomain" in os.environ:
                            str_username = os.environ["userdomain"] + os.sep + os.getlogin()
                        else:
                            str_username = os.getlogin()
                    except:
                        str_username = "NA"
                    execution_details["user"] = str_username
                    str_environment_type = env_config_util.base_config["environment_type"]
                    os.environ["environment_type"] = str_environment_type
                    lst_arguments = sys.argv
                    bool_parallel = self.get_int_value(
                        self.is_parallel_execution(lst_arguments)
                    )
                    execution_details["isParallel"] = bool_parallel
                    run_commands = lst_arguments
                    str_set_args = set(lst_arguments)
                    for str_argument in str_set_args:
                        str_argument = str(str_argument)
                        if "pytest" in str_argument or "py.test" in str_argument:
                            run_commands.remove(str_argument)
                        elif "features" in str_argument and "tests" in str_argument:
                            last_forward_slash = str(str_argument).rfind("/")
                            last_backward_slash = str(str_argument).rfind("\\")
                            str_arg = str(str_argument)[
                                max(last_forward_slash, last_backward_slash) + 1 :
                            ]
                            run_commands.remove(str_argument)
                            run_commands.append(str_arg)
                        elif "python" in str_argument:
                            run_commands.remove(str_argument)
                    execution_details["runCommand"] = run_commands
                    try:
                        for a in lst_arguments:
                            if "-m=" in a:
                                execution_details["executionTags"] = a.replace("-m=", "")
                            if "-m" == a:
                                int_index = lst_arguments.index(a)
                                execution_details["executionTags"] = lst_arguments[
                                    int_index + 1
                                ]
                            if "-k=" in a:
                                execution_details["executionTags"] = a.replace("-k=", "")
                            if "-k" == a:
                                int_index = lst_arguments.index(a)
                                execution_details["executionTags"] = lst_arguments[
                                    int_index + 1
                                ]
                    except Exception as ex:
                        self.logger.error("Error setting the execution tag " + str(ex))
                        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error setting the execution tag " + str(ex))

                    dashboard_ui_url = (
                        "https://dashboards-mi-qa.midevcld.spglobal.com/automation/execution/"
                    )
                    if (
                        "dashboard_ui_url" in env_config_util.base_config.keys()
                        and env_config_util.base_config["dashboard_ui_url"] is not None
                    ):
                        dashboard_ui_url = env_config_util.base_config["dashboard_ui_url"]

                    self.logger.info("Going to push Execution Data " + str(execution_details))
                    self.push_execution_data(execution_details, dashboard_ui_url)
                    self.logger.info("Pushed Execution Data Complete " + str(execution_details))
                    self.save_execution_details(execution_details)
                else:
                    self.logger.info("--------------------Rerun Logs--------------------")

    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error(
            "Error occured in pytest_session_start_auto_dash_configuration --> " + str(e)
        )
        self.cafe_logger.exception(
            "Error occured in pytest_session_start_auto_dash_configuration --> " + str(e)
        )
        pytest.exit(
            "Execution ID could not be generated. Either your python client version is not in line with cafe version or VPN is not connected or Reporting Services are down. \n Try one more time. If issue persists. Try executing with reporting flag to false. \n Error -> "
            + str(e)
        )

    def savescreenshot_s3(self, pstr_end_time):
    """
    Description:
       |  This method is used to save screen shots
    :param pstr_end_time: This parameter takes the end date of execution as input
    :type pstr_end_time: String
    :return: Returns string Screenshot saved path
    """
    try:
        self.str_screenshotvalue = (
            pstr_end_time.replace("-", "")
            .replace(" ", "")
            .replace("+", "")
            .replace(":", "")
            .replace(".", "")
        )

        session = self.python_client_reporting_utils.open_aws_session()
        self.cli = self.python_client_reporting_utils.open_s3_client(session)

        self.str_screenshotname = self.str_screenshotvalue + ".png"
        image_object = pyautogui.screenshot()
        imgByteArr = io.BytesIO()
        image_object.save(imgByteArr, format="PNG")
        imgByteArr = imgByteArr.getvalue()
        pstr_execution_id = os.environ["execution_id"]
        encoded = base64.b64encode(imgByteArr)
        str_path = self.python_client_reporting_utils.save_screenshot(
            self.cli, encoded, pstr_execution_id, self.str_screenshotname
        )
        return str_path
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error while saving screenshot" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error while saving screenshot" + str(e))
        raise Exception(e)
    return str_path

    def savescreenshotweb_s3(self, pstr_end_time, pstr_driver):
    """
    Description:
        |  This method is used to save screen shots of web applications

    :param pstr_screenshot_directory: This parameter takes the screen shot directory path
    :type pstr_screenshot_directory: String
    :param pstr_driver: This Parameter Takes the driver object
    :type pstr_driver: object
    :param pstr_end_time: This parameter takes the end date of execution as input
    :type pstr_end_time: String

    :return: Returns string Screenshot saved path
    """
    try:
        self.str_screenshotvalue = (
            pstr_end_time.replace("-", "")
            .replace(" ", "")
            .replace("+", "")
            .replace(":", "")
            .replace(".", "")
        )
        session = self.python_client_reporting_utils.open_aws_session()
        self.cli = self.python_client_reporting_utils.open_s3_client(session)
        pstr_execution_id = os.environ["execution_id"]
        self.str_screenshotname = self.str_screenshotvalue + ".png"
        try:
            if "ui_web" in pytest.globalDict["scenario_tags"]:
                if pstr_driver.window_handles is not None:
                    self.image_object = pstr_driver.get_screenshot_as_png()
                    encoded = base64.b64encode(self.image_object)

                    str_path = self.python_client_reporting_utils.save_screenshot(
                        self.cli, encoded, pstr_execution_id, self.str_screenshotname
                    )
                    return str_path
            else:
                self.image_object = pstr_driver.get_screenshot_as_png()
                encoded = base64.b64encode(self.image_object)
                str_path = self.python_client_reporting_utils.save_screenshot(
                    self.cli, encoded, pstr_execution_id, self.str_screenshotname
                )
                return str_path

        except Exception as e1:
            self.str_final_path = (
                self.str_s3_screenshot_path
                + self.str_bucket_directory
                + "noscreenshot%2Fnoscreenshot.png"
            )
            raise Exception("Exception occurred while taking screenshot -> " + str(e1))

        self.str_final_path = self.python_client_reporting_utils.get_screenshot_path(
            pstr_execution_id, self.str_screenshotname
        )
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error while saving screenshot " + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error while saving screenshot " + str(e))
        raise Exception("Exception occurred while saving screenshot -> " + str(e))
        self.str_final_path = str(e)
    return self.str_final_path

    def scenario_add_key_value_in_json(self, json_data, pstr_filename, pbool_fail=False):
    """
    Description: This is the method which adds the key value pair in json file
    :param pstr_key: This is the key to be added
    :param pstr_value: This is the value to be added
    :param pstr_filename: This is the filename in which key value to be added
    :return: None
    """
    try:

        thread_lock = threading.Semaphore()
        thread_lock.acquire()
        pbool_lock_acquired = False
        lock = LockFile(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_filename)
        while not lock.i_am_locking():
            try:
                lock.acquire(timeout=240)
            except LockTimeout:
                lock.break_lock()
                lock.acquire()
        if lock.i_am_locking():
            pbool_lock_acquired = True
        if os.path.isdir(self.automation_log_path):
            if not os.path.isfile(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_filename):
                if not pbool_fail:
                    sce_data = {"Execution_Report": []}
                else:
                    sce_data = {"Failed_Execution": json_data}
                scenario_report_file = open(
                    self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_filename, "w", encoding="utf-8"
                )
                json.dump(sce_data, scenario_report_file)
                scenario_report_file.close()
        if not pbool_fail:
            with open(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_filename, "r") as readfile:
                data = json.load(readfile)
                readfile.close()
            temp = data
            temp["Execution_Report"].append(json_data)

            binary1 = ast.literal_eval(str(temp))
            # json_data = json.dumps(binary1, indent=4)
            with open(self.automation_log_path + os.sep + pstr_filename, "w") as writefile:
                json.dump(binary1, writefile)
                # writefile.write(json_data)
                writefile.close()

    except Exception as e:
        self.logger.error("Error occcured in add_key_value_in_json-->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error occcured in add_key_value_in_json-->" + str(e))
    finally:
        if pbool_lock_acquired:
            lock.release()
        thread_lock.release()

    def session_finish_auto_dash_configuration(self, session):
    """
    Description: This method is to update the execution details of a particular execution.
    :param session: This is the pytest session object
    :return:None
    """
    try:
        pbool_execution_complete = False
        if self.is_report:
            if os.environ.get("PYTEST_XDIST_WORKER", "master") == "master":
                if os.environ.get("execution_id"):
                    self.logger.info("Inside session finish auto dash")
                    if not "--lf" in sys.argv:
                        ctDetails = {}
                        end_time = self.get_current_date_time()
                        try:
                            if (
                                int(os.environ["isCTBuild"])
                                and os.environ["ctBuildId"] != "null"
                                and os.environ["ctBuildId"] != None
                                and os.environ["ctBuildId"]
                            ):
                                ctDetails["executionEndTime"] = end_time
                                self.python_client_reporting_utils.update_ct_details(
                                    ctDetails, os.environ["ctBuildId"]
                                )
                        except Exception as e1:
                            self.logger.warning(
                                "CT details could not be updated. Error -> " + str(e1)
                            )
                        reporter = session.config.pluginmanager.get_plugin("terminalreporter")
                        execution_details = globals().get("execution_details", {})
                        execution_details["executionEndTime"] = end_time
                        execution_details["executionDuration"] = (
                            self.get_time_difference_seconds(
                                execution_details["executionEndTime"],
                                execution_details["executionStartTime"],
                            )
                        )

                        execution_details["totalInconclusive"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                            "Execution_TotalInconclusive", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                        )

                        execution_details["totalSkipped"] = 0
                        execution_details["skippedTests"] = []
                        execution_details["scenariosCount"] = session.testscollected
                        if execution_details["scenariosCount"] == 0:
                            execution_details["scenariosCount"] = None
                        self.add_key_value_in_json(
                            "scenariosCount",
                            execution_details["scenariosCount"],
                            pstr_temp_execution_filename,
                        )
                        execution_details["totalPass"] = 0
                        if session.testscollected == 0 or session.exitstatus in range(2, 6):
                            execution_details["executionStatus"] = "A"
                        if "passed" in reporter.stats:
                            execution_details["totalPass"] = len(reporter.stats["passed"])
                        if "skipped" in reporter.stats:
                            execution_details["totalSkipped"] = len(reporter.stats["skipped"])
                            self.add_key_value_in_json(
                                "totalSkipped",
                                execution_details["totalSkipped"],
                                pstr_temp_execution_filename,
                            )
                            for eachlist in reporter.stats["skipped"]:
                                execution_details["skippedTests"].append(
                                    eachlist.fspath.replace("features/tests/", "").replace(
                                        "features\\tests", ""
                                    )
                                    + " ->  Module Name : "
                                    + eachlist.head_line.replace("'", "")
                                )

                        if execution_details["totalInconclusive"]:
                            execution_details["totalPass"] = self.get_int_value(
                                execution_details["totalPass"]
                            ) - self.get_int_value(execution_details["totalInconclusive"])
                        if "failed" in reporter.stats:
                            execution_details["totalFail"] = len(reporter.stats["failed"])
                        else:
                            execution_details["totalFail"] = 0
                        if "rerun_failures" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
                            config_utils = self.config_utils.base_config
                            need_to_rerun = config_utils["rerun_failures"]
                            if need_to_rerun and execution_details["totalFail"] > 0:
                                self.logger.info(
                                    "Keeping the status of execution Live as we need to rerun few cases"
                                )
                                execution_details["executionStatus"] = "L"
                            else:
                                execution_details["executionStatus"] = "C"
                                os.environ["execution_complete"] = "Yes"
                                pbool_execution_complete = True
                        else:
                            execution_details["executionStatus"] = "C"
                            pbool_execution_complete = True
                            os.environ["execution_complete"] = "Yes"

                        self.logger.info(
                            "Going to update execution Data " + str(execution_details)
                        )
                        execution_details.pop("executionStartTime")
                        execution_details.pop("ctDetails")
                        self.update_execution_data(execution_details)
                        self.add_key_value_in_json(
                            "Execution_TotalPass",
                            execution_details["totalPass"],
                            pstr_temp_execution_filename,
                        )
                        self.add_key_value_in_json(
                            "Execution_TotalFail",
                            execution_details["totalFail"],
                            pstr_temp_execution_filename,
                        )
                        self.delete_file_lock_files()
                        need_to_rerun = False
                        if "rerun_failures" in self.config_utils.base_config.keys():
                            config_utils = self.config_utils.base_config
                            need_to_rerun = config_utils["rerun_failures"]
                            if not need_to_rerun or execution_details["totalFail"] == 0:
                                self.remove_temp_json_files()

                        else:
                            self.remove_temp_json_files()

                    else:
                        self.logger.info("Inside session finish for rerun")
                        self.logger.info("Checking if all reruns are done")
                        pbool_execution_complete = False

                        ed = {}
                        ed["totalPass"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                            "Execution_TotalPass", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                        )
                        ed["totalFail"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                            "Execution_TotalFail", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                        )
                        ed["scenariosCount"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                            "scenariosCount", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                        )
                        if ed["scenariosCount"] == 0:
                            ed["scenariosCount"] = None
                        ed["executionStatus"] = "L"
                        ed["totalSkipped"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                            "totalSkipped", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                        )
                        ed["totalInconclusive"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                            "Execution_TotalInconclusive", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                        )
                        ed["executionEndTime"] = self.get_current_date_time()
                        ed["executionDuration"] = self.get_time_difference_seconds(
                            ed["executionEndTime"],
                            self.get_value_from_json(
                                "executionStartTime", pstr_temp_execution_filename
                            ),
                        )

                        config_utils = ConfigUtils(os.getcwd())
                        int_rerun_count = config_utils.base_config["rerun_failures_count"]
                        self.logger.info("Got rerun count " + str(int_rerun_count))
                        int_rerun_iteration = config_utils.base_config["rerun_iteration"]
                        self.logger.info("Got rerun iteration " + str(int_rerun_iteration))
                        pbool_failure_still_exists = self.check_failure_tests_exists()
                        self.logger.info(
                            "Got pbool_failure_still_exists " + str(pbool_failure_still_exists)
                        )
                        if (
                            int_rerun_count == int_rerun_iteration
                        ) or not pbool_failure_still_exists:
                            self.logger.info("Rerun completed. So deleting files")
                            ed["executionStatus"] = "C"
                            os.environ["execution_complete"] = "Yes"
                            pbool_execution_complete = True
                            self.remove_temp_json_files()
                        self.logger.info("Going to update rerun execution data")
                        self.update_execution_data(ed)

    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error in session_finish_auto_dash_configuration-->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception(
            "Error in session_finish_auto_dash_configuration-->" + str(e)
        )
    finally:
        if pbool_execution_complete:
            self.upload_execution_log_file()
            self.python_client_reporting_utils.terminate_token()

    def set_collected_count(self, session):
    """
    Description: This method sets the execution total scenarios count. i.e how many scenarios are collected for execution.
    :param session: this is pytest session object
    :return: None
    """
    try:
        if self.is_report:
            if not "--lf" in sys.argv:
                if (os.environ.get("PYTEST_XDIST_WORKER", "master") == "master") or (
                    os.environ.get("PYTEST_XDIST_WORKER", "master") == "gw0"
                ):
                    self.logger.info(
                        "Checking Node value "
                        + str(os.environ.get("PYTEST_XDIST_WORKER", "master"))
                    )
                    if os.environ.get("execution_id"):
                        self.logger.info("Updating the Scenarios Count")
                        execution_details = {}
                        execution_details["scenariosCount"] = len(session.items)
                        self.logger.info(
                            "Collected Scenarios count is " + str(len(session.items))
                        )
                        execution_details["executionStatus"] = "L"
                        if len(session.items) > 0:
                            self.add_key_value_in_json(
                                "scenariosCount",
                                len(session.items),
                                pstr_temp_execution_filename,
                            )
                            self.update_execution_data(execution_details)
                            execution_details["isPerformanceExecution"] = 0
                            self.logger.info("Updated the Scenarios Count")
    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Error in set_collected_count-->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in set_collected_count-->" + str(e))

    def set_endtime(self):
    """
    Description:
        |  This method is used to fetch the endtime in elastic format

    :return: string
    """
    self.str_endtime = str((datetime.datetime.now()).strftime("%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S.%f"))
    pytest.globalDict["End_Time"] = (datetime.datetime.utcnow()).strftime(
        "%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S.%f"
    )
    return self.str_endtime

    def set_lookup_content_globally(self):
    """
    Description: This method is to collect the look up values and store in global dictionary
    :return: None
    """
    try:
        if self.is_report:
            self.logger.info(
                "Setting look up content globally for "
                + str(os.environ.get("PYTEST_XDIST_WORKER", "master"))
            )
            pytest.globalDict["platformtag_lookup"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                "platformtag_lookup", pstr_temp_platform_tag_file
            )

                "team_lookup", pstr_temp_team_tag_file
            )
            pytest.globalDict["functionality_lookup"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                "functionality_lookup", pstr_temp_functional_tag_file
            )

                "optionaltags_lookup", pstr_temp_execution_filename
            )
            pytest.globalDict["scenariocategory_lookup"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                "scenariocategory_lookup", pstr_temp_execution_filename
            )
            pytest.globalDict["feature_optionaltags_lookup"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                "feature_optionaltags_lookup", pstr_temp_execution_filename
            )

            pytest.globalDict["releasesprint_lookup"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                "releasesprint_lookup", pstr_temp_release_tag_file
            )
            pytest.globalDict["releasesprint_tag_name_lookup"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                "releasesprint_tag_name_lookup", pstr_temp_release_tag_file
            )
            pytest.globalDict["testdatatype_lookup"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                "testdatatype_lookup", pstr_temp_misc
            )
            pytest.globalDict["acceptable_environment_lookup"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                "acceptable_environment_lookup", pstr_temp_misc
            )

            pytest.globalDict["priority_lookup"] = self.get_value_from_json(
                "priority_lookup", pstr_temp_misc
            )

                "automationstatus_lookup", pstr_temp_misc
            )

                "testingtype_lookup", pstr_temp_misc
            )

                "product_lookup", pstr_temp_products

                "platform_lookup", pstr_temp_misc

    def update_execution_data(self, pdict_data):

    Description: This method is to call the api to update the execution data after execution is completed
    :param pdict_data: This is the payload containing details to be pushed

    def update_feature_data(self, pdict_data, pstr_feature_file_name):
    """
    Description: This method is used to update feaure data to Reporting
    :param pdict_data: This is the payload i.e the feature details to be updated to reporting
    :return: None
    """
    try:
        self.logger.info(
            "Updating the feature data for -" + pstr_feature_file_name + " : " + str(pdict_data)
        )
        if os.environ.get("execution_id"):
            if not globals().get("featureId_" + pstr_feature_file_name, None):
                featureid = self.get_value_from_json(
                    "featureId_" + pstr_feature_file_name, pstr_temp_feature_ids_filename
                )
            else:
                featureid = globals().get("featureId_" + pstr_feature_file_name, None)

            int_iteration = 5
            while int_iteration > 0:
                int_iteration = int_iteration - 1
                if not featureid:
                    self.logger.warning(
                        "Feature could not be read from Execution.json file. Trying again for feature name->"
                        + pstr_feature_file_name
                        + " featureid value -> "
                        + str(featureid)
                    )
                    int_iteration_count = 5
                    while True:
                        try:
                            if not globals().get("featureId_" + pstr_feature_file_name, None):
                                featureid = self.get_value_from_json(
                                    "featureId_" + pstr_feature_file_name,
                                    pstr_temp_feature_ids_filename,
                                )
                            else:
                                featureid = globals().get(
                                    "featureId_" + pstr_feature_file_name, None
                                )
                        except:
                            int_iteration_count = int_iteration_count - 1
                            if int_iteration_count < 0:
                                break
                            continue
                        else:
                            break
                else:
                    break
            if featureid is not None and featureid != "None" and featureid != "":
                globals()["featureId_" + pstr_feature_file_name] = featureid
                self.logger.info(
                    "Updating the feature data with feature Id "
                    + str(featureid)
                    + " and the data is "
                    + str(pdict_data)
                )
                self.python_client_reporting_utils.update_feature_details(pdict_data, featureid)
                self.logger.info("Feature ID Updated ->" + str(featureid))
            else:
                self.logger.error(
                    "Not Updating the feature data with feature Id "
                    + str(featureid)
                    + "Feature File Name: "
                    + pstr_feature_file_name
                )
                self.cafe_logger.exception(
                    "Not Updating the feature data with feature Id "
                    + str(featureid)
                    + "Feature File Name: "
                    + pstr_feature_file_name
                )

        else:
            self.logger.warning(
                "Feature data was not udpated as there is no Execution Id in environ variables"
            )

    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Feature data was " + str(pdict_data))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Feature data was " + str(pdict_data))
        self.logger.error("Error in update_feature_data-->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in update_feature_data-->" + str(e))

    def update_scenario_data(self, pdict_data):
    """
    Description: This method is used to update scenario data to Reporting
    :param pdict_data: This is the payload i.e the scenario details to be updated to reporting
    :return: None
    """
    try:
        int_iteration = 0
        while True:
            int_iteration += 1
            if globals().get(os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id"):
                self.logger.info("Going to update scenario data with data " + str(pdict_data))
                self.python_client_reporting_utils.update_scenario_details(
                    pdict_data,
                    globals().get(
                        os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id"
                    ),
                )
                self.logger.info(
                    "Scenario ID Updated -> "
                    + str(
                        globals().get(
                            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id"
                        )
                    )
                )
                break
            elif int_iteration > 5:
                self.logger.info(
                    "Scenario ID could not be Updated -> as current_scenario_id is:  "
                    + str(
                        globals().get(
                            os.environ.get("PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST") + "current_scenario_id"
                        )
                    )
                )
                break

    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error("Scenario Data was -> " + str(pdict_data))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Scenario Data was -> " + str(pdict_data))
        self.logger.error("Error in update_scenario_data-->" + str(e))
        self.cafe_logger.exception("Error in update_scenario_data-->" + str(e))

    def upload_exception_for_step_error_or_exception(self, pstr_exception_log):
    """
    Description:
        |  This method creates documentation of an API call into a json file and uploads it onto the S3

    :param pobj_api_response: API Response Object
    :type pobj_api_response: Response
    :return: None
    """
    try:
        if pstr_exception_log:
            final_string = ""
            final_string += "************************************************************************************************************************"
            final_string += "\n"
            final_string += "************************************************Error/Exceptions********************************************************"
            final_string += "\n"
            final_string += "************************************************************************************************************************"
            final_string += "\n"
            final_string += "\n"
            final_string += "\n"
            final_string += str(pstr_exception_log)
            binary = bytes(final_string, "utf-8")
            self.json_path_value = (
                self.set_endtime()
                .replace("-", "")
                .replace(" ", "")
                .replace("+", "")
                .replace(":", "")
                .replace(".", "")
            )

            session = self.python_client_reporting_utils.open_aws_session()
            self.cli = self.python_client_reporting_utils.open_s3_client(session)
            pstr_execution_id = os.environ["execution_id"]
            encoded = base64.b64encode(binary)
            return self.python_client_reporting_utils.save_string_data(
                self.cli, encoded, pstr_execution_id, self.json_path_value
            )

    except Exception as e:
        self.print_exception_information()
        self.logger.error(
            "Exception occurred in upload_exception_for_step_error_or_exception" + str(e)
        )
        self.cafe_logger.exception(
            "Exception occurred in upload_exception_for_step_error_or_exception" + str(e)
        )
